      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Staphylococcus aureus, a common bacterial pathogen that can be present in airborne droplets and aerosols and is targeted by phage-coupled nanoparticle detection platforms. | A bacterial pathogen referenced as the target for rapid DNA extraction using a handheld lateral flow strip from cells spiked into various samples; relevant to environmental and clinical detection workflows.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_83</data>
