    </node>
    <node id="PCR">
      <data key="d0">PCR</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Polymerase chain reaction, a nucleic acid amplification method used here in combination with dual-mode colorimetric–fluorescence biosensors for rapid and sensitive detection of Salmonella. | Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) is a thermal cycling-based nucleic acid amplification method that requires heat-induced denaturation and a high-precision thermal cycler; it serves as a reference standard against which isothermal methods are compared in terms of workflow complexity and instrumentation requirements. | Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) is a nucleic acid amplification method used as the laboratory-based gold standard molecular test for detecting SARS-CoV-2 genetic material, offering high sensitivity and specificity. | Polymerase chain reaction used as a molecular amplification and confirmation method to cross-check and validate the results of the capacitive biosensor for airborne H5N1 and E. coli detection. | Polymerase chain reaction (PCR), a thermal nucleic acid amplification method used for detection of carbapenemase-producing Enterobacteriaceae (CPE) and other pathogens, but limited by longer turnaround time, labor intensity, and need for specialized equipment.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_215,f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_520</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">PCR</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SALMONELLA">
      <data key="d0">SALMONELLA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A pathogenic genus of bacteria; in this context it is the target organism for dual-mode PCR-coupled biosensors designed for rapid and sensitive detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_215,f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_520</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-BASED DETECTION SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-BASED DETECTION SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of nucleic-acid-based biosensor platforms that use CRISPR effector enzymes and guide RNAs for detection; examples mentioned include SHERLOCK, DETECTR, and STOPCovid, used for viral diagnostics due to speed, specificity, and ease of use.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_215</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STOPCOVID">
      <data key="d0">STOPCOVID</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR-based biosensor platform designed for rapid detection of SARS-CoV-2 and other viral targets, highlighted as an emerging tool due to speed, specificity, and ease of use.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_215</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SHERLOCK TEST KIT">
      <data key="d0">SHERLOCK TEST KIT</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagnostic implementation of the SHERLOCK CRISPR assay that has received U.S. FDA EUA and is used clinically for detection of SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_215</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DETECTR TEST KIT">
      <data key="d0">DETECTR TEST KIT</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagnostic test kit based on the DETECTR CRISPR platform, authorized under U.S. FDA EUA for detection of SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_215</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FLUORESCENCE DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">FLUORESCENCE DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A reporter signal modality based on fluorescence, used in combination with AuNPs and in dual-mode biosensors to expand detection range and improve specificity. | A fluorescent readout modality used on-chip in the integrated influenza A microfluidic system and via smartphone in the COVID-19-targeted multiplexing system to indicate successful nucleic acid amplification and target detection. | A time-lapsed fluorescent signal captured by a smartphone in the lab-on-a-drone system, reporting successful PCR amplification of target nucleic acids.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_215</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
      <data key="d6">FLUORESCENCE SIGNAL DETECTION,FLUORESCENCE DETECTION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DUAL-MODE DETECTION METHOD (COLORIMETRIC–FLUORESCENCE)">
      <data key="d0">DUAL-MODE DETECTION METHOD (COLORIMETRIC–FLUORESCENCE)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A biosensor platform that combines colorimetric and fluorescence readouts together with PCR to achieve rapid and sensitive detection of Salmonella.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_215</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DUAL-MODE UCNPS–MB BIOSENSOR IN COMBINATION WITH PCR">
      <data key="d0">DUAL-MODE UCNPS–MB BIOSENSOR IN COMBINATION WITH PCR</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A specific dual-mode biosensor using upconversion nanoparticles (UCNPs) and molecular beacons (MB) together with PCR to sensitively detect Salmonella, providing colorimetric and fluorescence outputs.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_215</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ADESSO">
      <data key="d0">ADESSO</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">ADESSO (Accurate Detection of Evolving SARS-CoV-2 through SHERLOCK Optimization) is an optimized Cas13-based diagnostic platform derived from SHERLOCK, offering 96% sensitivity and 15-minute time-to-result for SARS-CoV-2 variant detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_216,f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_522</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REAL-TIME-MULTIPLEXED SHERLOCK ASSAY (REAL-TIME SLK)">
      <data key="d0">REAL-TIME-MULTIPLEXED SHERLOCK ASSAY (REAL-TIME SLK)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A real-time, multiplexed SHERLOCK-based in vitro diagnostic assay that enables simultaneous detection of multiple samples with sensitivity down to 5 copies/μL and a time to result under 30 minutes.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_216</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="96% SENSITIVITY (ADESSO)">
      <data key="d0">96% SENSITIVITY (ADESSO)</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">Performance metric for ADESSO indicating that the assay correctly identifies 96% of true positive SARS-CoV-2 cases under the reported validation conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_216</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="15 MIN TIME-TO-RESULT (ADESSO)">
      <data key="d0">15 MIN TIME-TO-RESULT (ADESSO)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Operational characteristic of the ADESSO assay, indicating that it can deliver SARS-CoV-2 detection results within approximately 15 minutes.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.65</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_216</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="5 COPIES/ΜL SENSITIVITY (REAL-TIME SLK)">
      <data key="d0">5 COPIES/ΜL SENSITIVITY (REAL-TIME SLK)</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">Reported analytical sensitivity of the real-time multiplexed SHERLOCK assay, capable of detecting target nucleic acids at concentrations as low as 5 copies per microliter.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_216</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&lt; 30 MIN TIME-TO-RESULT (REAL-TIME SLK)">
      <data key="d0">&lt; 30 MIN TIME-TO-RESULT (REAL-TIME SLK)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Operational characteristic of the real-time multiplexed SHERLOCK assay, indicating that it provides diagnostic results in under 30 minutes.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_216</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-BASED DETECTION OF BACTERIA, FUNGI AND PARASITES">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-BASED DETECTION OF BACTERIA, FUNGI AND PARASITES</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">General application of CRISPR-Cas nucleic acid detection assays, originally developed for viral diagnostics, expanded to detect other microorganisms including bacteria, fungi, and parasites.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_216</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR/CAS13-BASED DETECTION ASSAYS">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR/CAS13-BASED DETECTION ASSAYS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Genome-wide tiled and other CRISPR/Cas13-based nucleic acid detection assays used for diagnosing infectious diseases such as tuberculosis and schistosomiasis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_217</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SHERLOCK ONE-POT ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">SHERLOCK ONE-POT ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A one-pot CRISPR-based nucleic acid detection platform whose performance depends on compatibility and coordination of multiple enzymes in a single reaction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_217</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-DIRECTED INTEGRASE GENOME INSERTION SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-DIRECTED INTEGRASE GENOME INSERTION SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR-directed integrase platform enabling drag-and-drop insertion of large DNA sequences without double-strand DNA cleavage, primarily for genome engineering rather than diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.55</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_217</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NANOSCALE DYNAMIC CHEMICAL AND BIOLOGICAL SENSOR MATERIALS">
      <data key="d0">NANOSCALE DYNAMIC CHEMICAL AND BIOLOGICAL SENSOR MATERIALS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Nanoscale dynamic sensor material designs for chemical and biological sensing, aimed at control monitoring and early detection of advanced diseases.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_217</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CASPASE-3-RESPONSIVE NANOSENSORS FOR IN VIVO PHOTOACOUSTIC MONITORING">
      <data key="d0">CASPASE-3-RESPONSIVE NANOSENSORS FOR IN VIVO PHOTOACOUSTIC MONITORING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Implantable nanosensors that respond to caspase-3 activity and enable in vivo photoacoustic monitoring of stem cell location and apoptosis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_217</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="IMPLANTABLE NANOSENSORS FOR REAL-TIME ADRIAMYCIN MONITORING">
      <data key="d0">IMPLANTABLE NANOSENSORS FOR REAL-TIME ADRIAMYCIN MONITORING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Minimally invasive implantable nanosensors capable of real-time detection of adriamycin levels in the body to help assess clinical drug use.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_217</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HAEMOPHILUS INFLUENZAE">
      <data key="d0">HAEMOPHILUS INFLUENZAE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Haemophilus influenzae is a respiratory bacterium that can be transmitted via aerosols and droplets, making it relevant as an airborne pathogen in the context of respiratory infections and air-based detection or intervention strategies.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_226</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STREPTOCOCCUS PNEUMONIAE">
      <data key="d0">STREPTOCOCCUS PNEUMONIAE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Streptococcus pneumoniae is a major respiratory pathogen spread through airborne droplets, frequently implicated in pneumonia and other invasive diseases, and is a key target for airborne pathogen monitoring and control.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_226</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MULTIDRUG-RESISTANT BACTERIA">
      <data key="d0">MULTIDRUG-RESISTANT BACTERIA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">In this context, "multidrug-resistant bacteria" refers to bacterial strains resistant to multiple antibiotics, some of which can be transmitted via respiratory droplets or aerosols in clinical and community settings, making them relevant airborne targets for surveillance and intervention.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_226</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COVID-19">
      <data key="d0">COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">COVID-19, caused by SARS-CoV-2, is a viral respiratory disease transmitted primarily via aerosols and droplets, and is a central airborne pathogen of interest for nanoparticle-based antiviral strategies and biosensing. | Coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19), a respiratory infectious disease caused by SARS-CoV-2, discussed as the primary viral infection motivating the development and deployment of rapid, sensitive diagnostic systems and integrated micro- and nanosystems for nucleic acid-based virus detection. | The airborne viral pathogen (SARS-CoV-2 infection) targeted by the described optical biosensing platforms for diagnostic detection. | The disease caused by SARS-CoV-2, referenced to illustrate how suboptimal biological sampling during the COVID-19 pandemic led to false-negative diagnostic test results, motivating inclusion of internal controls. | The respiratory disease caused by the airborne coronavirus SARS-CoV-2; in the cited work, host antibodies specific to this pathogen are detected using a rapid electrochemical biosensor based on 3D graphene electrodes.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_226,f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_544,f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_548,f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_549</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
      <data key="d6">COVID-19</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SEVERE ACUTE RESPIRATORY SYNDROME (SARS)">
      <data key="d0">SEVERE ACUTE RESPIRATORY SYNDROME (SARS)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) is a viral respiratory illness caused by SARS-CoV, characterized by efficient person-to-person transmission via respiratory droplets and aerosols, making it a key airborne pathogen for epidemiological monitoring and potential biosensor-based air surveillance.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_293</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INFLUENZA VIRUSES CIRCULATING IN 2009">
      <data key="d0">INFLUENZA VIRUSES CIRCULATING IN 2009</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Influenza viruses circulating in 2009, including the pandemic H1N1 strain, spread predominantly through respiratory droplets and aerosols and are treated as airborne pathogens of interest for public health surveillance and biosensor detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_293</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MIDDLE EAST RESPIRATORY SYNDROME">
      <data key="d0">MIDDLE EAST RESPIRATORY SYNDROME</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Middle East respiratory syndrome (MERS), caused by MERS-CoV, is a severe respiratory disease transmitted primarily via respiratory droplets and close contact, as reviewed in the 2015 Lancet article.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_294</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EBOLA VIRUS DISEASE">
      <data key="d0">EBOLA VIRUS DISEASE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Ebola virus disease is a severe viral hemorrhagic fever caused by Ebola virus; although mainly spread via direct contact with bodily fluids and not classically airborne, it is included here as a pathogen of interest from the 2019 Lancet article.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.4</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_294</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ZIKA VIRUS DISEASE">
      <data key="d0">ZIKA VIRUS DISEASE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Zika virus disease, caused by Zika virus and primarily transmitted by Aedes mosquitoes rather than via the air, is included as a pathogen of interest from the New England Journal of Medicine preliminary report.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.3</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_294</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LASSA VIRUS">
      <data key="d0">LASSA VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Lassa virus is an arenavirus that can be transmitted via aerosols from rodent excreta and is targeted by glycoprotein nanoparticle vaccines that elicit neutralizing antibody responses and protection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_313</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PR8 INFLUENZA VIRUS">
      <data key="d0">PR8 INFLUENZA VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">The PR8 influenza virus (A/Puerto Rico/8/34 H1N1) is a laboratory strain of influenza A commonly used in vaccine and nasal immunization studies relevant to airborne influenza infection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_334</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SERS IMAGING-BASED APTASENSOR FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS A">
      <data key="d0">SERS IMAGING-BASED APTASENSOR FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS A</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A surface-enhanced Raman scattering (SERS) imaging-based aptamer sensor designed for ultrasensitive and reproducible detection of influenza virus A.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_341</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="VIRUS-BINDING PHAGE NANOFIBER–GOLD NANOPARTICLE BIOSENSOR">
      <data key="d0">VIRUS-BINDING PHAGE NANOFIBER–GOLD NANOPARTICLE BIOSENSOR</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A biosensor platform using virus-binding phage nanofibers decorated with gold nanoparticles for rapid, reliable, and ultrasensitive detection of pathogenic H9N2 viruses.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_341</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PATHOGENIC H9N2 VIRUSES">
