    <node id="ALL-IN-ONE DUAL CRISPR-CAS12A ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">ALL-IN-ONE DUAL CRISPR-CAS12A ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An integrated, ultrasensitive, visual nucleic acid detection platform that combines two CRISPR-Cas12a reactions in a single tube for SARS-CoV-2 detection. | A CRISPR-Cas12a–based all-in-one dual-target diagnostic assay for ultrasensitive and visual detection of SARS-CoV-2, designed for rapid, field-deployable use and compatible with isothermal amplification workflows. | An all-in-one dual CRISPR-Cas12a assay described by Ding et al. that enables ultrasensitive and visual detection of SARS-CoV-2 by integrating dual Cas12a-based detection components into a single reaction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_346,f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_347</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b,4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
      <data key="d6">ALL-IN-ONE DUAL CRISPR-CAS12A ASSAY</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-CAS13A">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-CAS13A</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR system built around the Cas13a nuclease, providing programmable RNA recognition and collateral cleavage in the amplification-free SARS-CoV-2 detection platform. | A CRISPR system based on the Cas12a effector nuclease that mediates sequence-specific DNA recognition and collateral cleavage in the all-in-one dual SARS-CoV-2 assay. | A DNA-targeting CRISPR effector nuclease (Cas12a) with target-activated collateral single-stranded DNA cleavage, used in assays such as AIOD-CRISPR for rapid nucleic acid detection. | An RNA-targeting CRISPR effector enzyme used in the fully microfluidic Ebola virus assay to generate a detection signal via collateral cleavage. | A Cas12a effector nuclease used in CRISPR diagnostics; upon binding its target nucleic acid, it unleashes indiscriminate single-stranded DNase activity that is exploited for signal amplification in nucleic acid detection assays. | A CRISPR effector nuclease (Cas12a) described as a promising detection mechanism within an HPAI surveillance framework, providing laboratory-grade analytical sensitivity with potential for practical on-farm deployment when integrated into suitable biosensor formats. | A Cas12-family CRISPR effector system discussed by Yan et al. (2019) as a lesser-known sibling of Cas9, relevant to nucleic acid detection applications. | A CRISPR effector nuclease (Cas12a) that, upon target recognition, exhibits collateral cleavage of single-stranded DNA, enabling sensitive nucleic acid detection in biosensor formats.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_346</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">CRISPR-CAS12A,CRISPR-CAS13A,CRISPR-CAS12</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DUAL CRISPR-CAS12A">
      <data key="d0">DUAL CRISPR-CAS12A</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">A dual-configuration CRISPR-Cas12a setup in which two Cas12a-mediated reactions are combined within one assay to enhance sensitivity and robustness for SARS-CoV-2 detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_346</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-BASED DIAGNOSTICS">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-BASED DIAGNOSTICS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">CRISPR-based diagnostics refers to a class of biosensor platforms that use CRISPR-Cas effectors such as Cas12a and Cas13 to detect nucleic acids from pathogens, leveraging programmable guide RNAs and collateral cleavage to generate measurable diagnostic signals. | CRISPR diagnostics refers to CRISPR-based nucleic acid detection platforms used for SARS-CoV-2 detection, leveraging CRISPR effector enzymes for sequence-specific identification of viral genetic material. | Modular CRISPR-based diagnostic assays that can be rapidly reprogrammed to detect different pathogens by replacing their guide RNA, making them strong candidates for rapid response to emerging infectious disease outbreaks. | A class of programmable nucleic acid detection platforms that use Cas12a for highly specific, on-site detection of viral RNA, suitable for rapid on-farm diagnostics. | A class of CRISPR effector–based nucleic acid diagnostic platforms described here as field-ready, rapid, and scalable tools that complement biosensor-based surveillance in poultry production environments, including on-farm AIV screening.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_347</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
      <data key="d6">CRISPR DIAGNOSTICS,CRISPR-CAS12A–BASED DIAGNOSTICS,CRISPR-BASED DIAGNOSTICS</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MASSIVELY MULTIPLEXED NUCLEIC ACID DETECTION WITH CAS13">
      <data key="d0">MASSIVELY MULTIPLEXED NUCLEIC ACID DETECTION WITH CAS13</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">The massively multiplexed nucleic acid detection system with Cas13, as described by Ackerman et al., is a CRISPR-based biosensor platform that uses Cas13 to simultaneously detect a large panel of nucleic acid targets, enabling high-throughput diagnostic or surveillance applications. | A CRISPR-based biosensor platform that uses Cas13 to simultaneously detect many nucleic acid targets in parallel, enabling high-throughput molecular diagnostics. | A high-plex CRISPR-Cas13-based platform for massively multiplexed nucleic acid detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.94</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_347</data>
      <data key="d5">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a,4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
