    <node id="MYCOBACTERIUM TUBERCULOSIS">
      <data key="d0">MYCOBACTERIUM TUBERCULOSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Mycobacterium tuberculosis is an airborne bacterial pathogen that causes tuberculosis and is transmitted via respiratory droplets; in this domain it represents a key target for biosensor-based air surveillance and detection assays. | Mycobacterium tuberculosis (Mtb) is the bacterial pathogen that causes tuberculosis (TB), a primarily airborne infectious disease transmitted via aerosolized droplets from infected individuals. It is highlighted as a major global health concern due to ∼1.5 million deaths annually, long and side-effect-prone treatment regimens, and the emergence of drug-resistant and multi-drug-resistant TB.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_359,f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_361,f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_401,f2b3cfad-751c-4e9d-a9ef-77be12b8fc1a_chunk_523</data>
