      <data key="d0">COMMERCIAL COVID-19 DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Commercial diagnostic platforms, including laboratory-based and point-of-care systems, that are approved by various regulators for COVID-19 testing and SARS-CoV-2 detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COMMERCIAL COVID-19 DIAGNOSTIC PRODUCTS APPROVED BY THE US FDA (THROUGH EMERGENCY USE AUTHORIZATION) AND HEALTH CANADA">
      <data key="d0">COMMERCIAL COVID-19 DIAGNOSTIC PRODUCTS APPROVED BY THE US FDA (THROUGH EMERGENCY USE AUTHORIZATION) AND HEALTH CANADA</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">The subset of commercial COVID-19 diagnostic products that have received Emergency Use Authorization from the US FDA and regulatory approval from Health Canada for SARS-CoV-2 detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NA-BASED TESTING">
      <data key="d0">NA-BASED TESTING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Nucleic-acid-based testing workflows for SARS-CoV-2, encompassing sample collection, viral RNA extraction, amplification, and signal readout for COVID-19 diagnosis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RNA EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">RNA EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A nucleic acid purification step in diagnostic workflows that isolates viral RNA from clinical specimens (e.g., nasal swabs) prior to nucleic-acid-based detection assays, often relying on consumables such as extraction columns. | Sample preparation procedures to isolate DNA from biological material, discussed in historical and current contexts as part of molecular diagnostic workflows. | A sample preparation step in which RNA is purified from collected specimens prior to isothermal amplification and CRISPR-based detection; included in the 45–60 minute total assay time.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_4,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_30,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_38,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
      <data key="d6">DNA EXTRACTION,RNA EXTRACTION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SAMPLE COLLECTION">
      <data key="d0">SAMPLE COLLECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">The initial pre-analytical step in diagnostic workflows in which clinical specimens (such as nasal swabs) are obtained from patients for subsequent nucleic acid extraction and analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_4,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NASAL SWAB COLLECTION">
      <data key="d0">NASAL SWAB COLLECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A specific sample collection procedure that uses nasal swabs to obtain upper respiratory specimens for downstream RNA extraction and NA-based virus detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NUCLEIC ACID EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">NUCLEIC ACID EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A generalized nucleic acid purification step that isolates viral nucleic acids (typically RNA for COVID-19) from collected samples, enabling NA-based virus detection on integrated micro- and nanosystems. | The preparatory step in which nucleic acids are extracted from clinical specimens prior to TRACE analysis; blinded testing of these extracts yielded MPXV signal only in samples from MPXV patients. | A nucleic-acid extraction step required prior to detection when applying the H5N1 electrochemical chip to clinical or environmental samples, forming part of a multistep sample-processing workflow. | A conventional sample preparation step involving isolation of nucleic acids, which the ANCA method is reported to bypass when detecting carbapenemase-producing bacteria in human samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_4,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">NUCLEIC ACID EXTRACTS,NUCLEIC-ACID EXTRACTION,NUCLEIC ACID EXTRACTION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-ON-A-CHIP">
      <data key="d0">LAB-ON-A-CHIP</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A highly integrated microfluidic diagnostic platform concept that miniaturizes and automates nucleic acid testing steps, including sample preprocessing, nucleic acid extraction, amplification, and signal detection for viral pathogens such as SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-IN-A-TUBE">
      <data key="d0">LAB-IN-A-TUBE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A compact diagnostic system concept in which nucleic acid testing workflows, including sample preprocessing, nucleic acid extraction, amplification, and signal detection, are integrated within a tube format for automated viral detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-IN-A-BOX">
      <data key="d0">LAB-IN-A-BOX</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An integrated diagnostic platform concept that packages sample preprocessing, nucleic acid extraction, amplification, and signal detection into a self-contained box-like system for point-of-care viral testing, including COVID-19.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LIONX DIAGNOSTIC PLATFORMS">
      <data key="d0">LIONX DIAGNOSTIC PLATFORMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A collective term for integrated 'lab-in/on-an-X' micro- and nanosystem diagnostic platforms that combine sample preprocessing, nucleic acid extraction, amplification, and signal detection to enable automated nucleic acid testing for viruses such as SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SAMPLE PREPROCESSING">
      <data key="d0">SAMPLE PREPROCESSING</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">An upstream processing step in integrated diagnostic platforms that prepares patient samples for nucleic acid extraction, helping to remove inhibitors and condition the sample for reliable amplification and detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NA EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">NA EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A general nucleic acid extraction step that isolates viral nucleic acids from patient samples as a critical preparatory step before amplification and signal detection in nucleic acid-based diagnostic assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_10,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_21,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_23,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_29,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A general nucleic acid amplification step used in testing workflows to increase the quantity of target viral RNA or cDNA, enabling sensitive detection in integrated diagnostic platforms. | A generic nucleic acid amplification step that is explicitly bypassed by the CRISPR-chip platform, indicating that the platform operates without pre-amplifying target nucleic acids.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
      <data key="d6">AMPLIFICATION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QUANTITATIVE RT-PCR (QRT-PCR)">
      <data key="d0">QUANTITATIVE RT-PCR (QRT-PCR)</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Quantitative reverse transcription PCR is a nucleic acid amplification method that converts viral RNA to cDNA and amplifies it quantitatively; it is described as the gold standard laboratory test for confirming suspected acute respiratory infections, including COVID-19. | A real-time PCR amplification method that quantitatively measures avian influenza viral RNA and enables molecular subtyping (e.g., H5 vs H7), serving as the benchmark laboratory diagnostic for AIV detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
      <data key="d6">QUANTITATIVE PCR (QPCR)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SIGNAL DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">SIGNAL DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The measurement phase of nucleic acid-based assays in which the presence of amplified viral nucleic acids is converted into a detectable readout signal on integrated diagnostic platforms.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SPUTUM">
      <data key="d0">SPUTUM</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A type of respiratory clinical specimen collected during COVID-19 sample collection from which SARS-CoV-2 can be isolated prior to RNA extraction and nucleic acid-based testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NASAL SWABS/WASHES">
      <data key="d0">NASAL SWABS/WASHES</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Respiratory specimen types collected from the nasal cavity that can contain SARS-CoV-2, serving as input material for RNA extraction and subsequent nucleic acid-based diagnostic testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THROAT SWABS/WASHES">
      <data key="d0">THROAT SWABS/WASHES</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Respiratory specimen types collected from the throat that can harbor SARS-CoV-2, used as clinical specimens for RNA extraction and downstream nucleic acid testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SPIKE PROTEIN (S)">
      <data key="d0">SPIKE PROTEIN (S)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">The spike (S) protein is a structural protein of SARS-CoV-2 that mediates binding to host cell receptors and facilitates viral entry; it is part of the viral pathogen’s structure relevant to diagnostic targeting.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MEMBRANE PROTEIN (M)">
      <data key="d0">MEMBRANE PROTEIN (M)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">The membrane (M) protein is a structural protein of SARS-CoV-2 required for general coronavirus functions and virion assembly, contributing to the structure of the airborne pathogen.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.4</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ENVELOPE PROTEIN (E)">
      <data key="d0">ENVELOPE PROTEIN (E)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">The envelope (E) protein is a structural protein of SARS-CoV-2 involved in coronavirus assembly and function, forming part of the viral particle targeted in diagnostic assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.4</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NUCLEOCAPSID PROTEIN (N)">
      <data key="d0">NUCLEOCAPSID PROTEIN (N)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">The nucleocapsid (N) protein is a structural protein of SARS-CoV-2 that associates with the viral RNA genome and is essential for general coronavirus functions, often serving as a target region in nucleic acid-based diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="VIRUS LYSIS">
      <data key="d0">VIRUS LYSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Initial sample preparation step that disrupts viral particles to release nucleic acids prior to purification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_6,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INHIBITION OF RIBONUCLEASE ENZYMES">
      <data key="d0">INHIBITION OF RIBONUCLEASE ENZYMES</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation step that suppresses RNase activity to prevent degradation of viral RNA during extraction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_6</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NUCLEIC ACID BINDING, WASHING, AND ELUTION">
      <data key="d0">NUCLEIC ACID BINDING, WASHING, AND ELUTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Multi-step solid-phase purification process where nucleic acids bind to a support, are washed to remove contaminants, and then eluted in purified form.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_6</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PHENOL-CHLOROFORM EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">PHENOL-CHLOROFORM EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Low-cost, liquid–liquid nucleic acid extraction method involving organic solvents, but with delicate handling and hazardous waste that can reduce PCR assay sensitivity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_6</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SILICA COLUMN-BASED SOLID-PHASE EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">SILICA COLUMN-BASED SOLID-PHASE EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Solid-phase nucleic acid extraction method using silica columns, typically requiring high centrifugal force and multiple liquid-handling and centrifugation steps.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_6</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ALUMINUM OXIDE MEMBRANE-BASED SOLID-PHASE EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">ALUMINUM OXIDE MEMBRANE-BASED SOLID-PHASE EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Solid-phase nucleic acid extraction platform using aluminum oxide membranes, relying on centrifugation and multiple washing/elution steps.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_6</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FUNCTIONALIZED SILICA PARAMAGNETIC MICROBEAD EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">FUNCTIONALIZED SILICA PARAMAGNETIC MICROBEAD EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Magnetic bead-based nucleic acid extraction method using functionalized silica paramagnetic microbeads to bind and isolate nucleic acids under magnetic control, reducing the need for column separation and repeated centrifugation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_6</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MAGNETIC MICROBEAD NA EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">MAGNETIC MICROBEAD NA EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A nucleic acid extraction method using magnetic microbeads to bind and isolate nucleic acids under magnetic control, eliminating column separation and repeated centrifugation but still requiring incubation and washing steps. | A nucleic acid extraction step that uses functionalized magnetic beads to capture, wash, and release DNA/RNA from samples, enabling automated or semi-automated preparation before molecular assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
      <data key="d6">MAGNETIC BEAD NA EXTRACTION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COLUMN-AFFINITY, SOLID-PHASE-BASED NA EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">COLUMN-AFFINITY, SOLID-PHASE-BASED NA EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A solid-phase nucleic acid extraction method using column affinity that involves multiple sample manipulation steps and relies heavily on laboratory equipment, making it less suitable for point-of-care testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_7,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PAPER-BASED NA EXTRACTION BY FILTRATION-BASED ISOLATION">
      <data key="d0">PAPER-BASED NA EXTRACTION BY FILTRATION-BASED ISOLATION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Filtration-based nucleic acid extraction performed on paper or membrane substrates, enabling isolation without complex device fabrication or laboratory equipment for centrifugation, separation, and elution.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_7,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CELLULOSE PAPER DISCS (FUSION 5 FILTERS)">
      <data key="d0">CELLULOSE PAPER DISCS (FUSION 5 FILTERS)</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Cellulose-based paper discs, such as Fusion 5 filters, used as a solid support for filtration-based nucleic acid isolation and subsequent on-disc amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="WHATMAN FLINDERS TECHNOLOGY ASSOCIATES (FTA) CARDS">
      <data key="d0">WHATMAN FLINDERS TECHNOLOGY ASSOCIATES (FTA) CARDS</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Commercial paper cards designed to capture and preserve nucleic acids, used as a membrane-based substrate for simplified nucleic acid extraction and direct on-card amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEMS INTEGRATING SOLID-PHASE NA EXTRACTION, AMPLIFICATION, AND DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEMS INTEGRATING SOLID-PHASE NA EXTRACTION, AMPLIFICATION, AND DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Microfluidic platforms that combine solid-phase nucleic acid extraction, amplification, and detection within a single reaction chamber to simplify operation and enable sensitive molecular diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="POC LIONX SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">POC LIONX SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Point-of-care Lab-in/on-an-X (LionX) diagnostic systems that aim to integrate nucleic acid extraction, amplification, and detection, often leveraging paper- or microfluidic-based methods for simplified operation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MICROFLUIDIC PAPER-BASED ANALYTICAL DEVICES (MPADS)">
      <data key="d0">MICROFLUIDIC PAPER-BASED ANALYTICAL DEVICES (MPADS)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Microfluidic paper-based analytical devices that use patterned paper channels for fluid handling and analysis, representing a promising platform for integrated nucleic acid extraction and detection at the point of care. | Paper-based microfluidic analytical devices (µPADs) cited as user-friendly platforms suitable for integration with more complex sampling and processing workflows for diagnostic biosensing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
      <data key="d6">MICROFLUIDIC PAPER-BASED ANALYTICAL DEVICES (ΜPADS)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DIRECT ON-DISC NA AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">DIRECT ON-DISC NA AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">An approach where nucleic acids extracted on a paper or membrane disc are directly amplified on the same substrate without elution into a separate reaction vessel.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.65</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RT-PCR AMPLIFICATION METHOD">
      <data key="d0">RT-PCR AMPLIFICATION METHOD</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction method that converts viral RNA into cDNA followed by thermal cycling amplification, enabling sensitive detection of viral nucleic acids. | A reverse transcription loop-mediated isothermal amplification method that converts viral RNA to cDNA and amplifies it at a constant temperature, providing rapid nucleic acid detection suitable for simplified instrumentation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
      <data key="d6">RT-LAMP AMPLIFICATION METHOD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NASBA AMPLIFICATION METHOD">
      <data key="d0">NASBA AMPLIFICATION METHOD</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Nucleic acid sequence-based amplification, an isothermal amplification method that targets RNA and generates amplified nucleic acid products without thermal cycling, serving as an alternative to PCR-based approaches.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QRT-PCR">
      <data key="d0">QRT-PCR</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Quantitative reverse transcription PCR, a real-time amplification method that converts viral RNA into cDNA and monitors amplification during thermal cycling, providing highly sensitive and specific quantification of viral RNA; widely used as a clinical gold standard. | Abbreviated name for quantitative reverse transcription PCR, the reference nucleic acid amplification method used to confirm positive viral cases and assess viral load in this study.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_9,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
      <data key="d6">QRT-PCR</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MIDDLE EAST RESPIRATORY SYNDROME (MERS)-COV">
      <data key="d0">MIDDLE EAST RESPIRATORY SYNDROME (MERS)-COV</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">The coronavirus causing Middle East respiratory syndrome (MERS), an airborne respiratory pathogen whose viral RNA is detectable by qRT-PCR-based molecular assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ZIKA VIRUSES">
      <data key="d0">ZIKA VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Zika viruses, whose RNA genomes can be detected by qRT-PCR; mentioned as viral RNA targets for molecular amplification, although they are primarily vector-borne rather than airborne.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LIMIT OF DETECTION (LOD) DOWN TO A SINGLE PATHOGEN">
      <data key="d0">LIMIT OF DETECTION (LOD) DOWN TO A SINGLE PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">An analytical sensitivity performance level where nucleic acid-based testing can detect as little as a single pathogen, indicating extremely low limits of detection for viral DNA or RNA.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NA-BASED TESTING OF VIRAL INFECTION">
      <data key="d0">NA-BASED TESTING OF VIRAL INFECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A validation context describing nucleic acid-based tests for viral infection that directly detect pathogenic DNA or RNA at very low quantities, demonstrating superior analytical sensitivity compared with serological testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QRT-PCR TESTING">
      <data key="d0">QRT-PCR TESTING</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Clinical and laboratory testing of qRT-PCR assays that has demonstrated high sensitivity and specificity for detecting a variety of viral RNAs, establishing qRT-PCR as the gold standard for early diagnosis of pathogenic infections including COVID-19.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PLATFORM SUITABLE FOR POC DIAGNOSTICS">
      <data key="d0">PLATFORM SUITABLE FOR POC DIAGNOSTICS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A point-of-care diagnostic platform concept that can integrate the main processing steps of infectious disease diagnosis, including nucleic acid extraction and amplification, into a compact workflow.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EARLY ACUTE PHASE OF SARS-COV-2 INFECTION">
      <data key="d0">EARLY ACUTE PHASE OF SARS-COV-2 INFECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagnostic testing context corresponding to the early acute phase of SARS-CoV-2 infection, when viral replication is high but antibodies are not yet detectable, making nucleic acid amplification-based assays particularly important.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RT-LAMP">
      <data key="d0">RT-LAMP</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Reverse transcription loop-mediated isothermal amplification (RT-LAMP) is an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method that directly amplifies reversely transcribed cDNA at a fixed temperature (~65 °C) in a one-step reaction, achieving rapid (≤1 h) and highly efficient RNA/DNA amplification suitable for pathogen detection, including respiratory viruses such as SARS-CoV-2. | Reverse transcription loop-mediated isothermal amplification, an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method used in the Thi et al. assay to amplify SARS-CoV-2 RNA prior to detection. | Reverse transcription loop-mediated isothermal amplification, an isothermal method that amplifies viral RNA targets as cDNA prior to or in conjunction with CRISPR-Cas12a detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_9,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_48,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_49</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
      <data key="d6">RT-LAMP</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Recombinase polymerase amplification (RPA) is an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method that uses DNA polymerase together with recombinase enzymes to achieve rapid nucleic acid amplification at a low constant temperature (~37 °C) within about 30 minutes, providing an alternative to thermal cycling-based PCR. | Recombinase polymerase amplification (RPA) is an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method that operates at approximately 37 °C, uses recombinase and DNA polymerase enzymes, and can reach high amplification efficiency within about 30 minutes. It has been implemented on LionX systems and applied to SARS-CoV-2 detection. | Recombinase polymerase amplification, an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method whose temperature profile is exploited in TRACE to amplify targets prior to or concurrent with CRISPR-based detection. | Recombinase polymerase amplification, an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method coupled with CRISPR-Cas12a assays to rapidly amplify target sequences at low, constant temperature. | Recombinase polymerase amplification (RPA) is an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method used in combination with lateral flow strip assays for rapid detection of OXA-48-like carbapenemase genes in Enterobacterales.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_9,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">RPA,RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PATHOGENIC AVIAN INFLUENZA">
      <data key="d0">PATHOGENIC AVIAN INFLUENZA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Pathogenic avian influenza refers to highly pathogenic influenza A viruses originating in birds that can infect the respiratory tract; here it is mentioned as a target pathogen detected by RT-LAMP-based assays, reflecting its relevance as a respiratory and potentially airborne pathogen.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RESPIRATORY VIRUSES">
      <data key="d0">RESPIRATORY VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Respiratory viruses, including but not limited to SARS-CoV-2 and influenza viruses, are pathogens that infect the respiratory tract and can be transmitted via aerosols or droplets; in this text they are targets for RT-LAMP-based detection assays. | A broad class of viruses that infect the respiratory tract and are commonly transmitted via aerosols or droplets in air. In this context, they are the diagnostic targets of the multiplexed CRISPR-based microfluidic platform and correspond to airborne pathogens when present in air or respiratory samples. | A general group of respiratory viruses that are rapidly and quantitatively detected using surface-enhanced Raman spectroscopy combined with machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_9,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
      <data key="d6">RESPIRATORY VIRUSES</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LIONX PLATFORMS">
      <data key="d0">LIONX PLATFORMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">LionX platforms are integrated diagnostic platforms into which RT-LAMP-based assays have been incorporated, providing a system for on-platform isothermal nucleic acid amplification and detection of pathogens such as respiratory viruses and avian influenza.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HELICASE-DEPENDENT AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">HELICASE-DEPENDENT AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Helicase-dependent amplification (HDA) is an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method that uses a helicase enzyme to unwind target DNA at a constant temperature (around 37 °C), eliminating the heat-induced denaturation step required in PCR for viral nucleic acid amplification and detection. | Helicase dependent amplification (HDA) is an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method that uses helicase to separate DNA strands, allowing amplification at constant temperature and integration into disposable diagnostic devices.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
      <data key="d6">HELICASE DEPENDENT AMPLIFICATION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXPONENTIAL AMPLIFICATION REACTION">
      <data key="d0">EXPONENTIAL AMPLIFICATION REACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">The exponential amplification reaction (EXPAR) is an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method that does not require conventional primers and instead performs nucleic acid amplification using a single, specifically designed target template sequence. | An exponential nucleic acid amplification step applied to RNA fragments generated by Argonaute cleavage, with double-stranded DNA detected via SYBR I dye.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">EXPONENTIAL AMPLIFICATION REACTION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NA SEQUENCE-BASED AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">NA SEQUENCE-BASED AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Nucleic acid sequence-based amplification (NASBA) is an isothermal amplification method designed to amplify single-stranded nucleic acids at a relatively low temperature (around 41 °C), enabling efficient molecular viral detection and generating up to 10^9 genomic amplicons in 1.5–2 hours. | Nucleic acid sequence-based amplification (NASBA) is an isothermal amplification technique primarily targeting RNA, enabling sensitive detection of viral and other pathogen genomes without thermal cycling.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
      <data key="d6">NUCLEIC ACID SEQUENCE-BASED AMPLIFICATION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QUANTITATIVE NASBA">
      <data key="d0">QUANTITATIVE NASBA</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Quantitative NASBA (QT-NASBA) is a highly sensitive quantitative variant of NASBA that provides amplification performance comparable to quantitative PCR (qPCR), enabling precise measurement of nucleic acid targets under isothermal conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QPCR">
      <data key="d0">QPCR</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Quantitative PCR (qPCR) is a standard nucleic acid amplification and detection platform used as the clinical reference method to evaluate the diagnostic performance of TRACE. | Real-time quantitative PCR platform used under laboratory conditions to quantify viral RNA, differentiate influenza A genotypes (e.g., H5 vs H7), and detect pathogenicity-associated motifs such as polybasic insertions at the HA0 cleavage site.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.98</data>
      <data key="d4">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_0,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_6,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_8,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_17,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_18,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_24,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_36</data>
      <data key="d5">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
      <data key="d6">QPCR</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LIONX SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">LIONX SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">LionX systems are integrated lab-on-chip–style biosensor platforms that can implement isothermal nucleic acid amplification methods and integrate nucleic acid extraction, amplification, and signal quantification for detection of infectious diseases in point-of-care (POC) settings.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_10,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OPTICAL DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">OPTICAL DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of nucleic acid detection platforms that quantify amplification products via optical readouts such as fluorescence, colorimetric changes, or Raman signals.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FLUORESCENT DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">FLUORESCENT DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An optical nucleic acid detection platform that uses fluorescent probes and measures fluorescence intensity to quantify amplified nucleic acids.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ELECTROCHEMICAL SENSING">
      <data key="d0">ELECTROCHEMICAL SENSING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A nucleic acid detection platform that measures electrical current, potential, or impedance changes at electrodes to infer the presence and amount of amplified nucleic acids.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ELECTRONIC SENSING">
      <data key="d0">ELECTRONIC SENSING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A nucleic acid detection platform that uses solid-state electronic components (such as field-effect transistors) to transduce nucleic acid binding or amplification events into electronic signals.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NANOPORE-BASED SEQUENCING">
      <data key="d0">NANOPORE-BASED SEQUENCING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A nucleic acid detection and sequencing platform in which single nucleic acid molecules pass through nanopores, producing characteristic ionic current signals that reveal sequence and presence of viral genomes. | Nanopore-based next-generation sequencing platform used for whole-genome sequencing and detection of various viruses.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.96</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_11,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_19,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
      <data key="d6">NANOPORE-BASED GENE SEQUENCING</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LATERAL FLOW ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">LATERAL FLOW ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A strip-based nucleic acid detection platform that typically uses colorimetric optical readouts, where amplification products are captured and visualized as lines or bands on a lateral flow strip. | A lateral-flow implementation of the TRACE platform that operates without nucleic acid isolation, refrigeration, or expensive equipment, designed to meet REASSURED criteria and provide performance comparable to qPCR on diverse clinical samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.92</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
      <data key="d6">LATERAL FLOW TRACE ASSAY</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LATERAL FLOW TEST">
      <data key="d0">LATERAL FLOW TEST</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lateral-flow-based diagnostic test format that converts nucleic acid detection results into visually observable bands or color changes on a test strip.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SURFACE-ENHANCED RAMAN SCATTERING">
      <data key="d0">SURFACE-ENHANCED RAMAN SCATTERING</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">An optical reporter signal modality in which Raman scattering from analytes is greatly enhanced by nanostructured surfaces, enabling sensitive spectral detection of nucleic acid targets.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FIELD-EFFECT TRANSISTOR">
      <data key="d0">FIELD-EFFECT TRANSISTOR</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An electronic biosensor platform in which changes in surface charge or binding events at the gate region modulate channel current, allowing electronic readout of nucleic acid detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GOLD NANOPARTICLE">
      <data key="d0">GOLD NANOPARTICLE</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A plasmonic nanomaterial used as an optical label or enhancer in nucleic acid assays, especially in lateral flow and colorimetric formats, where its aggregation state produces visible color changes.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAMP">
      <data key="d0">LAMP</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Loop-mediated isothermal amplification, a mature nucleic acid amplification method that can be combined with fluorescent probes for virus detection. | Loop-mediated isothermal amplification used to generate cDNA from SARS-CoV-2 and influenza virus RNA in an Argonaute-integrated assay.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_12,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_21,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_32,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">LAMP</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NASBA">
      <data key="d0">NASBA</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Nucleic acid sequence-based amplification, an isothermal amplification method that can be coupled with specific fluorescent target probes for viral nucleic acid detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.74</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_12,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="1 COPY RNA PER REACTION">
      <data key="d0">1 COPY RNA PER REACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">Reported analytical limit of detection for SARS-CoV using RT-PCR with fluorescent detection, corresponding to a single RNA copy per reaction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="100 COPIES/ML">
      <data key="d0">100 COPIES/ML</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">Reported analytical limit of detection for SARS-CoV-2 (COVID-19) using commercial RT-PCR systems, corresponding to 100 RNA copies per milliliter of sample.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_12,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_68</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-BASED TOOLS">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-BASED TOOLS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">CRISPR-based nucleic acid detection platforms that use CRISPR effector enzymes to cleave DNA fragments modified with fluorescent probe–quencher pairs, enabling highly specific fluorescent detection of target RNAs such as those from SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FLUORESCENT DETECTION SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">FLUORESCENT DETECTION SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Fluorescence-based nucleic acid detection systems that use fluorescent dyes or labeled probes to quantify amplification products, serving as the optical readout module in viral diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COMMERCIAL RT-PCR SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">COMMERCIAL RT-PCR SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Unspecified commercial diagnostic platforms based on RT-PCR that achieve detection of SARS-CoV-2 (COVID-19) down to 100 copies/mL using fluorescent readout.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SYNTHETIC BIOLOGY-BASED TECHNIQUES INTEGRATED WITH OPTICAL DETECTION SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">SYNTHETIC BIOLOGY-BASED TECHNIQUES INTEGRATED WITH OPTICAL DETECTION SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Synthetic biology-derived diagnostic platforms, including CRISPR-based methods, that are integrated with optical (fluorescent) detection modules to overcome limitations of conventional PCR-based assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FLUORESCENCE-BASED COVID-19 DIAGNOSTIC PROTOCOLS">
      <data key="d0">FLUORESCENCE-BASED COVID-19 DIAGNOSTIC PROTOCOLS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Reported diagnostic workflows specifically designed for COVID-19 that use fluorescence-based readouts, including RT-PCR and CRISPR-based assays, for rapid SARS-CoV-2 detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FLUORESCENT DETECTION SIGNAL">
      <data key="d0">FLUORESCENT DETECTION SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">General fluorescence readout used to quantify nucleic acid amplification products (e.g., in RT-PCR, LAMP, NASBA) or CRISPR-mediated cleavage events for viral detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SMARTPHONE FLUORESCENCE READER">
      <data key="d0">SMARTPHONE FLUORESCENCE READER</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A portable fluorescence-based biosensor platform that uses a smartphone as the detection and readout device for nucleic acid assays, achieving a limit of detection of 2.8 × 10^3 DNA copies in the described setup.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FLUORESCENCE READOUT">
      <data key="d0">FLUORESCENCE READOUT</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">An optical reporter signal based on fluorescence emission used to quantify nucleic acid detection sensitivity in portable platforms such as smartphone-based readers. | Time-resolved fluorescence signal recorded every minute to monitor Cas12-mediated reporter cleavage in CRISPR/Cas12a, CRISPR/Cas12b, and TRACE assays. | A fluorescent signal generated during isothermal amplification reactions, allowing sensitive detection and potential quantification of amplified influenza viral RNA. | Time-dependent fluorescence intensity used as the primary reporter signal to monitor ANCA reaction progress and amplification efficiency.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">FLUORESCENCE READOUT</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LIMIT OF 2.8 × 10^3 DNA COPIES">
      <data key="d0">LIMIT OF 2.8 × 10^3 DNA COPIES</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">The minimum detectable amount of target DNA, reported as 2.8 × 10^3 DNA copies, obtained using a smartphone fluorescence reader.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LATERAL FLOW TEST STRIP">
      <data key="d0">LATERAL FLOW TEST STRIP</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lateral flow test (LFT) strip used as a simple, autonomous biosensor platform for rapid nucleic acid detection via colorimetric readout on test and control lines. | A lateral flow strip-based biosensor platform used for rapid detection of nucleic acid targets, here applied to OXA-48-like carbapenemase genes in Enterobacterales.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">LATERAL FLOW STRIP</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COLORIMETRIC READOUT ON LFT STRIP">
      <data key="d0">COLORIMETRIC READOUT ON LFT STRIP</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A colorimetric reporter signal manifested as changes in color intensity on the test line of a lateral flow strip, enabling rapid visual or instrument-based readout of nucleic acid detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AUNP-BASED COLORIMETRIC SIGNAL IN SOLUTION">
      <data key="d0">AUNP-BASED COLORIMETRIC SIGNAL IN SOLUTION</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A solution-phase colorimetric reporter signal generated by gold nanoparticle (AuNP)–DNA conjugates that change color from red to blue upon aggregation induced by target DNA hybridization.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HANDHELD UV FLASHLIGHT PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">HANDHELD UV FLASHLIGHT PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A simple optical biosensor platform using handheld UV flashlights to excite fluorescence for sample-in-answer-out diagnostic applications in resource-limited settings.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CELLPHONE CAMERA PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">CELLPHONE CAMERA PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A biosensor platform that uses a cellphone camera as the detector for optical signals (fluorescent or colorimetric) in portable diagnostic assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SAMPLE-IN-ANSWER-OUT (SIAO) DIAGNOSTIC PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">SAMPLE-IN-ANSWER-OUT (SIAO) DIAGNOSTIC PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An integrated diagnostic platform concept where samples are processed and results are produced with minimal user intervention, often using portable optical detection modules such as smartphones, UV flashlights, or cameras.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ENTEROVIRUS 71">
      <data key="d0">ENTEROVIRUS 71</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Enterovirus 71 is a human viral pathogen associated with hand, foot, and mouth disease and neurological complications; here it is the target analyte detected by a portable SPR biosensor using optical signal enhancement.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_14,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ZIKA VIRAL RNA">
      <data key="d0">ZIKA VIRAL RNA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Zika viral RNA is the genomic RNA of Zika virus; in this context it is the nucleic acid target whose dye-labeled probe signal is enhanced via SERS hotspots formed between optical antennas and metallic nanoparticles.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INFLUENZA VIRUSES">
      <data key="d0">INFLUENZA VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Influenza viruses are respiratory pathogens transmitted via aerosols and droplets; here they are the targets in a SERS-based platform for rapid identification of virulence determinants with reported 100% sensitivity and selectivity. | A group of influenza A viruses, respiratory pathogens that can be transmitted via aerosols and are targets for rapid detection and subtyping. | A group of airborne respiratory viruses that can be present in aerosol or dust samples and whose infection-induced biochemical signatures can be distinguished by the label-free SERS platform based on intrinsic Raman spectral features. | A group of respiratory viruses transmissible via aerosols and droplets; in the Singh et al. study they serve as the viral targets captured by the reduced graphene oxide-based electrochemical microfluidic immunosensor. | A group of airborne influenza viruses whose RNA is amplified by LAMP and detected using Argonaute-integrated isothermal amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.92</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_14,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">INFLUENZA A VIRUSES,INFLUENZA VIRUSES</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PORTABLE SPR BIOSENSOR">
      <data key="d0">PORTABLE SPR BIOSENSOR</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A portable surface plasmon resonance (SPR) biosensor that uses metallic nanomaterials for optical signal enhancement and is designed to detect Enterovirus 71 with high analytical sensitivity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.94</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SERS-BASED RAPID IDENTIFICATION PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">SERS-BASED RAPID IDENTIFICATION PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A surface-enhanced Raman scattering (SERS)-based biosensor platform used for rapid identification of virulence determinants in influenza viruses, achieving 100% sensitivity and 100% selectivity and enabling amplification-free detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QUANTUM DOT BARCODE-BASED DIAGNOSTIC SENSORS">
      <data key="d0">QUANTUM DOT BARCODE-BASED DIAGNOSTIC SENSORS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Optical diagnostic biosensor platforms that use quantum dot barcodes for high-throughput detection of DNA markers, with smartphone-based imaging and colorimetric signal quantification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LOD OF 4.8 PG/ML">
      <data key="d0">LOD OF 4.8 PG/ML</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">A reported limit of detection of 4.8 pg/mL achieved by the portable SPR biosensor for Enterovirus 71, indicating high sensitivity of the optical biosensing platform.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COLORIMETRIC SIGNAL QUANTIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">COLORIMETRIC SIGNAL QUANTIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A colorimetric reporter signal from quantum dot barcode sensors that is captured by smartphone imaging and quantified to infer the presence and amount of DNA markers.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FLUORESCENCE SIGNAL OF A SINGLE DYE PROBE">
      <data key="d0">FLUORESCENCE SIGNAL OF A SINGLE DYE PROBE</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A fluorescence reporter signal generated by a single dye-labeled probe bound to Zika viral RNA, whose intensity is enhanced by SERS hotspots between optical antennas and metallic nanoparticles.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SERS-ENHANCED VIRULENCE DETERMINANT SIGNAL">
      <data key="d0">SERS-ENHANCED VIRULENCE DETERMINANT SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The SERS-enhanced optical signal corresponding to virulence determinants in influenza viruses, enabling rapid and highly sensitive identification with 100% sensitivity and selectivity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OPTICAL DETECTION METHODS FOR NA-BASED VIRUS TESTING">
      <data key="d0">OPTICAL DETECTION METHODS FOR NA-BASED VIRUS TESTING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Optical signal–based diagnostic platforms used for nucleic acid (NA) virus testing, offering high throughput, good sensitivity and specificity, and cost efficiency, but facing challenges for amplification-free detection and real-time sequencing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OPTICAL SIGNAL ENHANCEMENT FOR AMPLIFICATION-FREE DNA ANALYSIS">
      <data key="d0">OPTICAL SIGNAL ENHANCEMENT FOR AMPLIFICATION-FREE DNA ANALYSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Optical enhancement approaches (e.g., signal amplification at the sensor interface) aimed at enabling amplification-free DNA analysis, though typically requiring complex and time-consuming sample substrate preparation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GEL ELECTROPHORESIS FOR VISUALIZATION OF AMPLIFIED DNA">
      <data key="d0">GEL ELECTROPHORESIS FOR VISUALIZATION OF AMPLIFIED DNA</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Traditional gel electrophoresis setup used to visualize amplified DNA molecules in lab sample analysis, valued for simplicity and reliability but limited by bulky equipment and time-consuming procedures, making it unsuitable for routine clinical NA testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CAPILLARY ELECTROPHORESIS-BASED MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">CAPILLARY ELECTROPHORESIS-BASED MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Microfluidic platforms integrating and parallelizing nucleic acid analyses using capillary electrophoresis, enabling efficient on-chip RNA/DNA testing but requiring complex precise flow control and optical detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ELECTROCHEMICAL SENSING FOR NA TESTING">
      <data key="d0">ELECTROCHEMICAL SENSING FOR NA TESTING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Electrochemical signal–based detection platforms for nucleic acid testing, characterized by high sensitivity and specificity, simple device structures, and strong compatibility with micro- and nanoengineering technologies.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MOLECULAR AMPLIFICATION OF NUCLEIC ACIDS">
      <data key="d0">MOLECULAR AMPLIFICATION OF NUCLEIC ACIDS</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">General nucleic acid amplification processes (e.g., PCR or related methods) used to increase the amount of DNA/RNA prior to detection, which optical signal enhancement aims to avoid in amplification-free assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SAMPLE SUBSTRATE PREPARATION FOR OPTICAL ENHANCEMENT">
      <data key="d0">SAMPLE SUBSTRATE PREPARATION FOR OPTICAL ENHANCEMENT</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Complex and time-consuming preparation of substrates or surfaces required by many optical signal enhancement methods before nucleic acid samples can be analyzed.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ELECTROCHEMICAL NUCLEIC ACID BIOSENSOR USING MN2O3 NANOFIBER SENSING ELECTRODES">
      <data key="d0">ELECTROCHEMICAL NUCLEIC ACID BIOSENSOR USING MN2O3 NANOFIBER SENSING ELECTRODES</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Electrochemical DNA biosensor that employs electrospun semi-conductive Mn2O3 nanofibers as sensing electrodes, enabling amplification-free detection of Dengue DNA hybridization with high sensitivity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ELECTROCHEMICAL MICRORNA SERUM BIOSENSOR">
      <data key="d0">ELECTROCHEMICAL MICRORNA SERUM BIOSENSOR</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Electrochemical sensor platform for direct, amplification-free detection of microRNAs in serum samples with high sensitivity and specificity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LABEL-FREE ELECTROCHEMICAL ZIKA CDNA BIOSENSOR WITH DISPOSABLE THREE-CONTACT ELECTRODES">
      <data key="d0">LABEL-FREE ELECTROCHEMICAL ZIKA CDNA BIOSENSOR WITH DISPOSABLE THREE-CONTACT ELECTRODES</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Label-free electrochemical nucleic acid sensor using disposable three-contact electrode sensors for detection of Zika viral cDNA amplicons, achieving a limit of detection of 25 nM.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ELECTROCHEMICAL HEPATITIS A VIRUS CDNA BIOSENSOR ON CAPTURE DNA-MODIFIED GOLD ELECTRODE">
