      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HIV">
      <data key="d0">HIV</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Human immunodeficiency virus, cited as a viral target detectable by nanopore-based sequencing platforms. | A blood-borne retrovirus (HIV) cited as a target whose optical spectroscopic detection can be enhanced using nanomaterials targeted to specific viral antibodies.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_18,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_19,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_51</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
      <data key="d6">HUMAN IMMUNODEFICIENCY VIRUS</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HEPATITIS B VIRUS">
      <data key="d0">HEPATITIS B VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Hepatitis B virus, mentioned as a viral pathogen detectable using nanopore-based sequencing technologies. | Hepatitis A virus, a pathogenic virus detected by the rapid, label-free electrochemical DNA biosensor. | A human hepatotropic virus (HBV) mentioned as being detected from human blood serum using Raman spectroscopy, serving as an example of optical detection of blood-borne viruses. | A human pathogen (HCV) cited as detected from blood serum via Raman spectroscopy, further exemplifying virus identification by optical spectroscopic methods.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.92</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_18,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_19,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_58</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
      <data key="d6">HEPATITIS A VIRUS,HEPATITIS B VIRUS,HEPATITIS C VIRUS</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR/CAS9">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR/CAS9</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">CRISPR/Cas9 nuclease system immobilized on a graphene-based FET sensor for sequence-specific detection of unamplified target DNA. | CRISPR-Cas9 is the CRISPR effector nuclease used as the sequence-specific recognition element in the graphene field-effect transistor biosensor. | A CRISPR-associated nuclease system with collateral cleavage activity, widely used in nucleic acid diagnostics for signal amplification and detection. | A catalytically dead Cas9 variant used in CRISPR-based colorimetric assays for detecting SARS-CoV-2 and drug-resistant pH1N1. | The canonical CRISPR effector enzyme Cas9, referenced by Yan et al. (2019) as the well-known sibling of Cas12 and Cas13 and used as a basis of comparison.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">CRISPR-CAS9,CRISPR/CAS12,CRISPR/DCAS9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AMPLIFICATION-FREE DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">AMPLIFICATION-FREE DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Detection approach that does not use nucleic acid amplification (e.g., PCR), relying instead on the intrinsic sensitivity of FET-based platforms.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LOD 1.7 FM (GRAPHENE FET CRISPR/CAS9 ASSAY)">
      <data key="d0">LOD 1.7 FM (GRAPHENE FET CRISPR/CAS9 ASSAY)</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">Limit of detection of 1.7 femtomolar reported for the graphene-based FET sensor functionalized with CRISPR/Cas9 detecting unamplified target DNA.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
