      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Operational assay run time of 15 minutes for the graphene-based FET CRISPR/Cas9 DNA detection platform.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OXFORD NANOPORE TECHNOLOGIES SEQUENCING PLATFORMS">
      <data key="d0">OXFORD NANOPORE TECHNOLOGIES SEQUENCING PLATFORMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Commercial nanopore-based NGS instruments from Oxford Nanopore Technologies used for rapid whole-genome sequencing of viral pathogens, including SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.94</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COVID-19 DNA FRAGMENTS (AMPLIFIED)">
      <data key="d0">COVID-19 DNA FRAGMENTS (AMPLIFIED)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Amplified DNA fragments corresponding to SARS-CoV-2 genomic regions, sequenced on nanopore platforms within a few minutes in the Liu et al. study.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COVID-19 RNA SEQUENCING WORKFLOW">
      <data key="d0">COVID-19 RNA SEQUENCING WORKFLOW</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">The overall nanopore-based sequencing run for SARS-CoV-2 RNA, including sample preparation, system initialization, and sequencing, with total preparation and initialization time of about 7 hours.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DNA/RNA SAMPLE PREPARATION FOR COVID-19 SEQUENCING">
      <data key="d0">DNA/RNA SAMPLE PREPARATION FOR COVID-19 SEQUENCING</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Pre-analytical processing of SARS-CoV-2 DNA or RNA, including extraction and library preparation, required before nanopore sequencing and contributing significantly to total assay time (~7 hours).</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SEQUENCING SYSTEM INITIALIZATION FOR COVID-19 ASSAYS">
      <data key="d0">SEQUENCING SYSTEM INITIALIZATION FOR COVID-19 ASSAYS</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Setup and initialization procedures for the nanopore sequencing system prior to running COVID-19 RNA sequencing assays, contributing to the ~7-hour pre-run time.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SARS-COV-2 GENBANK REFERENCE DATABASE">
      <data key="d0">SARS-COV-2 GENBANK REFERENCE DATABASE</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">The established GenBank repository of SARS-CoV-2 genomic sequences used as a reference to identify and distinguish various viral targets in nanopore sequencing data.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REAL-TIME SINGLE-BASE-RESOLUTION MUTATION IDENTIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">REAL-TIME SINGLE-BASE-RESOLUTION MUTATION IDENTIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">The capability of nanopore-based sequencing to detect viral mutations at single-base resolution in real time, enabling immediate tracking of viral evolution during a pandemic.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LIONX DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">LIONX DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Integrated lab-in/on-an-X diagnostic platforms that automate virus detection workflows, including sample preparation, nucleic acid amplification, and signal detection, and are designed for both laboratory-based and point-of-care (POC) virus diagnostics such as COVID-19 testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ROCHE COBAS LIAT PCR SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">ROCHE COBAS LIAT PCR SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A commercial lab-in-a-tube diagnostic system that automates PCR-based clinical diagnosis of viral infections, including influenza virus and SARS-CoV-2, integrating nucleic acid extraction, amplification, and detection in a compact cartridge-like format.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_21,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NANOPORE-BASED BIOSENSING TECHNOLOGIES">
      <data key="d0">NANOPORE-BASED BIOSENSING TECHNOLOGIES</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Emerging biosensing platforms that use nanopore-based sequencing for nucleic acid detection, currently more suited for viral genome identification during pandemics but under development for potential use in viral infection diagnosis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NANOPORE-BASED SEQUENCING TECHNOLOGY">
      <data key="d0">NANOPORE-BASED SEQUENCING TECHNOLOGY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A nanopore-based sequencing platform for nucleic acid detection, presently applied mainly to virus genome identification amid pandemics and considered a candidate module for future integration into LionX diagnostic systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-IN-A-TUBE SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">LAB-IN-A-TUBE SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of LionX platforms that miniaturize and integrate traditional tube-based clinical virus testing procedures, including nucleic acid extraction, amplification, and detection, into a single tube or cartridge format.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SAMPLE PREPARATION">
      <data key="d0">SAMPLE PREPARATION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A generic initial processing step in LionX systems that precedes nucleic acid amplification and signal detection, encompassing operations such as nucleic acid extraction and other preparatory manipulations of clinical samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NA AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">NA AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A general nucleic acid amplification step integrated into LionX systems, representing methods such as PCR or isothermal amplification used to increase viral nucleic acid copies before detection. | Loop-mediated isothermal amplification used in the eight-channel microfluidic array device and in the silicon microfluidic chip within the smartphone-based multiplexing system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
      <data key="d6">LAMP AMPLIFICATION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The final detection/readout step in traditional and lab-in-a-tube virus testing workflows, where the amplified nucleic acid is measured to infer the presence of viral infection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.4</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TWO-STAGE RPA–LAMP CLOSED-TUBE DIAGNOSTIC ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">TWO-STAGE RPA–LAMP CLOSED-TUBE DIAGNOSTIC ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lab-in-a-tube diagnostic platform that integrates a two-stage isothermal amplification process—RPA in the tube cap followed by LAMP in the tube body after mixing—within a single closed tube, enabling sensitive detection of COVID-19 in non-laboratory settings.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_21</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MALARIA">
      <data key="d0">MALARIA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Malaria, caused by Plasmodium parasites, is the disease diagnosed by a paper-based microfluidic platform in the LionX system suite.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DNA EXTRACTION CARD">
      <data key="d0">DNA EXTRACTION CARD</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A DNA extraction card preloaded in a microcapillary is used to perform nucleic acid extraction from crude blood samples as part of an integrated microcapillary-based LAMP system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NA PRECONTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">NA PRECONTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Nucleic acid (NA) precontraction is a preparatory step integrated with amplification and detection in a microcapillary, concentrating nucleic acids prior to isothermal amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SIGNAL READOUT">
      <data key="d0">SIGNAL READOUT</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Signal readout in the pipette tip-based NA test refers to the measurable output generated after LAMP amplification to indicate the presence of target Ebola virus nucleic acids.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="2 COPIES OF TARGET NA FRAGMENTS">
      <data key="d0">2 COPIES OF TARGET NA FRAGMENTS</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">A limit of detection described as as low as 2 copies of target nucleic acid fragments, associated with the pipette tip-based NA test for Ebola virus detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CLOSED-TUBE ASSAY FOR COVID-19 DIAGNOSIS">
      <data key="d0">CLOSED-TUBE ASSAY FOR COVID-19 DIAGNOSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lab-in-a-tube closed-tube assay designed for COVID-19 diagnosis, enabling nucleic acid-based virus detection in a sealed reaction vessel to reduce contamination risk.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INTEGRATION OF TUBE-BASED DIAGNOSTIC WITH A SMARTPHONE">
      <data key="d0">INTEGRATION OF TUBE-BASED DIAGNOSTIC WITH A SMARTPHONE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A tube-based diagnostic platform integrated with a smartphone, likely using the phone for imaging or analysis of assay results in a portable format.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INTUBE SIMPLIFIED ASSAYS BY TABLETING REAGENTS">
      <data key="d0">INTUBE SIMPLIFIED ASSAYS BY TABLETING REAGENTS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lab-in-a-tube system where reagents are tableted within the tube, simplifying assay setup and enabling easy deployment of nucleic acid diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HIGH-THROUGHPUT SAMPLE-TO-ANSWER DETECTION OF DNA WITHIN MICROPIPETTE TIPS">
      <data key="d0">HIGH-THROUGHPUT SAMPLE-TO-ANSWER DETECTION OF DNA WITHIN MICROPIPETTE TIPS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A micropipette tip-based platform enabling high-throughput, sample-to-answer DNA detection, integrating multiple steps within the tip format.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INTEGRATION OF NA PRECONTRACTION, AMPLIFICATION, AND DETECTION IN A MICROCAPILLARY">
      <data key="d0">INTEGRATION OF NA PRECONTRACTION, AMPLIFICATION, AND DETECTION IN A MICROCAPILLARY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A microcapillary-based platform that integrates nucleic acid precontraction, amplification, and detection in a single capillary for streamlined diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MULTIPLEXED INTEGRATED MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEM FOR INFLUENZA DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">MULTIPLEXED INTEGRATED MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEM FOR INFLUENZA DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lab-on-a-chip multiplexed integrated microfluidic system designed to detect influenza, likely enabling simultaneous processing of multiple targets or samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INSTRUMENT-FREE MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORM FOR ZIKA VIRUS DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">INSTRUMENT-FREE MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORM FOR ZIKA VIRUS DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A microfluidic platform for Zika virus detection that operates without external instruments, suitable for low-resource or field settings.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PAPERBASED MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORM FOR MALARIA DIAGNOSIS">
      <data key="d0">PAPERBASED MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORM FOR MALARIA DIAGNOSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A paper-based microfluidic platform used for malaria diagnosis, leveraging capillary flow in paper for low-cost, portable testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-IN-A-BOX SYSTEM WITH THE FREEZE-DRIED AND CELL-FREE TECHNIQUES">
      <data key="d0">LAB-IN-A-BOX SYSTEM WITH THE FREEZE-DRIED AND CELL-FREE TECHNIQUES</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lab-in-a-box diagnostic system that uses freeze-dried, cell-free components to enable portable nucleic acid-based detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-IN-A-CARTRIDGE SYSTEM UTILIZING THE DROPLET MAGNETOFLUIDICS TECHNIQUE">
      <data key="d0">LAB-IN-A-CARTRIDGE SYSTEM UTILIZING THE DROPLET MAGNETOFLUIDICS TECHNIQUE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lab-in-a-cartridge system that employs droplet magnetofluidics to manipulate samples and reagents for automated nucleic acid detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-ON-A-DRONE SYSTEM THAT REALIZED PINPOINT DEPLOYMENT OF A SMARTPHONE-BASED DIAGNOSTIC PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">LAB-ON-A-DRONE SYSTEM THAT REALIZED PINPOINT DEPLOYMENT OF A SMARTPHONE-BASED DIAGNOSTIC PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lab-on-a-drone system enabling pinpoint deployment of a smartphone-based diagnostic platform, extending nucleic acid testing to remote locations.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PIPETTE TIP-BASED NA TEST">
      <data key="d0">PIPETTE TIP-BASED NA TEST</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A pipette tip-based nucleic acid test that integrates NA extraction, LAMP amplification, and signal readout in a single pipette tip, used for Ebola virus detection with very low limits of detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INTEGRATED MICROCAPILLARY-BASED LAMP WITH ALL REAGENTS AND DNA EXTRACTION CARD PRELOADED IN A CAPILLARY">
      <data key="d0">INTEGRATED MICROCAPILLARY-BASED LAMP WITH ALL REAGENTS AND DNA EXTRACTION CARD PRELOADED IN A CAPILLARY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An integrated microcapillary-based LAMP system with all reagents and a DNA extraction card preloaded in a capillary, used to test the CYP2C19 gene from crude blood samples without sophisticated instruments.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-ON-A-CHIP SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">LAB-ON-A-CHIP SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Microfluidic, lab-on-a-chip diagnostic platforms that integrate on-chip fluid manipulation and analytical testing, enabling automated, miniaturized assays with low sample and reagent consumption, high sensitivity, and short turnaround time for pathogen detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEMS FOR NA TESTING">
      <data key="d0">MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEMS FOR NA TESTING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Microfluidic platforms specifically designed for nucleic acid testing and pathogen detection, integrating sample handling and analysis on-chip as reviewed in the cited literature.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="VIRUSES">
      <data key="d0">VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">General class of viral pathogens, including respiratory viruses, that are cited as targets for integrated lab-on-a-chip and microfluidic diagnostic systems. | Viral pathogens whose nucleic acids can be detected by SHERLOCK at attomolar concentrations; many clinically relevant viruses are transmissible via aerosols or respiratory droplets.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
      <data key="d6">VIRUSES</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BACTERIA">
      <data key="d0">BACTERIA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Bacterial pathogens referenced as additional targets that have been detected using integrated lab-on-a-chip microfluidic diagnostic systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.4</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INTEGRATED MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEM FOR INFLUENZA A VIRUS DETECTION AND SUBTYPING">
      <data key="d0">INTEGRATED MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEM FOR INFLUENZA A VIRUS DETECTION AND SUBTYPING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lab-on-a-chip microfluidic system developed by Shen et al. for influenza A virus detection and subtyping that automates virus extraction, purification, RT-PCR amplification, and on-chip fluorescence signal detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INSTRUMENT-FREE MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORM WITH A SINGLE MICROFLUIDIC DEVICE FOR ZIKA VIRUS DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">INSTRUMENT-FREE MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORM WITH A SINGLE MICROFLUIDIC DEVICE FOR ZIKA VIRUS DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A microfluidic platform developed by Song et al. for Zika virus detection that operates without external instruments, performing on-chip nucleic acid extraction, purification, enrichment, RT-LAMP amplification, and colorimetric DNA detection, while reagents and washing buffers are added manually.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EIGHT-CHANNEL MICROFLUIDIC ARRAY DEVICE INTEGRATED WITH A PORTABLE LAMP AMPLIFICATION SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">EIGHT-CHANNEL MICROFLUIDIC ARRAY DEVICE INTEGRATED WITH A PORTABLE LAMP AMPLIFICATION SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A point-of-care eight-channel microfluidic array device developed by Wang et al., integrated with a portable LAMP amplification system for rapid screening of respiratory viruses within about one hour, achieving high sensitivity in clinical samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AUTOMATED CRISPR-BASED MICROFLUIDIC CHIP AND ITS FLUID MANIPULATION AND SIGNAL DETECTION PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">AUTOMATED CRISPR-BASED MICROFLUIDIC CHIP AND ITS FLUID MANIPULATION AND SIGNAL DETECTION PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An automated CRISPR-based microfluidic chip with an associated platform for fluid manipulation and signal detection, designed to avoid explicit sample preparation and nucleic acid amplification steps, but currently exhibiting lower sensitivity and selectivity than standard amplification-based assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.92</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SMARTPHONE-BASED MULTIPLEXING NA DETECTION SYSTEM WITH SILICON MICROFLUIDIC LAMP CHIP">
      <data key="d0">SMARTPHONE-BASED MULTIPLEXING NA DETECTION SYSTEM WITH SILICON MICROFLUIDIC LAMP CHIP</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A multiplex nucleic acid detection system by Sun et al. for COVID-19 diagnostics that integrates a silicon microfluidic chip for LAMP amplification with a smartphone for fluorescence signal detection; nucleic acid extraction is not performed on-chip and repeated manual pipetting is required.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.93</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
