    <node id="AFRICAN SWINE FEVER VIRUS">
      <data key="d0">AFRICAN SWINE FEVER VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A viral pathogen mentioned as a target of other centrifugal microfluidic systems for virus detection, illustrating the broader applicability of this platform class.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_25,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_63</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DENGUE VIRUS">
      <data key="d0">DENGUE VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A mosquito-borne virus cited as another target of centrifugal microfluidic detection systems, indicating that similar platforms can be configured for this pathogen. | Dengue virus is a human pathogenic virus mentioned as a target for optical spectroscopic diagnostic methods, particularly Raman spectroscopy, in human blood samples; although vector-borne in reality, it is typed here as an AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN per the constrained schema.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_25,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_58,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_63</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
      <data key="d6">DENGUE VIRUS</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BIND-WASH-ELUTE PROTOCOL ON SILICA-COATED MAGNETIC BEADS">
      <data key="d0">BIND-WASH-ELUTE PROTOCOL ON SILICA-COATED MAGNETIC BEADS</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">An on-chip nucleic acid extraction workflow in which viral RNA binds to silica-coated magnetic beads, is washed to remove impurities, and then eluted prior to amplification and detection on the centrifugal microfluidic platform.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PREAMPLIFIED RNA ALIQUOTING INTO 13 CHAMBERS THROUGH CENTRIFUGATION">
      <data key="d0">PREAMPLIFIED RNA ALIQUOTING INTO 13 CHAMBERS THROUGH CENTRIFUGATION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A chip operation in which preamplified viral RNA is distributed by centrifugation into 13 separate reaction chambers to enable multiplexed amplification and detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MPADS">
      <data key="d0">MPADS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Microfluidic paper-based analytical devices that use passive capillary flow in porous, paper-like substrates to perform low-infrastructure assays for virus detection, suitable for point-of-care and resource-limited settings.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LFT STRIPS">
      <data key="d0">LFT STRIPS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Lateral flow test strips, a widely used implementation of microfluidic paper-based analytical devices that provide simple, equipment-free detection of viral targets via capillary-driven flow.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INTEGRATED PAPER-PLASTIC HYBRID MICROFLUIDIC DEVICE FOR NA-BASED TESTING OF MALARIA">
      <data key="d0">INTEGRATED PAPER-PLASTIC HYBRID MICROFLUIDIC DEVICE FOR NA-BASED TESTING OF MALARIA</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A paper–plastic hybrid microfluidic platform integrating an origami mPAD for DNA extraction and processing, a plastic microfluidic device for LAMP amplification, and four lateral flow test strips for colorimetric readout, used for nucleic acid-based testing of malaria from finger-prick blood.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
