      <data key="d0">PRODUCTION OF ANTIMICROBIAL PEPTIDES, VACCINES, AFFINITY CONJUGATES, AND SMALL MOLECULES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Use of the paper-based synthetic biology platform to biosynthesize a diverse range of functional products, including antimicrobial peptides, vaccines, affinity conjugates, and small molecules, demonstrating its versatility beyond diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_28</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-IN-A-CARTRIDGE QRT-PCR SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">LAB-IN-A-CARTRIDGE QRT-PCR SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lab-in-a-cartridge quantitative RT-PCR diagnostic platform using a plastic cartridge with integrated fluid channels and droplet magnetofluidics for automated nucleic acid testing and melt curve analysis. | An integrated microfluidic lab-in-a-cartridge system reported by Xu et al. that combines on-cartridge RNA extraction with one-color, three-chamber pseudo-multiplexing RT-PCR for rapid influenza virus detection within 2.5 hours, using embedded microfluidic channels for precise aliquoting.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
