      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A disposable cartridge with CNC-milled three-dimensional fluid channels and an integrated chemical heater designed to perform isothermal nucleic acid amplification and fluorescent signal detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ISOTHERMAL NA AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">ISOTHERMAL NA AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A nucleic acid amplification approach performed at a constant temperature within the self-heating cartridge, enabled by a chemical heater and simplifying thermal control. | A constant-temperature nucleic acid amplification method implemented on a microfluidic chip to increase respiratory virus nucleic acid copies prior to colorimetric detection. | A class of nucleic acid amplification methods performed at a constant temperature, used as an alternative to qPCR in some diagnostic strategies for avian influenza virus detection in poultry production systems. | A class of nucleic acid amplification methods performed at a constant temperature, often used for rapid diagnostics but with complex reaction mixtures that can be incompatible with clinical samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION</data>
    </node>
