      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A validation outcome showing that the lab-in-a-cartridge qRT-PCR system produces quantitative results closely matching standard laboratory viral load measurements and benchtop PCR.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PLASTIC CARTRIDGE WITH INTEGRATED FLUID CHANNELS">
      <data key="d0">PLASTIC CARTRIDGE WITH INTEGRATED FLUID CHANNELS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A generic lab-in-a-cartridge style plastic cartridge with integrated fluid channels and chambers used for streamlined fluid manipulation and multi-step nucleic acid testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PLUNGER ROD-OPERATED VALVE ROTATION">
      <data key="d0">PLUNGER ROD-OPERATED VALVE ROTATION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A mechanical actuation mechanism in the Xpert Xpress SARS-CoV-2 cartridge that drives valve rotation to automate fluid transport within the cartridge.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-ON-A-DRONE DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">LAB-ON-A-DRONE DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A mobile lab-in-a-box mounted on a commercial drone that uses convective thermocycling with a single heater for PCR, smartphone-based time-lapse fluorescence readout, and rotor-driven centrifugation for sample preparation, enabling airborne molecular diagnostics in the field.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CENTRIFUGATION-BASED SAMPLE PREPARATION">
      <data key="d0">CENTRIFUGATION-BASED SAMPLE PREPARATION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A centrifugation-based sample processing step implemented on the lab-on-a-drone system by using the four onboard rotors as a centrifuge to prepare samples prior to PCR-based detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OPTICAL DETECTION MODULE">
      <data key="d0">OPTICAL DETECTION MODULE</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The integrated optical detection module in the lab-in-a-cartridge system that reads RT-PCR-generated optical signals, with performance comparable to commercial thermal cyclers and manual workflows.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CUSTOM-BUILT THERMAL CYCLER">
      <data key="d0">CUSTOM-BUILT THERMAL CYCLER</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">A custom-built thermal cycler integrated into the lab-in-a-cartridge system to perform RT-PCR cycling, whose performance matches that of commercial thermal cyclers.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PERFORMANCE COMPARISON TO MANUAL RNA PURIFICATION AND COMMERCIAL THERMAL CYCLERS">
      <data key="d0">PERFORMANCE COMPARISON TO MANUAL RNA PURIFICATION AND COMMERCIAL THERMAL CYCLERS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">An assay validation indicating that the integrated RNA extraction, custom-built thermal cycler, and optical detection module in the lab-in-a-cartridge system perform comparably to manual RNA purification and commercial thermal cyclers.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_30</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LABORATORY-BASED PCR-BASED ASSAYS">
      <data key="d0">LABORATORY-BASED PCR-BASED ASSAYS</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Conventional PCR-based nucleic acid amplification assays performed in laboratory settings, serving as a major diagnostic method for viral infections including COVID-19, but requiring multi-step fluid manipulations and several hours to complete.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-BASED NA DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-BASED NA DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A nucleic-acid diagnostic platform that uses CRISPR-based detection chemistry to identify viral genetic material as a rapid alternative to PCR-based assays, capable of producing accurate results within about 5 minutes without solid-phase extraction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HOLLOW-CHANNEL MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORMS">
      <data key="d0">HOLLOW-CHANNEL MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Microfluidic diagnostic platforms that use hollow channels to process samples and implement CRISPR-based nucleic acid detection for viral diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PAPER-BASED MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORMS">
      <data key="d0">PAPER-BASED MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Paper-based microfluidic diagnostic platforms that integrate CRISPR-based nucleic acid detection for viral diagnostics, enabling low-cost and portable testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ISOTHERMAL NA AMPLIFICATION-BASED PLATFORMS">
      <data key="d0">ISOTHERMAL NA AMPLIFICATION-BASED PLATFORMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Diagnostic platforms that rely on isothermal nucleic acid amplification methods, such as LAMP, to detect viral genetic material under constant temperature, simplifying hardware and reducing assay time.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ABBOTT ID NOW SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">ABBOTT ID NOW SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A commercial isothermal amplification-based diagnostic system that performs rapid nucleic acid testing for pathogens such as SARS-CoV-2, with reduced system weight, size, and assay turnaround time.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SMARTPHONE-BASED TESTING">
      <data key="d0">SMARTPHONE-BASED TESTING</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagnostic approach in which a smartphone, combined with a portable integrated system and a customized analytical application, is used as the readout and analysis platform to quantify assay results without specialized medical expertise.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MICROFLUIDIC DEVICE DESIGNS">
      <data key="d0">MICROFLUIDIC DEVICE DESIGNS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Microfluidic device architectures that, when combined with isothermal testing, are anticipated to yield more compact COVID-19 diagnostic systems with shorter turnaround time.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PORTABLE INTEGRATED SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">PORTABLE INTEGRATED SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A compact diagnostic hardware unit that performs the assay and generates a measurable output, designed to be coupled with a smartphone and custom analytical application for result quantification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INTEGRATED LIONX DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">INTEGRATED LIONX DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An integrated diagnostic biosensor platform for COVID-19 that combines computation power and communication functions to read assays with sufficient sensitivity, positioned as an alternative to professional analytical readers and whose performance must be monitored as SARS-CoV-2 mutates.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COVID-19 ASSAY AND DETECTION SYSTEM DEVELOPMENT">
      <data key="d0">COVID-19 ASSAY AND DETECTION SYSTEM DEVELOPMENT</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">The ongoing process of developing, optimizing, and monitoring COVID-19 assays and detection systems, including evaluation of practical detection performance over time as SARS-CoV-2 mutates and new strains emerge.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_33</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="2019 NOVEL CORONAVIRUS (2019-NCOV)">
      <data key="d0">2019 NOVEL CORONAVIRUS (2019-NCOV)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">2019 novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV) is an early designation for SARS-CoV-2, referenced in the context of detection by real-time RT-PCR assays in Eurosurveillance; it is not a distinct pathogen from SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION TESTS FOR SARS-COV-2 DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION TESTS FOR SARS-COV-2 DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A set of nucleic acid amplification-based assays (e.g., RT-PCR and related methods) specifically evaluated for analytical and clinical performance in detecting SARS-CoV-2 RNA in patient samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NUCLEIC ACID TESTING APPROACHES FOR COVID-19 DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">NUCLEIC ACID TESTING APPROACHES FOR COVID-19 DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A broad group of nucleic acid testing strategies, generally involving amplification of viral RNA, reviewed as approaches for detecting SARS-CoV-2 infection in COVID-19 diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="POINT-OF-CARE RNA-BASED DIAGNOSTIC DEVICE FOR COVID-19">
      <data key="d0">POINT-OF-CARE RNA-BASED DIAGNOSTIC DEVICE FOR COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A point-of-care diagnostic platform that detects SARS-CoV-2 RNA at or near the site of patient care, integrating sample handling, nucleic acid processing, and signal readout for rapid COVID-19 diagnosis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAB-ON-A-CHIP TECHNOLOGIES FOR VIRAL DIAGNOSIS">
      <data key="d0">LAB-ON-A-CHIP TECHNOLOGIES FOR VIRAL DIAGNOSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Miniaturized lab-on-a-chip platforms that integrate microfluidics and biosensing components to diagnose viral infections, including configurations capable of detecting SARS-CoV-2 nucleic acids.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BIOSENSORS FOR VIRUS DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">BIOSENSORS FOR VIRUS DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Biosensor-based diagnostic platforms that detect viruses by recognizing viral nucleic acids or proteins and converting this recognition into a measurable signal, proposed as an alternative medical diagnosis method for virus detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COVID-19 TESTING CHALLENGES AND LIMITATIONS">
      <data key="d0">COVID-19 TESTING CHALLENGES AND LIMITATIONS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">The evaluation of practical, analytical, and clinical challenges and limitations associated with COVID-19 diagnostic testing, including constraints that affect validation, deployment, and performance of SARS-CoV-2 assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.65</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ASSAY TECHNIQUES AND TEST DEVELOPMENT FOR COVID-19 DIAGNOSIS">
      <data key="d0">ASSAY TECHNIQUES AND TEST DEVELOPMENT FOR COVID-19 DIAGNOSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Methodological frameworks and development strategies for COVID-19 diagnostic tests, covering how SARS-CoV-2 assays are designed, optimized, and evaluated for analytical and clinical performance.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PNEUMONIA OUTBREAK ASSOCIATED WITH A NEW CORONAVIRUS OF PROBABLE BAT ORIGIN">
      <data key="d0">PNEUMONIA OUTBREAK ASSOCIATED WITH A NEW CORONAVIRUS OF PROBABLE BAT ORIGIN</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Foundational epidemiological and virological characterization of the novel coronavirus (later termed SARS-CoV-2) associated with a pneumonia outbreak, providing reference data that underpin subsequent diagnostic assay design and validation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.55</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GENOMIC CHARACTERISATION AND EPIDEMIOLOGY OF 2019 NOVEL CORONAVIRUS">
      <data key="d0">GENOMIC CHARACTERISATION AND EPIDEMIOLOGY OF 2019 NOVEL CORONAVIRUS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A detailed study of the genome sequence and epidemiology of the 2019 novel coronavirus (SARS-CoV-2), supplying essential target sequence information and epidemiologic context for designing and validating nucleic acid-based diagnostic assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REAL-TIME RT-PCR">
      <data key="d0">REAL-TIME RT-PCR</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Real-time reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction, a nucleic acid amplification method used for COVID-19 detection that converts viral RNA to cDNA and amplifies it for quantitative measurement. | A real-time polymerase chain reaction method integrated into a self-contained cartridge for rapid influenza diagnosis, providing quantitative thermal amplification of target nucleic acids. | A thermal cycling-based nucleic acid amplification and quantification method used as a comparator to LAMP for detecting carbapenemase and ESBL genes in clinical samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_38,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_68</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">REALTIME PCR,REAL-TIME PCR</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TOTAL RNA EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">TOTAL RNA EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation procedures focused on isolating total RNA from specimens, with different methods compared for their performance in viral detection. | Extraction of DNA from stool samples using the AccuPrep Stool DNA Extraction Kit as a preparatory step for downstream ANCA analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">STOOL DNA EXTRACTION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PROTEIN EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">PROTEIN EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation procedures to isolate proteins from biological samples, mentioned alongside DNA and RNA extraction as part of biomolecular extraction workflows relevant to diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THERMAL INACTIVATION OF SAMPLES">
      <data key="d0">THERMAL INACTIVATION OF SAMPLES</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A pre-analytical treatment in which samples are heated to inactivate pathogens, noted as a factor that can cause potential false-negative nucleic acid testing results for SARS-CoV-2 when viral loads are low.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TOTAL RNA EXTRACTION FROM SPUTUM FOR VIRAL DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">TOTAL RNA EXTRACTION FROM SPUTUM FOR VIRAL DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Comparison of different methods for extracting total RNA from sputum samples as a pre-analytical step for viral detection assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RNA EXTRACTION FROM ANIMAL CELLS AND TISSUE USING SILICA COLUMNS">
      <data key="d0">RNA EXTRACTION FROM ANIMAL CELLS AND TISSUE USING SILICA COLUMNS</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A cost-effective silica column-based protocol for extracting RNA from animal cells and tissues prior to downstream molecular analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
