    <node id="REAL-TIME REVERSE-TRANSCRIPTION PCR">
      <data key="d0">REAL-TIME REVERSE-TRANSCRIPTION PCR</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A real-time reverse-transcription PCR (RT-PCR) amplification chemistry used as the core method in six commercial MERS-CoV RNA detection kits. | A quantitative RT-PCR method that monitors cDNA amplification in real time via fluorescent readout, enabling sensitive and specific detection and quantification of RNA targets such as SARS-CoV-2. | Real-time reverse transcription PCR (rRT-PCR) used as a molecular amplification and detection method for avian influenza virus in local veterinary laboratories, whose performance was assessed via national proficiency testing from 2020–2022. | RealTime reverse transcriptase PCR is a nucleic acid amplification method used for diagnosis and pathotyping of Eurasian H7 avian influenza viruses and other influenza A virus targets.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
      <data key="d6">REAL-TIME REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION-PCR,REAL-TIME REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION PCR (RRT-PCR),REALTIME REVERSE TRANSCRIPTASE PCR</data>
    </node>
