    <node id="REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION (RT-LAMP)">
      <data key="d0">REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION (RT-LAMP)</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">RT-LAMP is an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method that combines reverse transcription of RNA with loop-mediated amplification, enabling rapid and sensitive detection of RNA viruses such as ZIKV in field-relevant samples. | RT-LAMP, an isothermal amplification method that couples reverse transcription of RNA with LAMP, enabling rapid, single-temperature detection of RNA targets such as viral genomes. | An isothermal nucleic acid amplification method that combines reverse transcription with loop-mediated amplification at a constant temperature, enabling rapid detection of RNA viruses such as H5N1 avian influenza without a thermocycler.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_45</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
      <data key="d6">REVERSE TRANSCRIPTIONAL LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION,REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION (RT-LAMP)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="2019-NCOV">
      <data key="d0">2019-NCOV</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">2019-nCoV is an early designation for the novel coronavirus responsible for the COVID-19 outbreak originating in Wuhan, China, discussed in the context of modelling its spread and molecular diagnosis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_45</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COVID-19 REAL-TIME RRT-PCR PANEL">
      <data key="d0">COVID-19 REAL-TIME RRT-PCR PANEL</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">The COVID-19 real-time rRT-PCR panel is a CDC-designed real-time reverse transcription PCR assay panel that uses specific primers and probes for detection of 2019-nCoV/SARS-CoV-2 RNA in clinical specimens.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_45</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COVID-19-RDRP/HEL REAL-TIME ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">COVID-19-RDRP/HEL REAL-TIME ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">The COVID-19-RdRp/hel real-time assay is a novel, highly sensitive and specific real-time molecular assay targeting the RNA-dependent RNA polymerase/helicase (RdRp/hel) region of the 2019-nCoV/SARS-CoV-2 genome to improve molecular diagnosis of COVID-19.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_45</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION-PCR">
      <data key="d0">REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION-PCR</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A thermal nucleic acid amplification method that first reverse-transcribes RNA into complementary DNA (cDNA) and then amplifies the cDNA by PCR; used as the core chemistry in many viral diagnostic assays including COVID-19 tests. | Reverse transcription (RT)-PCR is a nucleic acid amplification method that first converts RNA to cDNA and then amplifies it; Wang et al. used RT-PCR as the amplification step in a PfAgo-based assay for detecting SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION (RT)-PCR</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COVID-19-RDRP/HEL REAL-TIME REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION-PCR ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">COVID-19-RDRP/HEL REAL-TIME REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION-PCR ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">A specific real-time RT-PCR diagnostic assay targeting the RdRp/hel region of SARS-CoV-2, reported as highly sensitive and specific for improved molecular diagnosis of COVID-19 and validated in vitro and with clinical specimens.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">LAMP, an isothermal DNA amplification technique that uses multiple specially designed primers and a strand-displacing DNA polymerase to amplify nucleic acids at a constant temperature without thermal cycling. | Loop-mediated isothermal amplification (LAMP), an isothermal amplification method used in paper-based assays for highly pathogenic avian influenza, enabling rapid nucleic acid amplification without thermocycling. | A specific isothermal amplification method (LAMP) compared with real-time PCR for detecting carbapenemase and ESBL genes directly from bronchoalveolar lavage fluid.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_48,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_56,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RECOMBINATION PROTEIN–MEDIATED DNA DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">RECOMBINATION PROTEIN–MEDIATED DNA DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A recombinase-based nucleic acid detection approach in which recombination proteins facilitate primer targeting and strand exchange to enable isothermal DNA amplification and detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MOLECULAR-BASED ISOTHERMAL TESTS FOR FIELD DIAGNOSIS OF MALARIA">
      <data key="d0">MOLECULAR-BASED ISOTHERMAL TESTS FOR FIELD DIAGNOSIS OF MALARIA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A set of evaluations of molecular isothermal diagnostic tests, including LAMP- and RPA-type methods, for field diagnosis of malaria and their potential contribution to malaria elimination programs.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION OF NUCLEIC ACIDS">
      <data key="d0">ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION OF NUCLEIC ACIDS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A review and characterization of isothermal nucleic acid amplification methods, summarizing mechanisms, performance, and diagnostic applications of techniques such as LAMP and RPA.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION AND QUANTIFICATION OF NUCLEIC ACIDS AND ITS USE IN MICROSYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION AND QUANTIFICATION OF NUCLEIC ACIDS AND ITS USE IN MICROSYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A study describing how isothermal amplification strategies can be implemented for both amplification and quantification of nucleic acids, particularly in miniaturized microsystem formats.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION OF DNA">
      <data key="d0">LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION OF DNA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A foundational experimental study that established LAMP as a robust isothermal DNA amplification method, detailing its reaction design, sensitivity, and specificity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ACCELERATED REACTION BY LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION USING LOOP PRIMERS">
      <data key="d0">ACCELERATED REACTION BY LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION USING LOOP PRIMERS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A study demonstrating that the inclusion of loop primers accelerates LAMP reactions, significantly reducing time-to-result while maintaining amplification efficiency.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REVERSE TRANSCRIPTIONAL LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION (RT-LAMP) DIAGNOSTIC PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">REVERSE TRANSCRIPTIONAL LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION (RT-LAMP) DIAGNOSTIC PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagnostic platform built around RT-LAMP chemistry for rapid, isothermal amplification and detection of RNA targets, designed for clinical diagnostic use.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DNA DETECTION USING RECOMBINATION PROTEINS">
      <data key="d0">DNA DETECTION USING RECOMBINATION PROTEINS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">An experimental study that validates DNA detection based on recombination proteins, characterizing the performance of recombinase-driven isothermal amplification approaches.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION: BASICS, APPLICATIONS AND RECENT ADVANCES">
      <data key="d0">RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION: BASICS, APPLICATIONS AND RECENT ADVANCES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A review article summarizing the principles, applications, and recent developments of recombinase polymerase amplification (RPA) as a rapid isothermal nucleic acid amplification method.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ISOTHERMAL RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">ISOTHERMAL RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Isothermal recombinase polymerase amplification refers to RPA performed at a single, constant temperature, simplifying instrument requirements and facilitating integration into disposable and microfluidic devices.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MICROFLUIDIC LAB-ON-A-FOIL FOR NUCLEIC ACID ANALYSIS BASED ON ISOTHERMAL RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">MICROFLUIDIC LAB-ON-A-FOIL FOR NUCLEIC ACID ANALYSIS BASED ON ISOTHERMAL RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A microfluidic lab-on-a-foil device that performs nucleic acid analysis using isothermal RPA within a flexible foil-based microfluidic architecture, enabling rapid, low-temperature nucleic acid testing in a disposable format.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REAL-TIME MICROFLUIDIC RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION SLIPCHIP PLATFORM FOR CLOSTRIDIUM DIFFICILE TOXIN B GENE">
      <data key="d0">REAL-TIME MICROFLUIDIC RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION SLIPCHIP PLATFORM FOR CLOSTRIDIUM DIFFICILE TOXIN B GENE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A real-time microfluidic SlipChip platform implementing recombinase polymerase amplification to detect the toxin B gene of Clostridium difficile, providing integrated, quantitative nucleic acid detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MODIFIED RT-RPA">
      <data key="d0">MODIFIED RT-RPA</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Modified RT-RPA is a reverse-transcription recombinase polymerase amplification variant optimized for single-copy sensitivity and simultaneous dual-gene detection of RNA targets such as SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FIELD-DEPLOYABLE DUAL-GENE SARS-COV-2 RNA DETECTION VIA MODIFIED RT-RPA">
      <data key="d0">FIELD-DEPLOYABLE DUAL-GENE SARS-COV-2 RNA DETECTION VIA MODIFIED RT-RPA</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A field-deployable assay platform that uses modified RT-RPA to achieve single-copy sensitivity and simultaneous dual-gene detection of SARS-CoV-2 RNA, enabling highly sensitive point-of-care viral diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CLOSTRIDIUM DIFFICILE">
      <data key="d0">CLOSTRIDIUM DIFFICILE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Clostridium difficile is a bacterial pathogen primarily associated with gastrointestinal infection; its toxin B gene is a nucleic acid target for microfluidic RPA-based diagnostic platforms.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CLOSTRIDIUM DIFFICILE TOXIN B GENE TARGET">
      <data key="d0">CLOSTRIDIUM DIFFICILE TOXIN B GENE TARGET</data>
      <data key="d1">GUIDE_RNA</data>
      <data key="d2">The toxin B gene sequence of Clostridium difficile serves as the specific nucleic acid target for the SlipChip RPA assay; in CRISPR-based systems, a guide RNA would be designed against this sequence to confer specificity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.55</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INTEGRATED DISPOSABLE DEVICE FOR DNA EXTRACTION AND HELICASE DEPENDENT AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">INTEGRATED DISPOSABLE DEVICE FOR DNA EXTRACTION AND HELICASE DEPENDENT AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A disposable integrated device that combines on-chip DNA extraction with helicase dependent amplification, forming a compact platform for isothermal nucleic acid detection at the point of care.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXPAR">
      <data key="d0">EXPAR</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">EXPAR (exponential amplification reaction) is an isothermal DNA amplification method that can exhibit strong sequence dependence and is used for rapid nucleic acid signal amplification in diagnostic assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PAPER-BASED RNA EXTRACTION, IN SITU ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION, AND LATERAL FLOW DETECTION PLATFORM FOR INFLUENZA A (H1N1)">
      <data key="d0">PAPER-BASED RNA EXTRACTION, IN SITU ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION, AND LATERAL FLOW DETECTION PLATFORM FOR INFLUENZA A (H1N1)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A paper-based diagnostic platform that integrates RNA extraction, in situ isothermal amplification, and lateral flow detection to provide low-cost, rapid diagnosis of influenza A (H1N1) from clinical specimens.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="IN SITU ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">IN SITU ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">In situ isothermal amplification refers to performing nucleic acid amplification directly on a solid support, such as paper, at constant temperature, simplifying workflows in low-cost diagnostic platforms.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LATERAL FLOW DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">LATERAL FLOW DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Lateral flow detection is a strip-based visual readout method in which labeled amplification products migrate along a membrane and generate a visible line or band indicating target presence.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INFLUENZA A (H1N1)">
      <data key="d0">INFLUENZA A (H1N1)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Influenza A (H1N1) is a respiratory virus transmitted via aerosols and droplets and is an airborne pathogen targeted by paper-based isothermal amplification and lateral flow diagnostic platforms.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.94</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_47,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_48</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
