      <data key="d0">WEST NILE VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A viral pathogen cited as the target of a real-time reverse transcription loop-mediated isothermal amplification assay; included as a nucleic-acid-detectable pathogen in isothermal amplification workflows.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.4</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_48</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HIV-1">
      <data key="d0">HIV-1</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Human immunodeficiency virus type 1, mentioned as the target of rapid detection by RT-LAMP; while not airborne, it is a key viral pathogen in nucleic acid amplification-based diagnostic assay development.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_48,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_49,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_57,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_65</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Reverse transcription loop-mediated isothermal amplification (RT-LAMP), an isothermal amplification method that incorporates reverse transcription to detect RNA targets such as SARS-CoV-2, West Nile virus, and HIV-1.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_48</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ISOTHERMAL NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION METHODS">
      <data key="d0">ISOTHERMAL NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION METHODS</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A collective term for nucleic acid amplification techniques that operate at a constant temperature, evaluated comparatively for SARS-CoV-2 detection at the point of care. | A class of nucleic acid amplification techniques that operate at a constant temperature and are proposed as alternative diagnostic methods to culture and PCR for rapid, accurate, and cost-effective detection of carbapenemase-producing Enterobacteriaceae (CPE). | An isothermal nucleic acid amplification process underlying the ANCA method, enabling nucleic acid amplification at a constant temperature within a portable device.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_48</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">ISOTHERMAL NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION METHODS,ISOTHERMAL NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION IN ANCA METHOD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HANDHELD LATERAL FLOW STRIP FOR RAPID DNA EXTRACTION FROM STAPHYLOCOCCUS AUREUS">
