      <data key="d0">ISOTHERMAL NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of nucleic acid amplification methods that operate at a constant temperature, used here in combination with a lateral-flow device for visual detection of Zika virus. | A class of nucleic acid amplification methods operating at constant temperature, often used in one-pot formats with CRISPR/Cas detection to enable rapid, equipment-light diagnostics.</data>
