      <data key="d0">LATERAL-FLOW DEVICE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lateral-flow assay strip used as a visual readout platform when coupled to upstream nucleic acid amplification for pathogen detection, including Zika virus.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_49</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="2019 NOVEL CORONAVIRUS (COVID-19)">
      <data key="d0">2019 NOVEL CORONAVIRUS (COVID-19)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">The 2019 novel coronavirus, SARS-CoV-2, a respiratory virus targeted by single- and two-stage closed-tube molecular tests for use at home, in clinics, and at points of entry. | 2019 novel coronavirus disease (COVID-19), caused by SARS-CoV-2, is referenced in the context of rapid detection and point-of-care diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
