    <node id="CRISPR-CAS13A/C2C2">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-CAS13A/C2C2</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">The Cas13a (formerly C2c2) RNA-targeting CRISPR effector family with programmable and collateral RNase activity, used as the core nuclease in nucleic acid detection platforms such as SHERLOCK. | The Cas13a (formerly C2c2) CRISPR effector system used for nucleic acid detection, enabling RNA-guided recognition and collateral cleavage-based signal generation in diagnostic assays. | An RNA-guided RNase effector (formerly C2c2) used in CRISPR-based diagnostics; upon binding its RNA target, it exhibits collateral cleavage of nearby RNAs, enabling signal amplification in nucleic acid detection assays. | A Cas13a (C2c2) RNA-targeting effector nuclease used in CRISPR-based nucleic acid detection platforms, capable of collateral cleavage of reporter RNA molecules upon target recognition to generate a detectable signal. | An RNA-guided CRISPR effector nuclease (Cas13a, formerly C2c2) with target-activated collateral RNase activity, widely used as the core enzyme in CRISPR-based nucleic acid detection assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_50,ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d5">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1,4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99,6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">CRISPR-CAS13A/C2C2,CRISPR-CAS13A (C2C2)</data>
    </node>
