      <data key="d0">CRISPR-CAS12A-ASSISTED NUCLEIC ACID DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR-based nucleic acid detection assay that uses the Cas12a effector to detect target sequences, as described by Li et al. (2018). It leverages Cas12a’s collateral ssDNase activity for signal generation in molecular diagnostics. | A nucleic acid detection assay that uses Cas12a as the core effector enzyme, exploiting its target-activated indiscriminate ssDNA cleavage to amplify reporter signal for sensitive nucleic acid detection. | CRISPR-Cas12a-assisted nucleic acid detection is a CRISPR-based biosensing platform that uses Cas12a to recognize target nucleic acids and generate a detectable signal. | A nucleic acid detection strategy described by Li et al. that leverages Cas12a’s target-activated DNase activity to detect specific nucleic acid sequences, forming a conceptual basis for later Cas12a diagnostic assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">ed45ef2f-ad29-4058-8b09-5fed00b411a1_chunk_64</data>
