      <data key="d0">SPECIFICITY PROFILE FOR SARS-COV-2 SCREENING</data>
      <data key="d1">SPECIFICITY_PROFILE</data>
      <data key="d2">Overall specificity characteristics of the hyperspectral imaging assay, including the reported peak specificity of 87.5% against PCR-negative symptomatic controls.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANTIGEN TESTS">
      <data key="d0">ANTIGEN TESTS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Rapid immunoassay-based diagnostic tests that detect SARS-CoV-2 antigens, suitable for at-home use with results in about 15 minutes but with lower sensitivity and higher false-negative rates than PCR.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_6</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-BASED STRATEGIES">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-BASED STRATEGIES</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of molecular diagnostic platforms that use CRISPR effector enzymes and guide RNAs to detect nucleic acids, applied here to improve SARS-CoV-2 and other nucleic acid target detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_6</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="N GENE TARGETED ANTISENSE OLIGONUCLEOTIDE CAPPED PLASMONIC NANOPARTICLES">
      <data key="d0">N GENE TARGETED ANTISENSE OLIGONUCLEOTIDE CAPPED PLASMONIC NANOPARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A plasmonic nanoparticle-based biosensor functionalized with antisense oligonucleotides targeting the SARS-CoV-2 N gene, enabling selective naked-eye detection of the virus. | A plasmonic nanoparticle-based biosensing platform functionalized with antisense oligonucleotides targeting the SARS-CoV-2 N gene, enabling selective naked-eye detection via colorimetric changes in the ACS Nano 2020 study.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_6</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
      <data key="d6">N GENE–TARGETED ANTISENSE OLIGONUCLEOTIDE CAPPED PLASMONIC NANOPARTICLES</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RAMAN SPECTROSCOPY VIRUS DETECTION PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">RAMAN SPECTROSCOPY VIRUS DETECTION PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An optical biosensing platform that uses Raman spectroscopy to identify viral infections (e.g., Dengue virus, hepatitis B and C) in human blood or serum based on vibrational spectral signatures.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MICROFLUIDIC VIRUS CAPTURE AND IDENTIFICATION PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">MICROFLUIDIC VIRUS CAPTURE AND IDENTIFICATION PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A microfluidic, rapid, label-free optical platform designed to capture and identify viruses such as avian influenza A and other respiratory pathogens directly from clinical samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NANOMATERIAL-ENHANCED OPTICAL SPECTROSCOPY PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">NANOMATERIAL-ENHANCED OPTICAL SPECTROSCOPY PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An optical spectroscopic virus detection platform that incorporates nanomaterials targeted to specific viral antibodies to enhance signal and improve detection of viruses such as human immunodeficiency virus.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DIFFUSE REFLECTANCE NEAR-INFRARED SPECTROSCOPY PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">DIFFUSE REFLECTANCE NEAR-INFRARED SPECTROSCOPY PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A simple, noninvasive optical platform using diffuse reflectance near-infrared spectroscopy to distinguish mosquitoes infected with Zika virus from uninfected controls based on spectral differences.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OTHER RESPIRATORY INFECTION VIRUSES">
      <data key="d0">OTHER RESPIRATORY INFECTION VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A collective reference to additional respiratory viruses captured and identified by the microfluidic platform, indicating a broader class of airborne/respiratory pathogens addressed by the device.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.4</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COLORIMETRIC RT-LAMP ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">COLORIMETRIC RT-LAMP ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A colorimetric reverse-transcription loop-mediated isothermal amplification method used to amplify SARS-CoV-2 RNA in clinical samples, producing a visible color change as the readout.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SYNTHETIC VIRAL MODEL COMMONLY EMPLOYED FOR THE STUDY OF SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d0">SYNTHETIC VIRAL MODEL COMMONLY EMPLOYED FOR THE STUDY OF SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A synthetic viral model used as a surrogate for SARS-CoV-2 in hyperspectral imaging studies, enabling safe detection, identification, and quantification of virus-like particles in fluid samples via hyperspectral imaging of diffuse reflectance in the visible and near-infrared ranges.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SYNTHETIC VIRAL MODEL FOR SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d0">SYNTHETIC VIRAL MODEL FOR SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A synthetic viral surrogate commonly used to study and model SARS-CoV-2 behavior; detected via hyperspectral imaging of diffuse reflectance in the visible and near-infrared ranges.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HYPERSPECTRAL IMAGING OF DIFFUSE REFLECTANCE (VISIBLE AND NEAR-INFRARED)">
      <data key="d0">HYPERSPECTRAL IMAGING OF DIFFUSE REFLECTANCE (VISIBLE AND NEAR-INFRARED)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An optical biosensing platform that uses hyperspectral imaging of diffuse reflectance in the visible and near-infrared ranges to detect a synthetic viral model related to SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GAS CHROMATOGRAPHY-BASED BREATH ANALYSIS">
      <data key="d0">GAS CHROMATOGRAPHY-BASED BREATH ANALYSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A breath analysis platform using gas chromatography to detect SARS-CoV-2-related markers in exhaled air as part of non-contact, rapid COVID-19 screening approaches.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MASS SPECTROMETRY-BASED BREATH ANALYSIS">
      <data key="d0">MASS SPECTROMETRY-BASED BREATH ANALYSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A breath analysis platform using mass spectrometry to detect SARS-CoV-2-related markers in exhaled air and salivary aerosols for rapid COVID-19 screening.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PHOTONICS BIOSENSORS FOR BREATH ANALYSIS">
      <data key="d0">PHOTONICS BIOSENSORS FOR BREATH ANALYSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Optical biosensor platforms based on photonics used to detect SARS-CoV-2 or indirect markers in exhaled air and salivary aerosols for non-contact COVID-19 screening.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ELECTRONIC NOSE BREATH SENSORS">
      <data key="d0">ELECTRONIC NOSE BREATH SENSORS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Breath analysis platforms based on electronic nose concepts that sense complex volatile patterns in exhaled air to infer the presence of SARS-CoV-2 infection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TERAHERTZ SPECTROSCOPY BREATH ANALYSIS">
      <data key="d0">TERAHERTZ SPECTROSCOPY BREATH ANALYSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A breath analysis platform using terahertz spectroscopy to detect SARS-CoV-2 or related markers in exhaled air and salivary aerosols as a rapid, non-contact screening method.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ALPHA">
      <data key="d0">ALPHA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Alpha is a SARS-CoV-2 variant of concern; it is an airborne viral strain whose mutations can affect transmissibility, disease severity, and the performance of diagnostic tests and public health measures.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BETA">
      <data key="d0">BETA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Beta is a SARS-CoV-2 variant of concern; it is an airborne viral strain with mutations that may modify spread, clinical impact, and the effectiveness of existing diagnostic and public health interventions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GAMMA">
      <data key="d0">GAMMA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Gamma is a SARS-CoV-2 variant of concern; it is an airborne viral strain whose mutations can alter transmission dynamics and challenge diagnostic tests that are not variant-specific.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DELTA">
      <data key="d0">DELTA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Delta is a SARS-CoV-2 variant of concern; it is an airborne viral strain associated with increased transmissibility and potentially altered disease severity, emphasizing the need for tests that can distinguish specific variants.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OMICRON">
      <data key="d0">OMICRON</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Omicron is a SARS-CoV-2 variant of concern; its extensive mutations can impact transmissibility and diagnostic performance, underscoring the lack of authorized tests for specific SARS-CoV-2 variants as of December 2021.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OPTICAL DIFFUSE REFLECTANCE HYPERSPECTRAL IMAGING IN THE VISIBLE AND NEAR INFRARED RANGES COMBINED WITH SPECIFIC DATA ANALYSIS">
      <data key="d0">OPTICAL DIFFUSE REFLECTANCE HYPERSPECTRAL IMAGING IN THE VISIBLE AND NEAR INFRARED RANGES COMBINED WITH SPECIFIC DATA ANALYSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A proof-of-concept biosensing platform that uses optical diffuse reflectance hyperspectral imaging in the visible and near-infrared ranges, together with dedicated data analysis, to enable fast primary screening of 5-µL fluid samples for SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.93</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FAST PRIMARY SCREENING OF SARS-COV-2 IN 5-ΜL FLUID SAMPLES DEPOSITED ON A SURFACE">
      <data key="d0">FAST PRIMARY SCREENING OF SARS-COV-2 IN 5-ΜL FLUID SAMPLES DEPOSITED ON A SURFACE</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">The specific implementation of the hyperspectral imaging-based test, in which 5-µL fluid samples deposited on a surface are rapidly screened for the presence of SARS-CoV-2 using optical diffuse reflectance hyperspectral imaging and data analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="VNIR HYPERSPECTRAL IMAGING DROPLET ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">VNIR HYPERSPECTRAL IMAGING DROPLET ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A visible and near-infrared (VNIR) hyperspectral imaging platform that analyzes small (5 µL) droplets of water-based, optically transparent biofluids on a supporting plate, using sub-surface scattering and averaged pixel spectra relative to background to distinguish SARS-CoV-2-positive samples from negative controls at droplet and patient levels.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SARS-COV-2 IN NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATE AND SALIVA">
      <data key="d0">SARS-COV-2 IN NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATE AND SALIVA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">SARS-CoV-2 viral particles present in human nasopharyngeal exudate and fresh saliva samples, with particle diameters of approximately 120–140 nm, below the resolution of the VNIR optical imaging used in the assay.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DROPLET DEPOSITION ON SUPPORTING PLATE">
      <data key="d0">DROPLET DEPOSITION ON SUPPORTING PLATE</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation step in which 5 µL droplets of synthetic viral models in saline, artificial saliva, and human clinical samples (SARS-CoV-2-positive and corresponding negative controls) are deposited on a supporting plate for VNIR hyperspectral imaging.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BACKGROUND-REFERENCED SPECTRAL AVERAGING AND INTEGRATION">
      <data key="d0">BACKGROUND-REFERENCED SPECTRAL AVERAGING AND INTEGRATION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">The analysis procedure for the VNIR hyperspectral assay, which computes averaged differences of pixel spectra relative to the background and integrates them at droplet and patient levels, instead of relying on distinct spectral peaks or absorption bands.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUB-SURFACE SCATTERING–BASED REFLECTANCE SIGNAL">
      <data key="d0">SUB-SURFACE SCATTERING–BASED REFLECTANCE SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The optical reflectance signal arising primarily from sub-surface scattering within the 5 µL biofluid droplets under VNIR illumination, used as the measurable output for distinguishing positive from negative samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_15</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HYPERSPECTRAL IMAGING AND SPECTRAL DATA ANALYSIS PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">HYPERSPECTRAL IMAGING AND SPECTRAL DATA ANALYSIS PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A biosensing platform that uses hyperspectral optical diffuse reflectance measurements in the visible and near-infrared ranges, converted to pseudo-absorbance spectra and processed with spectral feature descriptors, PLS-DA, and a feed-forward neural network to detect and quantify SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXPERIMENT 1: SYNTHETIC SARS-COV-2 MODELS WITH AND WITHOUT SPIKE PROTEIN">
      <data key="d0">EXPERIMENT 1: SYNTHETIC SARS-COV-2 MODELS WITH AND WITHOUT SPIKE PROTEIN</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Assay run evaluating the platform’s ability to discern between two types of synthetic SARS-CoV-2 models, one bearing the characteristic spike protein and one lacking it.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXPERIMENT 2: CLASSIFICATION OF SARS-COV-2-POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATE SAMPLES">
      <data key="d0">EXPERIMENT 2: CLASSIFICATION OF SARS-COV-2-POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATE SAMPLES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Assay run assessing classification performance of the platform on human nasopharyngeal exudate samples that are SARS-CoV-2-positive or negative, using the same specimens employed for conventional PCR tests.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXPERIMENT 3: OBSERVATIONAL STUDY OF FRESH SARS-COV-2-POSITIVE SAMPLES">
      <data key="d0">EXPERIMENT 3: OBSERVATIONAL STUDY OF FRESH SARS-COV-2-POSITIVE SAMPLES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Observational, descriptive assay run using fresh SARS-CoV-2-positive samples to study their hyperspectral signatures with the developed platform.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OPTICAL DIFFUSE REFLECTANCE TO PSEUDO-ABSORBANCE CONVERSION">
      <data key="d0">OPTICAL DIFFUSE REFLECTANCE TO PSEUDO-ABSORBANCE CONVERSION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Data preprocessing step in which optical diffuse reflectance spectra in the visible and near-infrared ranges are converted into pseudo-absorbance spectra prior to feature extraction and modeling.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SPECTRAL FEATURE DESCRIPTORS (SFDS)">
      <data key="d0">SPECTRAL FEATURE DESCRIPTORS (SFDS)</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Derived spectral metrics computed from pseudo-absorbance spectra that summarize relevant optical features used as input signals for classification and quantification of SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PARTIAL LEAST-SQUARES DISCRIMINANT ANALYSIS (PLS-DA)">
      <data key="d0">PARTIAL LEAST-SQUARES DISCRIMINANT ANALYSIS (PLS-DA)</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A multivariate discriminant modeling approach applied to the spectral data to generate latent variables and decision scores that serve as analytical signals for distinguishing SARS-CoV-2-positive from negative samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.65</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FEED-FORWARD NEURAL NETWORK (FFNN) CLASSIFIER">
      <data key="d0">FEED-FORWARD NEURAL NETWORK (FFNN) CLASSIFIER</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A machine learning model that processes spectral inputs to produce classification outputs and quantitative estimates related to the presence and amount of SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HYPERSPECTRAL IMAGING ASSAY WITH FEED-FORWARD NEURAL NETWORK CLASSIFIER">
      <data key="d0">HYPERSPECTRAL IMAGING ASSAY WITH FEED-FORWARD NEURAL NETWORK CLASSIFIER</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A biosensing platform that illuminates fluid droplets with halogen lamps, records VNIR hyperspectral images using a sliding sensor, digitally preprocesses pixel reflectance spectra into pseudo-absorbance, extracts spectral feature descriptors, and uses a trained feed-forward neural network to perform pixel-based binary classification of viral content.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.93</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SPIKE PSEUDOTYPED LENTIVIRAL PARTICLES (SYNTHETIC CORONAVIRUSES)">
      <data key="d0">SPIKE PSEUDOTYPED LENTIVIRAL PARTICLES (SYNTHETIC CORONAVIRUSES)</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Lentiviral particles pseudotyped with coronavirus spike protein, used as synthetic coronavirus surrogates that generate characteristic spectral signatures in the hyperspectral imaging assay to model and detect viral content.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HUMAN SALIVA SAMPLES FROM SARS-COV-2 SUSPECTS">
      <data key="d0">HUMAN SALIVA SAMPLES FROM SARS-COV-2 SUSPECTS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Fresh human saliva samples, both SARS-CoV-2-positive and negative, collected from suspected COVID-19 cases and analyzed by the hyperspectral imaging assay as part of an observational, descriptive study.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INACTIVATED NASOPHARYNGEAL SWAB SAMPLES FOR SARS-COV-2 PCR TESTS">
      <data key="d0">INACTIVATED NASOPHARYNGEAL SWAB SAMPLES FOR SARS-COV-2 PCR TESTS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Inactivated human nasopharyngeal exudate samples, the same specimens used for conventional SARS-CoV-2 PCR testing, analyzed by the hyperspectral imaging assay to compare imaging-based detection with standard molecular diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CONVENTIONAL SARS-COV-2 PCR TESTS">
      <data key="d0">CONVENTIONAL SARS-COV-2 PCR TESTS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Standard molecular diagnostic PCR assays for SARS-CoV-2 used as a reference method to characterize the positivity or negativity of nasopharyngeal and saliva samples and to validate the performance of the hyperspectral imaging assay.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.77</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PHOTOACOUSTIC SPECTRAL DETECTION PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">PHOTOACOUSTIC SPECTRAL DETECTION PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An optical/photoacoustic hyperspectral imaging and analysis platform that acquires pixel-level reflectance spectra from droplets containing viral particles and applies methods such as partial least squares-discriminant analysis (PLS-DA) to detect the presence of viral content.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_18</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ENGINEERED SARS-COV-2-LIKE VIRAL PARTICLES">
      <data key="d0">ENGINEERED SARS-COV-2-LIKE VIRAL PARTICLES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Engineered viral particles designed to resemble SARS-CoV-2 virions in overall shape, diameter, double lipid envelope, and spike protein-decorated surface. They are used as safer surrogates for SARS-CoV-2 to enable preliminary assessment of the detection approach while reducing biosafety requirements.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SPECTRAL DISCRIMINATION OF SPIKE PSEUDOTYPED LENTIVIRAL PARTICLES (EXPERIMENT 1, PLS-DA MODEL 1)">
      <data key="d0">SPECTRAL DISCRIMINATION OF SPIKE PSEUDOTYPED LENTIVIRAL PARTICLES (EXPERIMENT 1, PLS-DA MODEL 1)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Optical biosensing approach that uses pseudo-absorbance pixel spectra and partial least squares-discriminant analysis (PLS-DA Model 1) to discriminate SARS-CoV-2 spike pseudotyped lentiviral particles from negative controls in phosphate buffered solution and artificial saliva, at different viral concentrations.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PLS-DA MODEL 1 TENFOLD CROSS-VALIDATION">
      <data key="d0">PLS-DA MODEL 1 TENFOLD CROSS-VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Tenfold cross-validation procedure applied to PLS-DA Model 1 to evaluate its performance in discriminating SARS-CoV-2 spike pseudotyped lentiviral particles from controls on a per-pixel basis, summarized by an overall score value and linear correlations.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXPERIMENT 1 ASSAY RUN (S-LP AND G-LP IN PBS AND ARTIFICIAL SALIVA)">
      <data key="d0">EXPERIMENT 1 ASSAY RUN (S-LP AND G-LP IN PBS AND ARTIFICIAL SALIVA)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Specific experimental run in which pseudo-absorbance spectra of SARS-CoV-2 spike pseudotyped lentiviral particles (S-LP and G-LP) at high and low concentrations, and their negative controls, were measured in phosphate buffered solution and artificial saliva for spectral discrimination.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PSEUDO-ABSORBANCE (PA) PIXEL SPECTRA AND SPECTRAL FEATURE DESCRIPTOR (SFD, 483–610 NM)">
      <data key="d0">PSEUDO-ABSORBANCE (PA) PIXEL SPECTRA AND SPECTRAL FEATURE DESCRIPTOR (SFD, 483–610 NM)</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Optical readout comprising mean pseudo-absorbance pixel spectra and a derived spectral feature descriptor computed in the 483–610 nm band, used as the signal features for discriminating SARS-CoV-2 spike pseudotyped lentiviral particles from negative controls.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SAMPLE PREPARATION IN PHOSPHATE BUFFERED SOLUTION AND ARTIFICIAL SALIVA">
      <data key="d0">SAMPLE PREPARATION IN PHOSPHATE BUFFERED SOLUTION AND ARTIFICIAL SALIVA</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Preparation of spike pseudotyped lentiviral particles in phosphate buffered solution (PBS) and artificial saliva (AS), including high and low viral concentrations and corresponding negative controls, to mimic expelled respiratory fluids and human specimens for optical detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OPTICAL TECHNIQUE FOR VIRUS-SPECIFIC DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">OPTICAL TECHNIQUE FOR VIRUS-SPECIFIC DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An optical, pixel-based classification method that uses spectral feature descriptors to obtain virus-specific information related to proteins integrated in the viral capsid and to discern the presence of the SARS-CoV-2 spike protein in various sample matrices.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.96</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PLS-DA PIXEL-BASED CLASSIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">PLS-DA PIXEL-BASED CLASSIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A partial least squares discriminant analysis–based pixel-level optical classification method used as one of the two approaches to analyze viral solutions and inactivated nasopharyngeal exudates for SARS-CoV-2 detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FFNN PIXEL-BASED CLASSIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">FFNN PIXEL-BASED CLASSIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A feed-forward neural network–based pixel-level optical classification method used alongside PLS-DA to analyze viral solutions and inactivated nasopharyngeal exudates for SARS-CoV-2 detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INACTIVATED NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATE SPECIMENS">
      <data key="d0">INACTIVATED NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATE SPECIMENS</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Clinical nasopharyngeal exudate samples used for PCR testing that have been inactivated in transport media containing lysis buffer, resulting in loss of native viral particle structure while preserving genetic material for safer optical analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GUANIDINIUM THIOCYANATE LYSIS BUFFER">
      <data key="d0">GUANIDINIUM THIOCYANATE LYSIS BUFFER</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A chemical lysis buffer commonly present in commercial swab transport media that inactivates SARS-CoV-2 viral particles while preserving their genetic material, altering the molecular structure relevant to optical detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SYNTHETIC BIOFLUIDS (SALINE SOLUTION AND ARTIFICIAL SALIVA)">
      <data key="d0">SYNTHETIC BIOFLUIDS (SALINE SOLUTION AND ARTIFICIAL SALIVA)</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Synthetic fluid matrices, including saline solution and artificial saliva, used as controlled environments for viral solutions to study optical detection of SARS-CoV-2 spike protein and virus–medium interactions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 SPIKE PROTEIN IN VIRAL SOLUTIONS">
      <data key="d0">DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 SPIKE PROTEIN IN VIRAL SOLUTIONS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Experimental application of the optical technique to discern the presence of the SARS-CoV-2 spike protein in viral solutions prepared in synthetic biofluids such as saline solution and artificial saliva.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXPERIMENT 2: DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 IN NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATES">
      <data key="d0">EXPERIMENT 2: DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 IN NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">An assay run in which inactivated nasopharyngeal exudates from 72 subjects (31 PCR-positive and 41 PCR-negative) were analyzed using PLS-DA and FFNN optical pixel-based classification methods to assess SARS-CoV-2 detection under safer conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.92</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PCR TESTING OF NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATES">
      <data key="d0">PCR TESTING OF NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Reference molecular diagnostic method used to classify nasopharyngeal exudate specimens as SARS-CoV-2 positive or negative, serving as the ground truth for validating the optical detection experiment.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SPECTRAL FEATURE DESCRIPTOR OF VIRIONS">
      <data key="d0">SPECTRAL FEATURE DESCRIPTOR OF VIRIONS</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">An optical spectral feature descriptor derived from the virions that reflects molecular or structural differences, such as proteins integrated in the viral membrane or capsid, and is used as the signal for classification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QUANTITATIVE REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION PCR">
      <data key="d0">QUANTITATIVE REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION PCR</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Quantitative reverse transcription PCR (qRT-PCR) is a nucleic acid amplification method that converts viral RNA to cDNA and then amplifies target sequences by PCR to confirm positive cases and quantify viral load in nasopharyngeal exudate samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_23</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PLS-DA MODEL 2 (PER-PIXEL CLASSIFIER, TRIAL 1)">
      <data key="d0">PLS-DA MODEL 2 (PER-PIXEL CLASSIFIER, TRIAL 1)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Per-pixel partial least squares-discriminant analysis model (Model 2, Trial 1) using 12 latent variables and capturing 95.15% variance to classify pixel spectra from patient samples as SARS-CoV-2 positive or negative.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FEED-FORWARD NEURAL NETWORK (FFNN, TRIAL 1)">
      <data key="d0">FEED-FORWARD NEURAL NETWORK (FFNN, TRIAL 1)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Feed-forward neural network model (Trial 1) used to classify pixel spectra, droplets, and patients as SARS-CoV-2 positive or negative based on spectral features.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXPERIMENT 1: SYNTHETIC VIRAL MODELS IN SALINE AND ARTIFICIAL SALIVA">
      <data key="d0">EXPERIMENT 1: SYNTHETIC VIRAL MODELS IN SALINE AND ARTIFICIAL SALIVA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Assay run using synthetic SARS-CoV-2 viral models prepared in saline solution and artificial saliva, yielding more informative photoacoustic spectra than Experiment 2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXPERIMENT 2: NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATE IN INACTIVATION MEDIUM">
      <data key="d0">EXPERIMENT 2: NASOPHARYNGEAL EXUDATE IN INACTIVATION MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Assay run using nasopharyngeal exudate samples in inactivation medium, producing less informative photoacoustic spectra compared to synthetic preparations in Experiment 1.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SPECTRAL FEATURE DESCRIPTOR (SFD, 870–910 NM BAND)">
      <data key="d0">SPECTRAL FEATURE DESCRIPTOR (SFD, 870–910 NM BAND)</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Quantitative spectral feature descriptor computed from pixel spectra in the 870–910 nm band, used as a signal metric for distinguishing positive and negative samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PIXEL-LEVEL CLASSIFICATION OUTPUT (MEDIAN VALUE)">
      <data key="d0">PIXEL-LEVEL CLASSIFICATION OUTPUT (MEDIAN VALUE)</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Median value of the model output used to classify individual pixels as positive or negative, with a defined threshold indicated by a blue dashed line.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DROPLET-LEVEL CLASSIFICATION OUTPUT">
      <data key="d0">DROPLET-LEVEL CLASSIFICATION OUTPUT</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Aggregated classification output at the droplet level derived from pixel classifications, used to generate ROC curves for droplet classification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">4dc306e7-3b4b-4f0b-9c14-b13bbd895a99_chunk_25</data>
