      <data key="d0">CRISPR-BASED ASSAYS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A class of diagnostic platforms that use CRISPR effectors for nucleic acid detection, proposed to address diagnostic gaps and rapid outbreak response. | Diagnostic platforms that use CRISPR effector enzymes and guide RNAs to detect specific nucleic acid sequences, proposed as rapid, portable, decentralized tools that complement qPCR for on-site detection of pathogens like HPAI.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_29</data>
