      <data key="d0">COMPETITIVE ELISA FOR H5 HEMAGGLUTININ ANTIBODIES</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A competitive enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay developed and validated for the detection of antibodies against H5 hemagglutinin, providing a serological method to assess exposure or immune response to H5 avian influenza viruses.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="VALIDATION OF COMPETITIVE ELISA FOR H5 ANTIBODIES">
      <data key="d0">VALIDATION OF COMPETITIVE ELISA FOR H5 ANTIBODIES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">The analytical and diagnostic performance evaluation of the competitive ELISA targeting H5 hemagglutinin antibodies, including its sensitivity and specificity for detecting H5-related immune responses.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_92</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REAL-TIME COLOURIMETRIC RT-LAMP ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">REAL-TIME COLOURIMETRIC RT-LAMP ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A real-time colorimetric implementation of RT-LAMP in which amplification of viral RNA is monitored via a visible color change, enabling rapid visual detection of highly pathogenic influenza viruses.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_93</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REAL-TIME COLOURIMETRIC RT-LAMP ASSAY FOR H5 CLADE 2.3.4.4B">
      <data key="d0">REAL-TIME COLOURIMETRIC RT-LAMP ASSAY FOR H5 CLADE 2.3.4.4B</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A real-time colourimetric reverse transcription loop-mediated isothermal amplification (RT-LAMP) assay specifically designed for rapid detection of highly pathogenic H5 clade 2.3.4.4b avian influenza viruses.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_94</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HIGHLY PATHOGENIC H5 CLADE 2.3.4.4B AVIAN INFLUENZA VIRUSES">
      <data key="d0">HIGHLY PATHOGENIC H5 CLADE 2.3.4.4B AVIAN INFLUENZA VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Highly pathogenic H5 avian influenza A viruses belonging to clade 2.3.4.4b, important airborne pathogens in birds with zoonotic potential.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.92</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_94</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ON-SITE RT-RPA/CRISPR-CAS12A H5 DETECTION ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">ON-SITE RT-RPA/CRISPR-CAS12A H5 DETECTION ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An on-site, visual detection assay for H5 subtype avian influenza virus that combines reverse transcription recombinase polymerase amplification (RT-RPA) with CRISPR/Cas12a-based readout.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_94</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR/CAS12A DETECTION MODULE">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR/CAS12A DETECTION MODULE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR-based nucleic acid detection module employing Cas12a to recognize RT-RPA–amplified H5 avian influenza virus sequences and generate a visual signal.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_94</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ADVANCES IN H5N1 DETECTION TECHNIQUES REVIEW">
      <data key="d0">ADVANCES IN H5N1 DETECTION TECHNIQUES REVIEW</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A review article summarizing advances in detection techniques for the H5N1 avian influenza virus, including performance characteristics of various assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_94</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COMMUNICABLE EPISODE 09: UPDATE ON AVIAN FLU">
      <data key="d0">COMMUNICABLE EPISODE 09: UPDATE ON AVIAN FLU</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">An update on avian influenza that discusses current knowledge and context for avian flu, including relevance of diagnostic detection methods.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.55</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_94</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AVIAN FLU">
      <data key="d0">AVIAN FLU</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Avian flu refers to avian influenza viruses that cause respiratory infection in birds and can infect humans; it is the focus of the communicable disease update on avian influenza.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_95</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SMARTPHONE-BASED FLUORESCENT DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">SMARTPHONE-BASED FLUORESCENT DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A smartphone-integrated fluorescent diagnostic platform that uses the phone as a fluorescence reader for point-of-care detection of highly pathogenic H5N1 viruses.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_96</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SPR APTASENSOR FOR DETECTION OF AVIAN INFLUENZA VIRUS H5N1">
      <data key="d0">SPR APTASENSOR FOR DETECTION OF AVIAN INFLUENZA VIRUS H5N1</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A surface plasmon resonance (SPR) aptamer-based biosensor reported by Bai et al. (2012) for detecting avian influenza virus H5N1. It uses an aptamer as the biorecognition element and an SPR optical transduction mechanism for label-free virus detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_97</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SURFACE-ENHANCED RAMAN SPECTROSCOPY VIRUS DETECTION PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">SURFACE-ENHANCED RAMAN SPECTROSCOPY VIRUS DETECTION PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A biosensing platform based on surface-enhanced Raman spectroscopy (SERS) combined with machine learning, as described by Yang et al. (2022), enabling rapid and quantitative detection and classification of respiratory viruses from their Raman spectral signatures.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_97</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SURFACE PLASMON RESONANCE BIOSENSING PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">SURFACE PLASMON RESONANCE BIOSENSING PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A surface plasmon resonance (SPR) biosensor platform used for label-free detection of biomolecular interactions, here applied to the detection of H5N1 avian influenza virus and integrated with near-infrared organic photodetectors.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_103</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PSEUDOMONAS AERUGINOSA">
      <data key="d0">PSEUDOMONAS AERUGINOSA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Pseudomonas aeruginosa is an opportunistic bacterial pathogen capable of forming biofilms; while primarily associated with water and surfaces, it can be present in aerosols in clinical and environmental settings, making it relevant as a potential airborne pathogen for monitoring. | A pathogenic bacterium detected by a label-free electrochemiluminescent biosensor using phage as a specific recognition agent.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_105</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b,4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
      <data key="d6">PSEUDOMONAS AERUGINOSA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CROSS PRIMING AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">CROSS PRIMING AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Cross priming amplification is an isothermal DNA amplification method whose mechanism and optimization are characterized for use in nucleic acid amplification workflows.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_110</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REDUCED GRAPHENE OXIDE-BASED ELECTROCHEMICAL IMMUNOSENSOR INTEGRATED WITH A MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">REDUCED GRAPHENE OXIDE-BASED ELECTROCHEMICAL IMMUNOSENSOR INTEGRATED WITH A MICROFLUIDIC PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An electrochemical immunosensor developed by Singh et al. (2017) that uses reduced graphene oxide electrodes integrated with a microfluidic channel to enable label-free detection of influenza viruses via antibody–virus binding and electrochemical readout.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_111</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MAGNETIC QUANTUM DOT NANOBEAD TEST-STRIP ASSAY FOR INFLUENZA A VIRUS">
      <data key="d0">MAGNETIC QUANTUM DOT NANOBEAD TEST-STRIP ASSAY FOR INFLUENZA A VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lateral-flow-like test-strip biosensor reported by Bai et al. (2020) that employs magnetic quantum dot nanobeads for rapid enrichment and ultrasensitive detection of influenza A virus in human specimens, combining magnetic separation with fluorescent quantum dot readout.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_111</data>
      <data key="d5">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA (ARTIFICIAL NUCLEIC ACID CIRCUIT WITH ARGONAUTE PROTEIN)">
      <data key="d0">ANCA (ARTIFICIAL NUCLEIC ACID CIRCUIT WITH ARGONAUTE PROTEIN)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An Argonaute protein–based artificial nucleic acid circuit designed to perform continuous autocatalytic, cross-catalytic cleavage reactions for one-step, amplification-free, isothermal DNA detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE (CPKP)">
      <data key="d0">CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE (CPKP)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Application context in which the ANCA platform is used to detect carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae directly, without DNA extraction or amplification, across multiple sample types.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_0,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CARBAPENEM-RESISTANT BACTERIA IN HUMAN URINE AND BLOOD">
      <data key="d0">CARBAPENEM-RESISTANT BACTERIA IN HUMAN URINE AND BLOOD</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Use case where the ANCA platform detects carbapenem-resistant bacteria present in human urine and blood samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CPKP SWABBED FROM SURFACES WITH THREE-DIMENSIONAL NANOPILLAR STRUCTURE">
      <data key="d0">CPKP SWABBED FROM SURFACES WITH THREE-DIMENSIONAL NANOPILLAR STRUCTURE</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Surface swab detection scenario where CPKP collected from surfaces are directly identified using the ANCA method combined with a three-dimensional nanopillar structure.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CPKP IN RECTAL SWAB SPECIMENS FROM INFECTED PATIENTS">
      <data key="d0">CPKP IN RECTAL SWAB SPECIMENS FROM INFECTED PATIENTS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Clinical application of the ANCA method to detect CPKP in rectal swab specimens from infected patients, used to evaluate diagnostic performance.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ONE-STEP, AMPLIFICATION-FREE, ISOTHERMAL DNA DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">ONE-STEP, AMPLIFICATION-FREE, ISOTHERMAL DNA DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">An amplification-free detection regime enabled by the ANCA platform, operating under isothermal conditions in a single step without separate nucleic acid amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NO DNA EXTRACTION AND AMPLIFICATION STEPS">
      <data key="d0">NO DNA EXTRACTION AND AMPLIFICATION STEPS</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Omission of conventional DNA extraction and amplification procedures in the ANCA workflow, allowing direct detection from clinical and environmental samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SENSITIVITY 100% AND SPECIFICITY 100% FOR CPKP IN RECTAL SWABS">
      <data key="d0">SENSITIVITY 100% AND SPECIFICITY 100% FOR CPKP IN RECTAL SWABS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Reported diagnostic performance metrics of the ANCA method when applied to rectal swab specimens, showing 100% sensitivity and 100% specificity for CPKP detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_0</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION ASSAY (ISOPLEX CRE-ART)">
      <data key="d0">LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION ASSAY (ISOPLEX CRE-ART)</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A loop-mediated isothermal amplification (LAMP) assay, marketed as Isoplex CRE-ART, designed to detect common carbapenemase-encoding genes in Gram-negative bacteria, improving speed and practicality of CPE diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION COMBINED WITH LATERAL FLOW STRIP">
      <data key="d0">RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION COMBINED WITH LATERAL FLOW STRIP</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">An isothermal recombinase polymerase amplification (RPA) assay coupled with a lateral flow strip readout for rapid detection of OXA-48-like carbapenemase genes in Enterobacterales, enabling point-of-care CPE testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PURIFICATION PROCEDURES">
      <data key="d0">PURIFICATION PROCEDURES</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Additional sample preparation steps required to make complex isothermal amplification mixtures compatible with clinical samples, involving purification of nucleic acids.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ENDONUCLEASES WITH SEQUENCE-SPECIFIC CATALYTIC PROPERTIES">
      <data key="d0">ENDONUCLEASES WITH SEQUENCE-SPECIFIC CATALYTIC PROPERTIES</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">A broad class of sequence-specific endonucleases, including CRISPR-associated proteins, used as tools for nucleic acid target identification in diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.72</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR/CAS SYSTEMS">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR/CAS SYSTEMS</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">Clustered regularly interspaced short palindromic repeats and associated Cas proteins used as programmable, sequence-specific nucleases for molecular diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-MEDIATED SURFACE-ENHANCED RAMAN SCATTERING ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-MEDIATED SURFACE-ENHANCED RAMAN SCATTERING ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR-based biosensing platform that uses surface-enhanced Raman scattering (SERS) for detecting multidrug-resistant bacteria.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COLORIMETRIC CRISPR/DCAS9 ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">COLORIMETRIC CRISPR/DCAS9 ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR/dCas9-based colorimetric biosensor platform for detecting SARS-CoV-2 and drug-resistant pH1N1.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LATERAL FLOW ASSAY BASED ON ROLLING CIRCLE AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">LATERAL FLOW ASSAY BASED ON ROLLING CIRCLE AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A lateral flow assay platform that uses rolling circle amplification and capture ligand-modified oligonucleotides for nucleic acid detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.68</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR/CAS12 SYSTEM">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR/CAS12 SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR-based diagnostic platform built around Cas12-family nucleases that recognize target nucleic acids and then exhibit collateral cleavage of nearby single-stranded DNA, enabling signal generation and amplification in biosensing assays. | A CRISPR-based diagnostic platform built around Cas13-family nucleases that recognize target RNA sequences and then exhibit collateral cleavage of nearby single-stranded RNA, enabling signal generation and amplification in biosensing assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">CRISPR/CAS13 SYSTEM</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HOLMESV2">
      <data key="d0">HOLMESV2</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR-Cas12b-assisted nucleic acid detection platform used for highly sensitive detection and DNA methylation quantitation, leveraging Cas12b collateral cleavage of single-stranded DNA for signal amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_49</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-CAS12B-ASSISTED PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-CAS12B-ASSISTED PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A biosensing platform that uses the Cas12b nuclease as the CRISPR effector to detect nucleic acids and DNA methylation, relying on Cas12b collateral cleavage activity for signal generation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR/CAS12A-BASED BIOSENSOR">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR/CAS12A-BASED BIOSENSOR</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A specific and sensitive biosensor that uses Cas12a as the CRISPR effector and a cleavable DNA reporter to detect target nucleic acids via Cas12a-mediated collateral cleavage of the reporter.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR/DCAS9 COLORIMETRIC ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR/DCAS9 COLORIMETRIC ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A colorimetric CRISPR assay using catalytically dead Cas9 (dCas9) for detection of SARS-CoV-2 and drug-resistant pH1N1, producing a visible color change upon target recognition.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_48</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DRUG-RESISTANT PH1N1">
      <data key="d0">DRUG-RESISTANT PH1N1</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A drug-resistant strain of the 2009 pandemic H1N1 influenza A virus, treated as an airborne pathogen target for CRISPR/dCas9-based colorimetric detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_49</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DNA REPORTER FOR CRISPR/CAS12A">
      <data key="d0">DNA REPORTER FOR CRISPR/CAS12A</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A highly efficient single-stranded DNA reporter substrate designed for Cas12a-based biosensors; it is cleaved during Cas12a collateral activity, generating a measurable signal (e.g., fluorescence) that reports target detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COLLATERAL CLEAVAGE ACTIVITY OF CAS12">
      <data key="d0">COLLATERAL CLEAVAGE ACTIVITY OF CAS12</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The non-specific cleavage of nearby single-stranded DNA by Cas12 after target recognition, which is harnessed as an amplified reporter signal in CRISPR/Cas12-based biosensors. | The non-specific cleavage of nearby single-stranded RNA by Cas13 after target recognition, which is used as an amplified reporter signal in CRISPR/Cas13-based biosensors.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">COLLATERAL CLEAVAGE ACTIVITY OF CAS13</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STRINGENT CLEAVAGE-SITE PROXIMITY REQUIREMENT">
      <data key="d0">STRINGENT CLEAVAGE-SITE PROXIMITY REQUIREMENT</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">A practical constraint in CRISPR/Cas diagnostic applications where the preferred nuclease cleavage site must be located in close proximity to the target sequence, limiting assay design flexibility and performance.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION (LAMP)">
      <data key="d0">LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION (LAMP)</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Loop-mediated isothermal amplification (LAMP) is an isothermal nucleic acid amplification method mentioned as an alternative to PCR that can precede Argonaute-based detection, enabling amplification without thermal cycling. | An isothermal DNA amplification technique that has been integrated with thermal lysis in prior one-step assays, cited as related prior art supporting the feasibility of high-temperature, direct bacterial detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_7,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_46</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL DNA AMPLIFICATION (LAMP)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LIGATION CHAIN REACTION">
      <data key="d0">LIGATION CHAIN REACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A ligation-based amplification method coupled with Argonaute proteins to join short oligonucleotide strands and enable reporter probe cleavage for viral target detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.65</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FOODBORNE PATHOGENIC BACTERIA">
      <data key="d0">FOODBORNE PATHOGENIC BACTERIA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Foodborne pathogenic bacteria whose DNA is amplified by PCR and detected via Argonaute-triggered fluorescent cleavage; they serve as pathogenic DNA targets in the described assay.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.4</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_8,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_17</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HPV">
      <data key="d0">HPV</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Human papillomavirus, a viral pathogen detected in an Argonaute-coupled ligation chain reaction assay alongside SARS-CoV-2.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.4</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SYBR I DYE">
      <data key="d0">SYBR I DYE</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A DNA-binding fluorescent dye used to detect double-stranded DNA produced by exponential amplification following Argonaute-mediated cleavage.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA METHOD">
      <data key="d0">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Artificial nucleic acid circuit with Ago protein (ANCA), a DNA detection platform that couples a rationally designed self-reporting DNA complex with programmable sequence-guided cleavage activity of Argonaute proteins to create a single-protein, one-step assay with positive feedback and exponential signal amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_11,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_12,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_13,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_15,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_16,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_17,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_18,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_19,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_22,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_24,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_25,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_26,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_27,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_28,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_29,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_35,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_36,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_37,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_40,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ARTIFICIAL NUCLEIC ACID CIRCUIT WITH AGO PROTEIN (ANCA)">
      <data key="d0">ARTIFICIAL NUCLEIC ACID CIRCUIT WITH AGO PROTEIN (ANCA)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Implementation of the ANCA DNA detection technology that integrates an artificial nucleic acid circuit and Argonaute protein-mediated cleavage for programmable, target-specific nucleic acid detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PROGRAMMABLE SEQUENCE-GUIDED CLEAVAGE ACTIVITY OF AGO PROTEINS">
      <data key="d0">PROGRAMMABLE SEQUENCE-GUIDED CLEAVAGE ACTIVITY OF AGO PROTEINS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Use of Argonaute proteins as a programmable nuclease module within the detection system, where guide sequences direct cleavage of DNA reporters to generate signal.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SELF-REPORTING DNA COMPLEX">
      <data key="d0">SELF-REPORTING DNA COMPLEX</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Rationally designed DNA complex within ANCA that both participates in the nucleic acid circuit and reports target recognition and cleavage events, enabling intrinsic signal generation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FLUORESCENT RESULT">
      <data key="d0">FLUORESCENT RESULT</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Fluorescence signal produced upon Ago-mediated cleavage of a reporter probe or self-reporting DNA complex, used as the readout of target DNA detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="POSITIVE FEEDBACK LOOP WITH EXPONENTIAL SIGNAL AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">POSITIVE FEEDBACK LOOP WITH EXPONENTIAL SIGNAL AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Signal amplification mechanism in ANCA where Ago-mediated cleavage products feed back into the artificial nucleic acid circuit, generating exponential increase in reporter signal without traditional nucleic acid amplification enzymes.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SINGLE-STEP ANCA REACTION">
      <data key="d0">SINGLE-STEP ANCA REACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Configuration of the ANCA assay as a one-step reaction that combines target recognition, cleavage, and signal generation in a single mixture.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE (CPKP) DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE (CPKP) DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Application of the ANCA method to detect carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae as a specific DNA target.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING BACTERIA SPIKED INTO HUMAN SAMPLES">
      <data key="d0">CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING BACTERIA SPIKED INTO HUMAN SAMPLES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Validation scenario where carbapenemase-producing bacteria are added to human-derived samples to test the performance of the ANCA detection method in a complex matrix.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AGO PROTEIN-BASED LIGATION CHAIN REACTION ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">AGO PROTEIN-BASED LIGATION CHAIN REACTION ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Earlier DNA detection approach that combined ligation chain reaction with Ago proteins to join short strands, cleave a reporter probe, and generate fluorescence, but required multiple enzymes and steps.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AGO PROTEIN-BASED NON-AMPLIFICATION DETECTION METHODS">
      <data key="d0">AGO PROTEIN-BASED NON-AMPLIFICATION DETECTION METHODS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Previously reported Argonaute-based detection methods that do not use nucleic acid amplification but showed relatively poor performance compared to ANCA.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.65</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HIGH SPECIFICITY OF ANCA">
      <data key="d0">HIGH SPECIFICITY OF ANCA</data>
      <data key="d1">SPECIFICITY_PROFILE</data>
      <data key="d2">Specificity profile of the ANCA platform, arising from programmable Ago-guided recognition and the design of the artificial nucleic acid circuit.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">ANCA ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagnostic implementation of the ANCA method used in clinical and applied settings, including testing of rectal swab specimens from patients and surface/bodily fluid samples, to detect carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae (CPKP) with reported perfect clinical performance in the described study.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THREE-DIMENSIONAL (3D) NANOPILLAR ARRAY STRUCTURE">
      <data key="d0">THREE-DIMENSIONAL (3D) NANOPILLAR ARRAY STRUCTURE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A three-dimensional nanopillar array interface integrated with the ANCA method to enable direct identification of bacteria collected from surfaces such as pig skin, desks, gloves, scissors, knobs, and tweezers.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING BACTERIA">
      <data key="d0">CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING BACTERIA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A broader group of bacteria that produce carbapenemase enzymes, used as target organisms when spiked into human samples such as urine and blood to evaluate the detection capability of the ANCA method without nucleic acid amplification or extraction. | Enterobacteriaceae that produce carbapenemase enzymes, conferring resistance to carbapenem antibiotics; they are the target organisms of the Check-Direct CPE(R) assay.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING ENTEROBACTERIACEAE</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CLINICAL SENSITIVITY AND SPECIFICITY OF 100% AND 100%">
      <data key="d0">CLINICAL SENSITIVITY AND SPECIFICITY OF 100% AND 100%</data>
      <data key="d1">SPECIFICITY_PROFILE</data>
      <data key="d2">The reported diagnostic performance of the ANCA assay for detecting CPKP in rectal swab specimens, indicating 100% clinical sensitivity and 100% clinical specificity in the evaluated patient cohort.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BACTERIA SWABBED FROM SURFACES">
      <data key="d0">BACTERIA SWABBED FROM SURFACES</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A sampling step in which bacteria are collected by swabbing surfaces such as pig skin, desks, gloves, scissors, knobs, and tweezers prior to detection using the ANCA method with a 3D nanopillar array structure.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.55</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RECTAL SWAB SPECIMENS">
      <data key="d0">RECTAL SWAB SPECIMENS</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Clinical rectal swab samples collected from patients and used as input specimens for the ANCA assay to diagnose infections with carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DIAGNOSE CPKP-INFECTED PATIENTS USING RECTAL SWAB SPECIMENS">
      <data key="d0">DIAGNOSE CPKP-INFECTED PATIENTS USING RECTAL SWAB SPECIMENS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A clinical validation scenario in which the ANCA assay is applied to rectal swab specimens from patients to diagnose carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae infections, yielding 100% sensitivity and 100% specificity in the reported study.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="POINT-OF-CARE BACTERIAL TESTING">
      <data key="d0">POINT-OF-CARE BACTERIAL TESTING</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A projected application context for the ANCA assay, highlighting its potential use in point-of-care settings for early-stage bacterial infection testing to improve diagnostic accuracy and treatment outcomes.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TARGET NUCLEIC ACID">
      <data key="d0">TARGET NUCLEIC ACID</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">The nucleic acid analyte (e.g., target DNA) whose presence initiates the ANCA reaction cycle by being cleaved by Ago/G1 and Ago/G2 complexes, ultimately leading to fluorescence output.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GUIDE DNA 1 (G1)">
      <data key="d0">GUIDE DNA 1 (G1)</data>
      <data key="d1">GUIDE_RNA</data>
      <data key="d2">A designed guide DNA strand that forms an Ago/G1 complex to hybridize with and cleave the target DNA, initiating the ANCA reaction cycle. | A designed guide DNA strand that forms an Ago/G2 complex to cooperatively hybridize with and cleave the target DNA, contributing to generation of Trigger 1 (T1).</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">GUIDE DNA 2 (G2)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TRIGGER 1 (T1)">
      <data key="d0">TRIGGER 1 (T1)</data>
      <data key="d1">GUIDE_RNA</data>
      <data key="d2">A DNA trigger strand generated by cleavage of the target DNA that can also function as a guide DNA, forming an Ago/T1 complex to cleave the reporter (R) in the ANCA cycle. | A DNA trigger strand produced during reporter (R) cleavage that can also act as a guide DNA, forming an Ago/T2 complex to cleave the reporter complement (R*), regenerating T1.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">TRIGGER 2 (T2)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REPORTER (R)">
      <data key="d0">REPORTER (R)</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">A fluorophore- and quencher-labeled reporter oligonucleotide that is cleaved by the Ago/T1 complex, releasing a fluorescent output and generating Trigger 2 (T2).</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REPORTER COMPLEMENT (R*)">
      <data key="d0">REPORTER COMPLEMENT (R*)</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The complement strand to the reporter (R) that is cleaved by the Ago/T2 complex to regenerate Trigger 1 (T1), sustaining the ANCA amplification cycle.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_11</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TARGET DNA">
      <data key="d0">TARGET DNA</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">The nucleic acid analyte recognized and cleaved by Ago-guide complexes in the ANCA reaction; its presence initiates and sustains the positive feedback amplification cycle that leads to signal generation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KPC">
      <data key="d0">KPC</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A specific DNA target sequence (derived from KPC carbapenemase gene) used as the model analyte to evaluate the performance of the ANCA amplification method.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_12,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA EVALUATION WITH KPC">
      <data key="d0">ANCA EVALUATION WITH KPC</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">An experimental run of the ANCA amplification method using KPC DNA as the target, in which strong fluorescence signals were observed in the presence of all reaction components.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PAGE ANALYSIS OF R/R* STRUCTURES">
      <data key="d0">PAGE ANALYSIS OF R/R* STRUCTURES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis (PAGE) analysis used to confirm degradation or integrity of the R and R* reporter structures, validating the feasibility and amplification behavior of the ANCA method under different reaction conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA COMPARATIVE EXPERIMENTS WITHOUT R*">
      <data key="d0">ANCA COMPARATIVE EXPERIMENTS WITHOUT R*</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Comparative ANCA reaction conditions lacking R*, where Ago/G1 and Ago/G2 cleave target DNA to form Ago/T1 and cleave R to release Output and T2, but no further amplification occurs and no fluorescence signal is observed even after 400 minutes.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA">
      <data key="d0">ANCA</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">An exponential nucleic acid amplification method that uses positive feedback to amplify target DNA, involving components R, R*, G1, G2, Ago, and specific buffer conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA WITHOUT R*">
      <data key="d0">ANCA WITHOUT R*</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A variant of the ANCA amplification method in which the R* component is omitted; it cleaves target DNA and R but does not support further exponential amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA ASSAY RUN (FIG. 2C)">
      <data key="d0">ANCA ASSAY RUN (FIG. 2C)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Experimental ANCA reactions with full component set (including R and R*) monitored by time-dependent fluorescence and PAGE analysis under defined concentrations of target DNA, R, R*, G1, G2, Ago, MgCl2, NaCl, and BSA.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA ASSAY RUN WITHOUT R* (FIG. 2D)">
      <data key="d0">ANCA ASSAY RUN WITHOUT R* (FIG. 2D)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Experimental ANCA reactions lacking R* monitored by time-dependent fluorescence and PAGE analysis to demonstrate loss of exponential amplification under the same buffer and component conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUPPLEMENTARY FIG. 6 HIGH-TARGET ASSAY RUN">
      <data key="d0">SUPPLEMENTARY FIG. 6 HIGH-TARGET ASSAY RUN</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">ANCA-related experiment using a 10-fold higher concentration of target DNA and R alone, showing a slower but detectable increase in fluorescence signal over time (spectrum 5 in Supplementary Fig. 6).</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_14</data>
