    </node>
    <node id="THRESHOLD TIME (T AND T0) METRIC">
      <data key="d0">THRESHOLD TIME (T AND T0) METRIC</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Derived reporter metric where T0 is the threshold time for the no-bacteria control and T is the threshold time for test samples; the difference T0–T indicates successful detection of target bacteria.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DIRECT USE OF CULTURED BACTERIA WITHOUT DNA PURIFICATION">
      <data key="d0">DIRECT USE OF CULTURED BACTERIA WITHOUT DNA PURIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation approach in which cultured K. pneumoniae cells are added directly to the ANCA reaction mixture, omitting DNA extraction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA REACTION MIXTURE COMPOSITION">
      <data key="d0">ANCA REACTION MIXTURE COMPOSITION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Reaction buffer conditions for ANCA including 10 mM MgCl2, 75 mM NaCl, and 10 µg/mL BSA, used for direct detection of antibiotic-resistant bacteria.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INCUBATION AT 75 °C">
      <data key="d0">INCUBATION AT 75 °C</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Incubation condition for the ANCA reaction mixture containing bacteria, enabling isothermal amplification and fluorescence-based detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_19</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CPKP">
      <data key="d0">CPKP</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae, an antibiotic-resistant bacterial pathogen that is the primary detection target of the ANCA method in various sample matrices.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="K. PNEU (IMP)">
      <data key="d0">K. PNEU (IMP)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">An IMP carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae variant directly identified by the assay, representing a specific carbapenemase resistance genotype of K. pneumoniae.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="K. PNEU (WT)">
      <data key="d0">K. PNEU (WT)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Wild-type Klebsiella pneumoniae lacking carbapenemase production, used as a non-resistant comparator strain to demonstrate discrimination between WT and CPKP.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PRE-CONCENTRATION">
      <data key="d0">PRE-CONCENTRATION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A conventional sample preparation step that concentrates bacteria or nucleic acids from larger volumes prior to detection; explicitly not required in the ANCA workflow.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THERMAL LYSIS">
      <data key="d0">THERMAL LYSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Heat-induced disruption of bacterial cells, achievable within 15 minutes at temperatures above 60 °C, which underlies the ability of the ANCA method to access nucleic acids directly during the high-temperature reaction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M. SMEGMATIS">
      <data key="d0">M. SMEGMATIS</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Mycobacterium smegmatis, a bacterial species used in previous integrated thermal lysis and LAMP assays, illustrating the generalizability of high-temperature, one-step nucleic-acid detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.4</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BUFFER MATRIX">
      <data key="d0">BUFFER MATRIX</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Assay condition in which CPKP is directly detected in buffer using the ANCA method, serving as a simplified matrix for performance characterization.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="URINE MATRIX (99%)">
      <data key="d0">URINE MATRIX (99%)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Assay condition in which CPKP is directly detected in 99% urine using the ANCA method, demonstrating applicability to clinical urine samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.55</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BLOOD MATRIX (99%)">
      <data key="d0">BLOOD MATRIX (99%)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Assay condition in which CPKP is directly detected in 99% blood using the ANCA method, demonstrating applicability to near-whole-blood clinical samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.55</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DETECTION OF K. PNEUMONIAE (IMP) IN URINE">
      <data key="d0">DETECTION OF K. PNEUMONIAE (IMP) IN URINE</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Experimental runs where the IMP circuit within the ANCA method was used to detect IMP-type carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae in human urine samples, achieving detection in up to 99% of samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DETECTION OF K. PNEUMONIAE (KPC) AND K. PNEUMONIAE (IMP) IN BLOOD">
      <data key="d0">DETECTION OF K. PNEUMONIAE (KPC) AND K. PNEUMONIAE (IMP) IN BLOOD</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Experimental runs using the ANCA method to detect KPC- and IMP-type carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae in human blood samples, with detection rates of approximately 90% for KPC and 99% for IMP.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DIAGNOSIS OF ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA USING ANCA METHOD">
      <data key="d0">DIAGNOSIS OF ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA USING ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Conceptual and practical validation of the ANCA method as a diagnostic approach for antibiotic-resistant bacteria, compared to standard multi-step clinical procedures for carbapenemase-producing Enterobacteriaceae (CPE).</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STANDARD DIAGNOSTIC PROCEDURE FOR CPE">
      <data key="d0">STANDARD DIAGNOSTIC PROCEDURE FOR CPE</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">The conventional multi-step clinical workflow for detecting carbapenemase-producing Enterobacteriaceae, including sample collection, bacterial culturing, colony identification and isolation, antibiotic susceptibility testing, and determination of carbapenem resistance.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_22</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KPC CIRCUIT MIXTURE">
      <data key="d0">KPC CIRCUIT MIXTURE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">The reaction mixture containing the molecular circuit specific for KPC that is combined directly with rectal swab-immersed transport media in the ANCA assay. | ANCA nucleic acid circuit formulation specifically designed to detect IMP-type carbapenemase genes in bacterial samples and clinical matrices.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_24,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">IMP CIRCUIT MIXTURE</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RECTAL SWAB-IMMERSED TRANSPORT MEDIA PREPARATION">
      <data key="d0">RECTAL SWAB-IMMERSED TRANSPORT MEDIA PREPARATION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation step in which rectal swabs are collected using cotton swabs and each swab is placed into transport media, yielding rectal swab-immersed transport media used directly in the ANCA assay.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_24,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="T0 – T CUT-OFF CALCULATION">
      <data key="d0">T0 – T CUT-OFF CALCULATION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Statistical procedure to define the diagnostic cut-off for the ANCA assay, where the cut-off T0 – T value is set as the mean T0 – T of 80 negative samples plus five times the mean standard deviation of those negatives, resulting in a cut-off of 10.11.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BLINDED ANCA DIAGNOSTIC RUN">
      <data key="d0">BLINDED ANCA DIAGNOSTIC RUN</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Blinded diagnostic testing of clinical rectal swab samples using the ANCA method, in which 63 KPC-positive and 79 negative samples were evaluated and positive samples were labeled #81–#143 based on T0 – T values.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FLUORESCENCE MONITORING SIGNAL">
      <data key="d0">FLUORESCENCE MONITORING SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The fluorescence readout recorded during incubation of the KPC circuit mixture with rectal swab-immersed transport media, used to determine threshold time (T) and derive T0 – T values for classification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PCR DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS">
      <data key="d0">PCR DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Reference PCR-based diagnostic measurements providing Ct0 and Ct values for the same clinical samples, used to validate the ANCA assay via correlation between T0 – T and Ct0 – Ct.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CORRELATION BETWEEN T0 – T AND CT0 – CT">
      <data key="d0">CORRELATION BETWEEN T0 – T AND CT0 – CT</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Observed strong correlation between ANCA-derived T0 – T values and PCR-derived Ct0 – Ct values for KPC-positive clinical samples, supporting the accuracy of the ANCA method.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SPECIFICITY OF ANCA FOR KPC-POSITIVE SAMPLES">
      <data key="d0">SPECIFICITY OF ANCA FOR KPC-POSITIVE SAMPLES</data>
      <data key="d1">SPECIFICITY_PROFILE</data>
      <data key="d2">Specificity profile of the ANCA assay in the clinical evaluation, where only one false-positive signal (clinical sample #2) was observed when compared to hospital diagnostic results among 79 negative samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.87</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_24</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CPKP DIAGNOSIS FROM RECTAL SWAB-IMMERSED TRANSPORT MEDIA">
      <data key="d0">CPKP DIAGNOSIS FROM RECTAL SWAB-IMMERSED TRANSPORT MEDIA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Application of the ANCA method to rectal swab-immersed transport media to diagnose carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae, using threshold time (T) and cycle threshold (Ct) metrics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="T0 − T THRESHOLD METRIC">
      <data key="d0">T0 − T THRESHOLD METRIC</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The diagnostic signal defined as the difference between threshold time for pure transport media (T0) and threshold time for clinical samples (T), with a cut-off value of 10.11 used to classify samples. | Quantitative readout defined as the difference between the threshold time for a pristine rectal swab (T0) and that for a clinical or spiked sample (T), used to discriminate positive from negative samples with a cut-off value of 12.55.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">T0–T THRESHOLD METRIC</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KPC-POSITIVE CPKP SAMPLES">
      <data key="d0">KPC-POSITIVE CPKP SAMPLES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Assay runs using the ANCA method on clinical and spiked samples positive for KPC-type carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae, evaluated via T0 − T and Ct0 − Ct metrics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="K. PNEUMONIAE (KPC)-SPIKED RECTAL SWAB TRANSPORT MEDIA">
      <data key="d0">K. PNEUMONIAE (KPC)-SPIKED RECTAL SWAB TRANSPORT MEDIA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Rectal swab-immersed transport media samples artificially spiked with KPC-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae, used to generate ROC curves and estimate diagnostic performance of the ANCA method. | Rectal swab-immersed transport media samples artificially spiked with IMP-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae, used to generate ROC curves and evaluate ANCA diagnostic performance for IMP-type carbapenemase.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">K. PNEUMONIAE (IMP)-SPIKED RECTAL SWAB TRANSPORT MEDIA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KPC CPKP DIAGNOSTIC PERFORMANCE (ROC, 200 SAMPLES)">
      <data key="d0">KPC CPKP DIAGNOSTIC PERFORMANCE (ROC, 200 SAMPLES)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Validation of the ANCA method using ROC analysis on 200 rectal swab-immersed transport media samples (143 clinical and 57 K. pneumoniae (KPC)-spiked), yielding 100% clinical sensitivity and 98.7% specificity. | Validation of the ANCA method using ROC analysis on 160 rectal swab-immersed transport media samples (80 clinical and 80 K. pneumoniae (IMP)-spiked), yielding 100% clinical sensitivity and 100% specificity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">IMP CPKP DIAGNOSTIC PERFORMANCE (ROC, 160 SAMPLES)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CPKP DIAGNOSIS FROM RECTAL SWAB">
      <data key="d0">CPKP DIAGNOSIS FROM RECTAL SWAB</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Application of the ANCA method directly to rectal swab samples to diagnose carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae, using threshold time differences (T0–T) and a defined cut-off value.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="T0–T CUT-OFF VALUE 12.55">
      <data key="d0">T0–T CUT-OFF VALUE 12.55</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Empirically determined decision threshold (T0–T = 12.55) used to classify rectal swab samples as positive or negative in the ANCA assay, indicated as a dashed black line in the plots.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CLINICAL PERFORMANCE: 160-SAMPLE IMP COHORT">
      <data key="d0">CLINICAL PERFORMANCE: 160-SAMPLE IMP COHORT</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Validation of the ANCA method on 160 rectal swab–immersed transport media samples (80 clinical and 80 K. pneumoniae IMP-spiked), yielding 100% clinical sensitivity and 100% specificity. | Validation of the ANCA method on 200 rectal swab samples (143 clinical and 57 K. pneumoniae KPC-spiked), yielding 100% clinical sensitivity and 100% specificity and supporting ROC curve analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">CLINICAL PERFORMANCE: 200-SAMPLE KPC COHORT</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ROC CURVE ANALYSIS FOR ANCA">
      <data key="d0">ROC CURVE ANALYSIS FOR ANCA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Receiver operating characteristic (ROC) curve analysis generated from diagnostic results of 200 rectal swab samples to evaluate the discriminative performance of the ANCA method.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COMPARISON OF RECTAL SWAB VS TRANSPORT MEDIA SIGNALS">
      <data key="d0">COMPARISON OF RECTAL SWAB VS TRANSPORT MEDIA SIGNALS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Scatter plot comparison of T0–T values from direct rectal swab samples (red) and corresponding transport media (black) for KPC-positive clinical and mock clinical samples, assessing matrix effects and consistency.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BACTERIA-SPIKED RECTAL SWAB PANEL (57 SAMPLES)">
      <data key="d0">BACTERIA-SPIKED RECTAL SWAB PANEL (57 SAMPLES)</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Set of 57 bacteria-spiked rectal swab samples used alongside clinical samples to assess the clinical sensitivity and specificity of the ANCA method.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_26</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KFDA REFERENCE PERFORMANCE STANDARD">
      <data key="d0">KFDA REFERENCE PERFORMANCE STANDARD</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Regulatory benchmark from the Korean Food &amp; Drug Administration stating that approved molecular diagnostics have 95% clinical sensitivity and 95% specificity, motivating the need to test at least 80 positive samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.72</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_26</data>
