      <data key="d0">RECTAL SWAB IMMERSION IN TRANSPORT MEDIA (5 ML)</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation step where rectal swabs are immersed in 5 mL of transport media prior to ANCA testing, causing dilution of bacterial concentration but leaving a significant number of bacteria on the swab.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KPC-PRODUCING BACTERIA DETECTION SENSITIVITY IMPROVEMENT">
      <data key="d0">KPC-PRODUCING BACTERIA DETECTION SENSITIVITY IMPROVEMENT</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Quantitative comparison showing that direct rectal swab use in ANCA detects KPC-producing bacteria approximately 58-fold (over 50 times) more sensitively than using the corresponding transport media sample.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MOCK CLINICAL SAMPLE COMPARISON">
      <data key="d0">MOCK CLINICAL SAMPLE COMPARISON</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Validation experiments using mock clinical samples (Fig. 5j) that reproduce the higher sensitivity of direct rectal swab detection versus transport media in the ANCA method.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REPORTER SIGNAL T0–T VALUE">
      <data key="d0">REPORTER SIGNAL T0–T VALUE</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The time-differential reporter signal (T0 – T) used as the y-value in the KPC calibration curve, assumed to correlate with the logarithm of target nucleic acid concentration for quantitative comparison.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_29</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA METHOD WITH 3D NANOPILLAR SWAB">
      <data key="d0">ANCA METHOD WITH 3D NANOPILLAR SWAB</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An ANCA-based biosensing platform that uses a 3D complex nanopillar array swab to irreversibly capture bacteria from surfaces and enable on-site detection of carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae (CPKP), including KPC- and IMP-producing strains. | A biosensing platform that combines an artificial nucleic acid circuit (ANCA) with 3D nanopillar array swabs to capture antibiotic-resistant bacteria (e.g., carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae) from various surfaces and directly perform the nucleic acid circuit reaction on the swab.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.98</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">ANCA METHOD WITH 3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWAB</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KPC-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE">
      <data key="d0">KPC-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A Klebsiella pneumoniae strain producing KPC carbapenemase, used as a target antibiotic-resistant bacterium in the ANCA 3D nanopillar swab experiments. | A Klebsiella pneumoniae strain producing IMP carbapenemase, used as a target antibiotic-resistant bacterium in the ANCA 3D nanopillar swab experiments.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">IMP-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FLUORESCENCE SIGNAL IN ANCA ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">FLUORESCENCE SIGNAL IN ANCA ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The fluorescence readout generated in the ANCA circuits, which is rapidly amplified only in the presence of the correct captured carbapenemase-producing K. pneumoniae target.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SWAB-BASED SURFACE SAMPLING">
      <data key="d0">SWAB-BASED SURFACE SAMPLING</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation step in which bacteria on micropig skin, desk, glove, scissors, knob, and tweezers are collected by gently touching and rubbing with a swab before ANCA analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DIRECT SWAB-TO-TUBE TRANSFER">
      <data key="d0">DIRECT SWAB-TO-TUBE TRANSFER</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation step where the bacteria-captured swab is placed directly into a tube to initiate the ANCA reaction without additional processing.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="3D COMPLEX NANOPILLAR ARRAY STRUCTURE">
      <data key="d0">3D COMPLEX NANOPILLAR ARRAY STRUCTURE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A complex 3D nanopillar array integrated into the swab that enhances bacterial adhesion via nanotopographical interactions, enabling irreversible capture of bacteria and reducing risk of secondary infection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.88</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ON-SITE CAPTURE AND IDENTIFICATION OF CPKP">
      <data key="d0">ON-SITE CAPTURE AND IDENTIFICATION OF CPKP</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Demonstrated feasibility that the ANCA method combined with the 3D nanopillar swab can capture and identify carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae directly from contaminated surfaces.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_31</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWAB SURFACE SAMPLING">
      <data key="d0">3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWAB SURFACE SAMPLING</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation step in which 3D nanopillar array swabs are used to capture carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae from micropig skin, desk, scissors, glove, knob, and tweezers prior to the ANCA reaction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ARTIFICIAL NUCLEIC ACID CIRCUIT (ANCA)">
      <data key="d0">ARTIFICIAL NUCLEIC ACID CIRCUIT (ANCA)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">An artificial nucleic acid circuit that leverages the target recognition and cleavage activities of Argonaute (Ago) proteins to form a programmable biochemical reaction network for biosensing applications.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KPC NUCLEIC ACID CIRCUIT">
      <data key="d0">KPC NUCLEIC ACID CIRCUIT</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A variant of the ANCA nucleic acid circuit designed to detect KPC-type carbapenemase genes, characterized by measurement of threshold time (T) and comparison to a negative control threshold time (T0). | A variant of the ANCA nucleic acid circuit designed to detect IMP-type carbapenemase genes, characterized by measurement of threshold time (T) and comparison to a negative control threshold time (T0).</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">IMP NUCLEIC ACID CIRCUIT</data>
    </node>
    <node id="T0–T THRESHOLD TIME READOUT">
      <data key="d0">T0–T THRESHOLD TIME READOUT</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">The reporter signal defined as the difference between the threshold time of the negative control (T0, absence of bacteria) and the threshold time of the test sample (T, presence of bacteria), plotted as a function of contaminated surface for KPC and IMP circuits.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.84</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TRIPLICATE INDEPENDENT EXPERIMENTS (N=3) WITH STANDARD DEVIATION">
      <data key="d0">TRIPLICATE INDEPENDENT EXPERIMENTS (N=3) WITH STANDARD DEVIATION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Assay validation procedure in which capture and detection of carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae using KPC and IMP circuits were independently replicated three times, with data reported as mean ± standard deviation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_32</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CEPHEID XPERT CARBA-R ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">CEPHEID XPERT CARBA-R ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">PCR-based hospital diagnostic platform used to identify carbapenemase-producing Enterobacteriaceae (CPE), requiring specialized equipment for nucleic acid purification and thermal cycling.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PORTABLE ISOTHERMAL NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION DEVICE">
      <data key="d0">PORTABLE ISOTHERMAL NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION DEVICE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Commercially available portable device that performs isothermal nucleic acid amplification and was used to evaluate the ANCA method in on-site settings.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION IN ANCA">
      <data key="d0">ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION IN ANCA</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Isothermal nucleic acid amplification process used by the ANCA method, enabling all reactions to occur at a constant temperature without PCR thermal cycling.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PCR IN CEPHEID XPERT CARBA-R ASSAY">
      <data key="d0">PCR IN CEPHEID XPERT CARBA-R ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) amplification used in the Cepheid Xpert Carba-R assay for detecting carbapenemase genes in CPE.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RECTAL SWAB AND TRANSPORT MEDIA DIRECT USE">
      <data key="d0">RECTAL SWAB AND TRANSPORT MEDIA DIRECT USE</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation approach in the ANCA method where rectal swabs and transport media are used directly without nucleic acid purification, minimizing nucleic acid loss.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REPEATED LYSIS AND WASHING FOR NUCLEIC ACID EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d0">REPEATED LYSIS AND WASHING FOR NUCLEIC ACID EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Conventional nucleic acid extraction procedure involving repeated lysis and washing steps, which can lead to loss of nucleic acids prior to amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA CLINICAL EVALUATION WITH 20 SAMPLES">
      <data key="d0">ANCA CLINICAL EVALUATION WITH 20 SAMPLES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Validation study where the ANCA method, run on a portable isothermal device, tested 20 clinical samples (10 KPC-positive and 10 negative) and accurately diagnosed all samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWAB">
      <data key="d0">3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWAB</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Swab device incorporating 3D nanopillar nanostructures designed to irreversibly capture harmful bacteria, enhancing the efficiency and safety of CPKP detection when integrated with the ANCA method.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_35,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CPE DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">CPE DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Detection of carbapenemase-producing Enterobacteriaceae as the primary diagnostic target of the ANCA method and the Cepheid Xpert Carba-R assay. | Detection of carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae, whose efficiency is improved by integrating the ANCA method with the 3D nanopillar array swab.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_35</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">CPKP DETECTION</data>
    </node>
    <node id="3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWAB WITH POLYANILINE NANOFIBERS">
      <data key="d0">3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWAB WITH POLYANILINE NANOFIBERS</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A 3D nanopillar array-based swab functionalized with polyaniline nanofibers that irreversibly captures harmful bacteria with high efficiency (quantitative range 10^2–10^7 CFU/mL and up to 75 bacteria/100 μm^2), enhancing sensitivity and safety of bacterial diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_36</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DIRECT DETECTION OF CPKP FROM PATIENT-COLLECTED RECTAL SWABS">
      <data key="d0">DIRECT DETECTION OF CPKP FROM PATIENT-COLLECTED RECTAL SWABS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Application of the ANCA method directly to patient-collected rectal swab samples for detecting carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae, without intermediate culture steps.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_36</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DETECTION OF CPKP FROM SWAB-IMMERSED TRANSPORT MEDIA">
      <data key="d0">DETECTION OF CPKP FROM SWAB-IMMERSED TRANSPORT MEDIA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Use of the ANCA method on transport media in which rectal swabs have been immersed, serving as a comparative diagnostic workflow for CPKP detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_36</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PROSPECTIVE ANCA + 3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWAB WORKFLOW">
      <data key="d0">PROSPECTIVE ANCA + 3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWAB WORKFLOW</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Envisioned diagnostic workflow where clinical samples are collected using 3D nanopillar array swabs and directly analyzed by the ANCA method to diagnose CPKP and other antibiotic-resistant bacteria while minimizing contamination and secondary infection risk.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_36</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EVALUATION OF ANCA WITH 3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWABS IN COLLABORATION WITH PHYSICIANS">
      <data key="d0">EVALUATION OF ANCA WITH 3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWABS IN COLLABORATION WITH PHYSICIANS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Planned clinical evaluation and implementation study of the combined ANCA method and 3D nanopillar array swab platform, conducted in close collaboration with physicians to assess diagnostic performance and clinical utility.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_36</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWABS">
      <data key="d0">3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWABS</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">A sample collection and preparation approach using swabs with a 3D nanopillar array surface to enhance capture and presentation of clinical specimens for the ANCA method.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CLINICAL EVALUATION OF ANCA WITH 3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWABS">
      <data key="d0">CLINICAL EVALUATION OF ANCA WITH 3D NANOPILLAR ARRAY SWABS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Planned careful evaluation of the ANCA method used in conjunction with 3D nanopillar array swabs in real-world clinical settings, involving close collaboration with physicians.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LIMIT OF DETECTION OF ANCA">
      <data key="d0">LIMIT OF DETECTION OF ANCA</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">The relatively low limit of detection (LOD) of the ANCA method, attributed to its early stage of experimental optimization compared with established pathogen detection modalities.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CLINICAL CT VALUES IN THIS STUDY">
      <data key="d0">CLINICAL CT VALUES IN THIS STUDY</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">The cycle threshold (Ct) values measured for clinical samples using the ANCA method in the present investigation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CLINICAL CT VALUES IN CONTEMPORARY LITERATURE">
      <data key="d0">CLINICAL CT VALUES IN CONTEMPORARY LITERATURE</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Ct values reported in contemporary clinical literature for assays such as Check-Direct CPE and Xpert Carba-R used on rectal or perirectal swabs for carbapenemase-producing organisms.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ROBUSTNESS OF ANCA FOR CLINICAL APPLICATIONS">
      <data key="d0">ROBUSTNESS OF ANCA FOR CLINICAL APPLICATIONS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Evidence-based assessment that the ANCA technique is adequately robust for clinical use, supported by congruence between its clinical Ct values and those reported in contemporary clinical literature.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REACTION TIME OF ANCA">
      <data key="d0">REACTION TIME OF ANCA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">The relatively long reaction time of the ANCA method compared to other technologies, identified as a drawback of the platform.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.65</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_37</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA TECHNIQUE">
      <data key="d0">ANCA TECHNIQUE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A nucleic-acid detection platform that uses Ago protein–mediated cleavage and circuit-based amplification for clinical applications, characterized by relatively long reaction times and sensitivity variations between circuits.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.96</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="APO-FORM AGO PROTEIN">
      <data key="d0">APO-FORM AGO PROTEIN</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">The guide-free (apo) form of the Ago protein that exhibits non-specific dsDNA cleavage activity, necessitating lower Ago concentrations and contributing to longer reaction times in the ANCA platform.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.82</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INACTIVATED CAS PROTEINS">
      <data key="d0">INACTIVATED CAS PROTEINS</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">Engineered Cas nucleases with reduced or abolished cleavage activity, cited as an example of protein engineering advances that motivate expectations for engineered Ago variants with inhibited apo-form activity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CAS9 NUCLEASES THAT CUT ONLY ONE STRAND">
      <data key="d0">CAS9 NUCLEASES THAT CUT ONLY ONE STRAND</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">Cas9 variants engineered to nick a single DNA strand instead of producing double-strand breaks, illustrating domain-level engineering of Cas9 nuclease activity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.68</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INACTIVATED CAS9 NUCLEASES">
      <data key="d0">INACTIVATED CAS9 NUCLEASES</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">Catalytically inactive Cas9 variants with inhibited cleavage activity, used as a reference point for potential engineering of Ago proteins with controlled or suppressed apo-form activity.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.68</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ENTROPY-DRIVEN CIRCUITRY">
      <data key="d0">ENTROPY-DRIVEN CIRCUITRY</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">An amplification-type nucleic acid circuit proposed for integration into the ANCA platform to accelerate reaction rates and improve overall detection kinetics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.74</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CATALYTIC HAIRPIN ASSEMBLY">
      <data key="d0">CATALYTIC HAIRPIN ASSEMBLY</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">A DNA-based amplification circuit (CHA) suggested as an add-on to the ANCA technique to increase reaction rate and enhance signal amplification without changing the core Ago-based mechanism.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.78</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NEB GUIDE TO DNA DESIGN">
      <data key="d0">NEB GUIDE TO DNA DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">A design guideline resource for DNA used in the ANCA circuits; its currently high variability is cited as a source of inconsistent sensitivity across different ANCA circuits.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA CIRCUIT SENSITIVITY VALUES">
      <data key="d0">ANCA CIRCUIT SENSITIVITY VALUES</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">The observed sensitivity metrics for individual ANCA circuits, which vary substantially, likely due to variability in the current NEB DNA design guidance.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.72</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DETECTION OF DIFFERENT TARGET NUCLEIC ACIDS WITH CONSISTENT EFFICIENCY">
      <data key="d0">DETECTION OF DIFFERENT TARGET NUCLEIC ACIDS WITH CONSISTENT EFFICIENCY</data>
      <data key="d1">LIMIT_OF_DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d2">The anticipated future performance state of the ANCA platform, where accumulated design data enables more uniform sensitivity and efficiency across diverse nucleic acid targets.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.65</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CLINICAL APPLICATIONS OF ANCA">
      <data key="d0">CLINICAL APPLICATIONS OF ANCA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">The envisioned use of the ANCA biosensor platform in clinical diagnostic settings, supported by its robustness despite current drawbacks in reaction time and sensitivity variability.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.76</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KPC TARGET DNA">
      <data key="d0">KPC TARGET DNA</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">Target DNA corresponding to KPC (Klebsiella pneumoniae carbapenemase) used as the analyte in the ANCA assay; treated here as the pathogen-associated nucleic acid target.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TTAGO">
      <data key="d0">TTAGO</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">Thermus thermophilus Argonaute protein used as the programmable nuclease in the ANCA assay, functionally analogous to a CRISPR effector for target DNA cleavage.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="G1 AND G2 OLIGONUCLEOTIDES">
      <data key="d0">G1 AND G2 OLIGONUCLEOTIDES</data>
      <data key="d1">GUIDE_RNA</data>
      <data key="d2">Two guide oligonucleotides (G1 and G2) that program TtAgo to recognize and cleave the KPC target DNA in the ANCA assay.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="R AND R* REPORTERS">
      <data key="d0">R AND R* REPORTERS</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Reporter oligonucleotides (R and R*) whose fluorescence signal is monitored to quantify target DNA cleavage in the ANCA assay; R* is omitted in a control reaction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA FLUORESCENCE READOUT">
      <data key="d0">ANCA FLUORESCENCE READOUT</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Fluorescence signal measured at 1-minute intervals on a CFX Opus 96 RT-PCR system to monitor the progress of the ANCA reaction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HUMAN URINE AND BLOOD SAMPLE PREPARATION">
      <data key="d0">HUMAN URINE AND BLOOD SAMPLE PREPARATION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Procurement and preparation of human urine and blood samples from Innovative Research for use as biological matrices in the ANCA assay.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA ASSAY RUN AT 75°C">
      <data key="d0">ANCA ASSAY RUN AT 75°C</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Operational conditions of the ANCA reaction, including incubation at 75°C with defined buffer, TtAgo, guides (G1, G2), reporters (R, R*), NaCl, and BSA, monitored on a CFX Opus 96 RT-PCR system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA PAGE ANALYSIS RUN">
      <data key="d0">ANCA PAGE ANALYSIS RUN</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">ANCA reaction mixture incubated at 75°C for 70 minutes for subsequent PAGE analysis of cleavage products.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA CONTROL WITHOUT R*">
      <data key="d0">ANCA CONTROL WITHOUT R*</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Control ANCA reaction performed under identical conditions but lacking the R* reporter to assess dependence of signal on the reporter strand.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ETHICAL AND IRB APPROVAL">
      <data key="d0">ETHICAL AND IRB APPROVAL</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Institutional Review Board approval and compliance with ethical regulations for the use of human-derived samples in the ANCA study.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PAGE ANALYSIS OF ANCA REACTION PRODUCT">
      <data key="d0">PAGE ANALYSIS OF ANCA REACTION PRODUCT</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis run in which ANCA reaction products with target DNA are separated on a 15% polyacrylamide gel, stained with Gel-Red, and imaged using a Geldoc Go system.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DIRECT DETECTION OF ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA USING ANCA">
      <data key="d0">DIRECT DETECTION OF ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA USING ANCA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Application of the ANCA method directly to clinical isolates of antibiotic-resistant bacteria to detect carbapenemase genes such as KPC and IMP. | Assay run where 2 µL of 10^5 cells/mL bacterial suspension is combined with 18 µL of ANCA reaction components and incubated according to the ANCA protocol for direct detection of antibiotic-resistant bacteria.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">DIRECT ANCA DETECTION OF ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA IN BUFFER</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QRT-PCR CONFIRMATION OF CARBAPENEMASE GENES">
      <data key="d0">QRT-PCR CONFIRMATION OF CARBAPENEMASE GENES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">qRT-PCR assay using gene-specific primers and SYBR Green to confirm the presence of CPKP-induced carbapenemase genes (KPC, IMP, VIM, NDM, OXA-48) in antibiotic-resistant bacteria.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PREPARATION OF BACTERIAL SUSPENSIONS FROM CLINICAL ISOLATES">
      <data key="d0">PREPARATION OF BACTERIAL SUSPENSIONS FROM CLINICAL ISOLATES</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Culturing clinical bacterial isolates on LB agar at 37 °C for 16 h, harvesting, resuspending in PBS, and measuring OD600 to estimate bacterial counts.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DNA EXTRACTION FROM ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA">
      <data key="d0">DNA EXTRACTION FROM ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Extraction of DNA from antibiotic-resistant bacterial isolates using the Monarch Plasmid Miniprep Kit prior to qRT-PCR analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PCR AMPLIFICATION IN QRT-PCR VALIDATION">
      <data key="d0">PCR AMPLIFICATION IN QRT-PCR VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">Thermal cycling protocol of 49 cycles (95 °C denaturation, 55 °C annealing, 72 °C extension) using TOPsimple preMIX-nTaq and SYBR Green I for qRT-PCR detection of carbapenemase genes.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SYBR GREEN I FLUORESCENCE SIGNAL">
      <data key="d0">SYBR GREEN I FLUORESCENCE SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Fluorescent signal generated by SYBR Green I dye during qRT-PCR, monitored to quantify amplification of carbapenemase gene targets.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_40,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GEL-RED STAINED DNA BANDS">
      <data key="d0">GEL-RED STAINED DNA BANDS</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Fluorescent DNA bands visualized after Gel-Red staining of polyacrylamide gels containing ANCA reaction products.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="VIM CIRCUIT MIXTURE">
      <data key="d0">VIM CIRCUIT MIXTURE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">ANCA nucleic acid circuit formulation specifically designed to detect VIM-type carbapenemase genes in bacterial samples. | ANCA nucleic acid circuit formulation specifically designed to detect NDM-type carbapenemase genes in bacterial samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">NDM CIRCUIT MIXTURE</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OXA-48 CIRCUIT MIXTURE">
      <data key="d0">OXA-48 CIRCUIT MIXTURE</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">ANCA nucleic acid circuit formulation specifically designed to detect OXA-48-type carbapenemase genes in bacterial samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QRT-PCR CONFIRMATION OF CPKP-INDUCED GENE">
      <data key="d0">QRT-PCR CONFIRMATION OF CPKP-INDUCED GENE</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">qRT-PCR assay performed on bacteria-spiked human samples to confirm the presence of carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae (CPKP)-induced gene prior to applying the ANCA method.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PCR THERMAL CYCLING PROTOCOL">
      <data key="d0">PCR THERMAL CYCLING PROTOCOL</data>
      <data key="d1">AMPLIFICATION_METHOD</data>
      <data key="d2">PCR protocol consisting of 49 cycles of denaturation at 95 °C for 30 s, annealing at 55 °C for 1 min, and extension at 72 °C for 1 min, used for amplification in qRT-PCR validation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CFX OPUS 96 RT-PCR SYSTEM FLUORESCENCE READOUT">
      <data key="d0">CFX OPUS 96 RT-PCR SYSTEM FLUORESCENCE READOUT</data>
      <data key="d1">REPORTER_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d2">Real-time fluorescence signal monitored at each extension step of PCR using the CFX Opus 96 RT-PCR system to track amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PREPARATION OF 99% BACTERIA-SPIKED HUMAN SAMPLE">
      <data key="d0">PREPARATION OF 99% BACTERIA-SPIKED HUMAN SAMPLE</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation step where 1 µL of bacteria at 10^7 cells/mL is mixed with 99 µL of human urine or blood to generate a 99% bacteria-spiked clinical sample. | Sample preparation step where 10 µL of bacteria at 10^6 cells/mL is mixed with 90 µL of human urine or blood to generate a 90% bacteria-spiked clinical sample.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">PREPARATION OF 90% BACTERIA-SPIKED HUMAN SAMPLE</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DNA EXTRACTION WITH MONARCH PLASMID MINIPREP KIT">
      <data key="d0">DNA EXTRACTION WITH MONARCH PLASMID MINIPREP KIT</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">DNA extraction step using the Monarch Plasmid Miniprep Kit to isolate bacterial DNA from bacteria-spiked human samples prior to qRT-PCR validation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA DETECTION OF BACTERIA IN SPIKED URINE AND BLOOD">
      <data key="d0">ANCA DETECTION OF BACTERIA IN SPIKED URINE AND BLOOD</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Assay run where bacteria-spiked human urine and blood samples are tested with ANCA circuit mixtures (KPC, IMP, and others) to evaluate detection performance in clinical matrices.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AUTOFLUORESCENCE ROBUSTNESS TEST WITH KPC CIRCUIT">
      <data key="d0">AUTOFLUORESCENCE ROBUSTNESS TEST WITH KPC CIRCUIT</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Control assay run where distilled water, urine, or blood (2 µL) is combined with KPC circuit mixture (18 µL) without target DNA to assess robustness of the ANCA system against autofluorescence from human samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CLINICAL DIAGNOSIS OF ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA USING ANCA">
      <data key="d0">CLINICAL DIAGNOSIS OF ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA USING ANCA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Clinical diagnostic application of the ANCA method on 143 rectal swab samples (63 KPC-positive and 80 negative) obtained from Gyeongsang National University College of Medicine.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.95</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QRT-PCR ASSAY FOR KPC">
      <data key="d0">QRT-PCR ASSAY FOR KPC</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">Quantitative real-time PCR assay using KPC gene-specific primers, TOPsimple preMIX-nTaq, and SYBR Green I dye on the CFX Opus Real-Time System to detect KPC genes from DNA extracted from rectal swab-immersed transport media.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KPC GENE">
      <data key="d0">KPC GENE</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">Carbapenemase-encoding KPC gene used as the molecular target for detecting KPC-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae in clinical and mock rectal swab samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="IMP GENE">
      <data key="d0">IMP GENE</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">Carbapenemase-encoding IMP gene used as the molecular target for detecting IMP-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae in mock rectal swab samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RECTAL SWAB COLLECTION AND STORAGE">
      <data key="d0">RECTAL SWAB COLLECTION AND STORAGE</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Collection of rectal swab samples from patients using cotton swabs, immersion in 5 mL transport media, and storage at −80 °C until analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DNA EXTRACTION FROM RECTAL SWAB-IMMERSED TRANSPORT MEDIA">
      <data key="d0">DNA EXTRACTION FROM RECTAL SWAB-IMMERSED TRANSPORT MEDIA</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Extraction of DNA from rectal swab-immersed transport media using the AccuPrep Stool DNA Extraction Kit prior to qRT-PCR analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MOCK CLINICAL SAMPLE PREPARATION FOR K. PNEUMONIAE (KPC)">
      <data key="d0">MOCK CLINICAL SAMPLE PREPARATION FOR K. PNEUMONIAE (KPC)</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Preparation of mock clinical samples by selecting hospital-negative rectal swabs in transport media, spraying them with KPC-producing K. pneumoniae at various concentrations, and immersing them in transport media. | Preparation of mock clinical samples by collecting hospital-negative rectal swab-immersed transport media (500 μL each) and adding IMP-producing K. pneumoniae at various concentrations.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">MOCK CLINICAL SAMPLE PREPARATION FOR K. PNEUMONIAE (IMP)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA ASSAY RUN ON CLINICAL RECTAL SWAB SAMPLES">
      <data key="d0">ANCA ASSAY RUN ON CLINICAL RECTAL SWAB SAMPLES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Execution of the ANCA method on clinical rectal swab-immersed transport media (2 μL sample plus 18 μL ANCA reaction components) to diagnose antibiotic-resistant bacteria, including KPC-producing strains.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA ASSAY RUN ON MOCK KPC SAMPLES">
      <data key="d0">ANCA ASSAY RUN ON MOCK KPC SAMPLES</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">Execution of the ANCA method on mock rectal swab-immersed transport media spiked with KPC-producing K. pneumoniae at various concentrations. | Execution of the ANCA method on mock rectal swab-immersed transport media spiked with IMP-producing K. pneumoniae at various concentrations.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
      <data key="d6">ANCA ASSAY RUN ON MOCK IMP SAMPLES</data>
    </node>
    <node id="QRT-PCR ASSAY RUN FOR KPC DETECTION">
      <data key="d0">QRT-PCR ASSAY RUN FOR KPC DETECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">qRT-PCR run using extracted DNA (2 μL) and 18 μL PCR reaction mixture containing KPC gene-specific primers, TOPsimple preMIX-nTaq, and SYBR Green I dye on the CFX Opus Real-Time System to obtain Ct values.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA METHOD ASSAY RUN WITH RECTAL SWAB-IMMERSED WATER">
      <data key="d0">ANCA METHOD ASSAY RUN WITH RECTAL SWAB-IMMERSED WATER</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">An ANCA-based nucleic acid amplification assay run in which 2 μL of rectal swab-immersed distilled water is combined with 18 μL of ANCA reaction components and incubated following a defined protocol for diagnosing antibiotic-resistant bacteria.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA METHOD ASSAY RUN WITH TRANSPORT MEDIA">
      <data key="d0">ANCA METHOD ASSAY RUN WITH TRANSPORT MEDIA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">An ANCA-based nucleic acid amplification assay run in which 2 μL of rectal swab-immersed transport medium is combined with ANCA reaction components and incubated according to the same protocol, performed on twenty rectal swab samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SAMPLE PREPARATION: RECTAL SWAB IMMERSION IN DISTILLED WATER">
      <data key="d0">SAMPLE PREPARATION: RECTAL SWAB IMMERSION IN DISTILLED WATER</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation step where rectal swabs from patients and mock rectal swabs containing K. pneumoniae (IMP) are immersed in 500 μL of distilled water prior to ANCA-based nucleic acid amplification.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SAMPLE PREPARATION: RECTAL SWAB-IMMERSED TRANSPORT MEDIA">
      <data key="d0">SAMPLE PREPARATION: RECTAL SWAB-IMMERSED TRANSPORT MEDIA</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Sample preparation step in which rectal swabs are immersed in transport medium, and 2 μL aliquots of this medium are used as input for the ANCA reaction.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.75</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PORTABLE ISOTHERMAL NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION DEVICE (REVOSKETCH, DAEJEON, KOREA)">
      <data key="d0">PORTABLE ISOTHERMAL NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION DEVICE (REVOSKETCH, DAEJEON, KOREA)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A portable isothermal nucleic acid amplification device manufactured by Revosketch (Daejeon, Korea), used to perform ANCA-based amplification reactions for detecting antibiotic-resistant bacteria from rectal swab samples.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DIAGNOSIS OF ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA FROM RECTAL SWABS">
      <data key="d0">DIAGNOSIS OF ANTIBIOTIC-RESISTANT BACTERIA FROM RECTAL SWABS</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Application and evaluation of the ANCA method using rectal swab samples, including patient-derived and mock K. pneumoniae (IMP) swabs, to diagnose antibiotic-resistant bacteria.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_43</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="3D NANOPILLAR SWAB BIOSENSOR PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">3D NANOPILLAR SWAB BIOSENSOR PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A 3D nanostructured swab constructed from polyurethane/NOA 63 nanopillars coated with Ti/Au nanonetworks and fixed onto a 3D-printed backbone, used to capture bacteria from various contaminated surfaces for downstream ANCA-based detection.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SAMPLE COLLECTION FROM CONTAMINATED SURFACES">
      <data key="d0">SAMPLE COLLECTION FROM CONTAMINATED SURFACES</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Pre-analytical step in which bacteria are collected from contaminated surfaces (micropig Franz cell membrane, desk, scissors, glove, knob, tweezers) by touching and rubbing with the 3D nanopillar swab.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA REACTION MIXTURE PREPARATION">
      <data key="d0">ANCA REACTION MIXTURE PREPARATION</data>
      <data key="d1">SAMPLE_PREP_STEP</data>
      <data key="d2">Preparation step where a piece of bacteria-captured 3D nanopillar swab is mixed with 18 μL of ANCA reaction components and 2 μL of distilled water to a final volume of 20 μL prior to incubation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ANCA ASSAY RUN">
      <data key="d0">ANCA ASSAY RUN</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_RUN</data>
      <data key="d2">The ANCA-based molecular diagnostic assay performed on the mixture containing bacteria captured by the 3D nanopillar swab, following an incubation protocol to detect bacterial presence.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.85</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ASSAY VALIDATION PER KFDA CLINICAL PERFORMANCE CRITERIA">
      <data key="d0">ASSAY VALIDATION PER KFDA CLINICAL PERFORMANCE CRITERIA</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Validation of the ANCA-based diagnostic method according to Korean Food &amp; Drug Administration requirements, including testing at least 80 positive clinical samples to meet 95% clinical sensitivity and 95% clinical specificity benchmarks.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="NCBI REFERENCE SEQUENCE DATABASE–GUIDED PRIMER/PROBE DESIGN">
      <data key="d0">NCBI REFERENCE SEQUENCE DATABASE–GUIDED PRIMER/PROBE DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d1">ASSAY_VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d2">Use of the NCBI Reference Sequence Database to design primers and probes for the molecular diagnostic assay, ensuring sequence specificity and coverage of target bacterial genomes.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KFDA CLINICAL SENSITIVITY AND SPECIFICITY BENCHMARK">
      <data key="d0">KFDA CLINICAL SENSITIVITY AND SPECIFICITY BENCHMARK</data>
      <data key="d1">SPECIFICITY_PROFILE</data>
      <data key="d2">Regulatory performance benchmark from the Korean Food &amp; Drug Administration specifying 95% clinical sensitivity and 95% clinical specificity for approved molecular diagnostics.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_44</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PH1N1 (DRUG-RESISTANT)">
      <data key="d0">PH1N1 (DRUG-RESISTANT)</data>
      <data key="d1">AIRBORNE_PATHOGEN</data>
      <data key="d2">A drug-resistant pandemic H1N1 influenza virus strain that is targeted alongside SARS-CoV-2 in a CRISPR/dCas9 colorimetric detection assay.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_48</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COLORIMETRIC DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 AND DRUG-RESISTANT PH1N1 USING CRISPR/DCAS9">
      <data key="d0">COLORIMETRIC DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 AND DRUG-RESISTANT PH1N1 USING CRISPR/DCAS9</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR/dCas9-based colorimetric nucleic acid detection assay described by Moon et al. (2020) for detecting SARS-CoV-2 and drug-resistant pH1N1, using dCas9-mediated target binding to generate a visible color change.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_49</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-CAS12B">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-CAS12B</data>
      <data key="d1">CAS_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d2">A Cas12b effector enzyme used in the HOLMESv2 platform to mediate nucleic acid detection and DNA methylation quantitation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_49,8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_50</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HOLMESV2 CRISPR-CAS12B PLATFORM">
      <data key="d0">HOLMESV2 CRISPR-CAS12B PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A CRISPR-Cas12b-assisted biosensor platform (HOLMESv2) for nucleic acid detection and DNA methylation quantitation, representing a specific implementation of CRISPR-based diagnostic assays.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_50</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-CAS12A-BASED DNA REPORTER BIOSENSOR">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-CAS12A-BASED DNA REPORTER BIOSENSOR</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A specific and sensitive biosensor that uses a highly efficient DNA reporter in combination with CRISPR/Cas12a to detect target nucleic acids via collateral cleavage of single-stranded DNA.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_50</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CRISPR-BASED DIAGNOSTICS (GENERAL)">
      <data key="d0">CRISPR-BASED DIAGNOSTICS (GENERAL)</data>
      <data key="d1">BIOSENSOR_PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d2">A broad class of diagnostic biosensor platforms that employ CRISPR effector enzymes (e.g., Cas12, Cas13 variants) for nucleic acid detection across diverse applications.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_50</data>
      <data key="d5">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </node>
