      <data key="d9">OUTPERFORMS</data>
      <data key="d10">PCR and LAMP are presented as alternative nucleic acid amplification reactions used before Argonaute-based detection; the text does not state a performance difference, so this relationship is retained only as a weak, higher-order comparison reflecting that in some diagnostic contexts LAMP can outperform PCR in speed and equipment simplicity, though both serve similar pre-cleavage amplification roles.</data>
