      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">The CRISPR–Cas12-based detection of SARS-CoV-2 assay employs Cas12 as the CRISPR effector nuclease to mediate target recognition and collateral cleavage for signal generation. | The CRISPR–Cas12-based detection platform employs Cas12 as its core CRISPR effector nuclease to generate a detectable signal upon recognition of SARS-CoV-2 RNA. | The CRISPR–Cas12-based detection platform employs the Cas12 nuclease as its core effector enzyme to recognize SARS-CoV-2 target sequences and generate a reporter signal. | The CRISPR–Cas12-based detection platform employs Cas12 as its core CRISPR effector enzyme to generate a detectable signal via collateral cleavage.</data>
      <data key="d11">1.0</data>
