      <data key="d10">The CRISPR–Cas12-based detection of SARS-CoV-2 assay is specifically designed to detect SARS-CoV-2 genetic material for diagnostic identification of this viral pathogen. | The CRISPR–Cas12-based detection platform is designed to detect SARS-CoV-2 RNA, enabling identification of this airborne pathogen in clinical samples. | The CRISPR–Cas12-based detection platform is explicitly designed to detect SARS-CoV-2 nucleic acids for molecular diagnosis of the viral pathogen. | The CRISPR–Cas12-based detection platform is designed to detect SARS-CoV-2 nucleic acids, enabling identification of this airborne pathogen from clinical samples. | The CRISPR–Cas12-based detection platform developed by Broughton et al. is designed to detect SARS-CoV-2 viral nucleic acids for COVID-19 diagnosis.</data>
