      <data key="d7">CT CHEST SCAN</data>
      <data key="d8">CT CHEST SCAN SPECIFICITY PROFILE</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
      <data key="d10">CT chest scans for COVID-19 diagnosis have a low specificity profile of about 25%, reflecting difficulty in distinguishing COVID-19 from other viral pneumonias. | CT chest scans for COVID-19 diagnosis exhibit relatively high sensitivity, reported in the range of 86%–98% for detecting lung abnormalities associated with infection.</data>
