      <data key="d10">The detection assay relies on the Cas12a nuclease, whose target-activated indiscriminate single-stranded DNase activity generates a detectable signal upon binding to the intended nucleic acid target. | The CRISPR-Cas12a-assisted nucleic acid detection assay employs Cas12a as its core CRISPR effector nuclease to recognize target nucleic acids and generate a detectable signal. | The CRISPR-Cas12a-assisted nucleic acid detection platform uses the Cas12a nuclease variant as its core CRISPR enzyme to mediate target recognition and signal generation. | The CRISPR-Cas12a-assisted nucleic acid detection platform employs Cas12a as its core CRISPR effector nuclease, using its guide RNA–directed target recognition and collateral ssDNA cleavage to convert nucleic acid binding into a measurable signal. | The CRISPR-Cas12a-assisted nucleic acid detection approach is built around the Cas12a nuclease, using its cis- and trans-cleavage activities on single-stranded DNA to detect target nucleic acids.</data>
