      <data key="d8">QPCR</data>
      <data key="d9">OUTPERFORMS</data>
      <data key="d10">Conventional qPCR is reported to achieve superior assay performance compared with one-pot CRISPR–NAA assays when Cas12a activity is not optimally tuned, indicating that such one-pot assays can be less sensitive than qPCR.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
