    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="RECOMBINASE POLYMERASE AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">RPA</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d10">The TRACE assay incorporates asynchronous recombinase polymerase amplification as its low-temperature nucleic acid amplification step to accumulate target amplicons before CRISPR/Cas12b detection. | The TRACE assay incorporates RPA to amplify the conserved MPXV J2L region prior to or during Cas12a detection, enhancing sensitivity for low viral load samples. | The TRACE assay is compatible with RPA as an isothermal amplification method to amplify MPXV DNA before or during CRISPR-based detection. | The TRACE assay incorporates RPA as its nucleic acid amplification step, using RPA’s lower optimal temperature range to promote amplicon accumulation before Cas12b-mediated trans-cleavage is activated. | The TRACE assay is formulated alongside RPA pellets, and both lyophilized CRISPR and RPA pellets are stored and tested together, indicating that TRACE uses RPA as a pre- or co-amplification step to increase nucleic acid target copies before CRISPR detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.98</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
