      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">GRNA</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_GUIDE</data>
      <data key="d10">TRACE relies on a guide RNA that complexes with Cas12b to form a ribonucleoprotein complex, conferring sequence-specific recognition of the amplified nucleic acid target. | The TRACE assay uses a guide RNA to direct Cas12b to the MPXV J2L gene target; optimization of the gRNA:ssRNA blocker ratio (1:4) improved signal and signal-to-noise.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="SSRNA BLOCKER">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">SSRNA BLOCKER</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_GUIDE</data>
      <data key="d10">TRACE employs a single-stranded RNA blocker that anneals to the guide RNA at low temperature to prevent Cas12b:gRNA complex assembly and suppress target cleavage during the amplification stage.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="LYSED CLINICAL SAMPLES">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">LYSED CLINICAL SAMPLES</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">TRACE is designed for direct addition of lysed clinical samples into lyophilized reagents, making sample lysis a required preparation step before the one-pot reaction.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="TWO-STAGE INCUBATION PROCEDURE">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">TWO-STAGE INCUBATION PROCEDURE</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The operation of TRACE is defined by a two-stage incubation procedure that temporally separates RPA and Cas12b activities via low- and high-temperature phases to optimize amplification and detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
