      <data key="d8">CAS12A</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">The TRACE assay employs Cas12a as its CRISPR effector nuclease to recognize MPXV J2L targets and generate a detectable signal. | The TRACE assay uses Cas12a in its first stage and then immediately inactivates Cas12a at the start of the second stage so that only Cas12b-driven detection contributes to the reporter signal.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
