      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="IN-SILICO SPECIFICITY PROFILE FOR MPXV J2L TARGETING">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">IN-SILICO SPECIFICITY PROFILE FOR MPXV J2L TARGETING</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
      <data key="d10">The TRACE assay design is supported by an in-silico specificity profile showing 99.6% coverage of reported MPXV strains with complete predicted specificity for the J2L region.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="CAS12B">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">CAS12B</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">The TRACE assay employs Cas12b as its core CRISPR effector nuclease to mediate target-dependent cis- and trans-cleavage of nucleic acids and reporters. | The TRACE assay employs Cas12b as its CRISPR effector nuclease, leveraging its activity at elevated temperatures to cleave the poly T reporter upon target recognition. | The TRACE one-pot assay employs Cas12b as its CRISPR effector enzyme, leveraging Cas12b’s higher temperature preference to perform trans-cleavage after the lower-temperature amplification phase has completed. | The TRACE assay employs Cas12b as the effector enzyme in its second stage, where newly formed Cas12b/J2L gRNA complexes recognize the J2L target and generate reporter signal.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="37 °C AMPLIFICATION PHASE">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">37 °C AMPLIFICATION PHASE</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d10">The TRACE assay includes a 37 °C amplification phase in which target nucleic acids are amplified while Cas12b activity is temporarily suppressed by ssRNA blockers.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="100 COPIES/TEST">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">10 COPIES/TEST</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_LOD</data>
      <data key="d10">In its initial configuration with incomplete attenuation of Cas12b-mediated amplicon cleavage, the TRACE assay exhibits a limit of detection of 10 copies per test.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="2.5 COPIES/TEST">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">2.5 COPIES/TEST</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_LOD</data>
      <data key="d10">After introducing ssRNA blockers to modulate Cas12b activity during the 37 °C amplification phase, the TRACE assay achieves an improved limit of detection of 2.5 copies per test.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="WEAK REPORTER SIGNAL">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">WEAK REPORTER SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">During the first stage of the assay, TRACE produces a weak reporter signal that reveals residual Cas12b activity despite attempts to attenuate cleavage.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="STRONG SIGNAL">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">STRONG SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">Under optimized conditions with appropriately designed ssRNA blockers, the TRACE assay produces a strong reporter signal indicative of effective target detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="TRACE ASSAY ANALYTICAL AND CLINICAL VALIDATION">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">TRACE ASSAY ANALYTICAL AND CLINICAL VALIDATION</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The analytical and clinical validation program, including systematic optimization of one-pot parameters, is used to establish the performance characteristics of the TRACE assay.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="TWO-POT RPA/CAS12A ASSAY">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">TWO-POT RPA/CAS12A ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d9">OUTPERFORMS</data>
      <data key="d10">With an improved limit of detection of 2.5 copies/test in a one-pot format, the TRACE assay achieves sensitivity comparable to the benchmark two-pot RPA/Cas12a assay while offering a simpler workflow.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_13</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="MPXV">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">MPXV</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The TRACE assay is designed to detect MPXV by targeting its genomic DNA, enabling sensitive detection of monkeypox virus in nucleic acid samples. | The TRACE assay is designed and optimized to detect MPXV nucleic acid, generating positive signals only in samples from MPXV-infected patients and not in samples where MPXV infection was ruled out. | The one-pot TRACE assay detects MPXV DNA released by the lysis protocol, forming the core detection chemistry underlying the lateral flow format. | In-silico analyses suggest that the current TRACE assay design should provide robust coverage of reported MPXV strains, indicating that the platform is intended to detect MPXV lineages circulating in endemic regions. | The TRACE assay is a CRISPR-based diagnostic specifically developed to detect MPXV, including genetically diverse lineages circulating in endemic regions. | The duplex TRACE assay detects MPXV by monitoring the stage-2 fluorescence signal (ΔF2) attributed to the MPXV J2L gene; samples with ΔF2 above threshold T2 are considered MPXV J2L-positive, indicating MPXV presence. | The TRACE assay is applied to nucleic acid samples from suspected MPXV clinical cases, indicating that it is designed to detect MPXV genetic material.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.96</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="MPXV DNA">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">MPXV DNA</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The TRACE assay directly detects MPXV DNA, using CRISPR-Cas12b and a guide RNA to recognize the viral DNA target and trigger reporter cleavage.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="J2L GENE">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">J2L GENE</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The TRACE assay specifically targets the MPXV J2L gene region as its primary detection locus, with limits of detection expressed in J2L gene copies per test. | Within the TRACE assay, the stage-2 fluorescence signal (ΔF2) is specifically attributed to the J2L gene target, and exceeding threshold T2 classifies a sample as J2L-positive.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="SSRNA BLOCKER 1-S14">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">SSRNA BLOCKER 1-S14</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_GUIDE</data>
      <data key="d10">The TRACE assay uses ssRNA blocker 1-S14 in combination with gRNA at a 1:4 gRNA:ssRNA ratio to modulate Cas12b activity and enhance signal-to-noise.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_14</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="FUSION GRNA WITH APPENDED SSRNA BLOCKING SEQUENCE">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">FUSION GRNA WITH APPENDED SSRNA BLOCKING SEQUENCE</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_GUIDE</data>
      <data key="d10">Fusion gRNAs with appended ssRNA blocking sequences were evaluated but showed complex behavior and were excluded from subsequent TRACE assay optimization and use.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
