      <data key="d8">TRACE ASSAY VALIDATION IN LARGE INDEPENDENT COHORTS</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">TRACE diagnostic performance estimates are recommended to be validated in large, independent cohorts of distinct specimen types.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_36</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE ASSAY" target="TRACE ASSAY VALIDATION ACROSS DIVERSE MPXV LINEAGES">
      <data key="d7">TRACE ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">TRACE ASSAY VALIDATION ACROSS DIVERSE MPXV LINEAGES</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">Future studies should validate TRACE using MPXV lineages from a wider range of endemic geographic sites to assess performance with genetically diverse strains.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_36</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
