      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">Executing the 18-min TRACE protocol (10 min at 37 °C plus 8 min at 60 °C) on patient samples yields the specific reporter signal at the 18-minute endpoint that is used for MPXV detection and semi-quantitative viral load estimation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.74</data>
