    <edge source="TRACE DUPLEX ASSAY" target="MPXV">
      <data key="d7">TRACE DUPLEX ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">MPXV</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The TRACE duplex assay is designed to detect Monkeypox virus (MPXV) as one of its primary targets, resolving MPXV-derived signal in the second, high-temperature stage. | The TRACE duplex assay detects MPXV infection status by targeting the viral J2L gene in clinical and biobank specimens.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
