    </edge>
    <edge source="TRACE DUPLEX ASSAY" target="CAS12A">
      <data key="d7">TRACE DUPLEX ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">CAS12A</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">During the first 37 °C stage, the TRACE duplex assay employs Cas12a as the active CRISPR nuclease to generate RNase P–specific fluorescent signal. | The TRACE duplex assay incorporates Cas12a, whose concentration (1000–125 nM as Cas12a–gRNA complexes) is optimized to balance RNase P and J2L detection and minimize residual activity in the second phase.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.96</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
