      <data key="d7">TRACE DUPLEX ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">CAS12B</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">In the second, 64 °C stage, the TRACE duplex assay uses Cas12b as the active CRISPR nuclease to detect MPXV J2L and generate ΔF2 signal after ssRNA blocker release. | The optimized TRACE duplex assay uses Cas12b at 400 nM as a CRISPR effector enzyme in the final duplex reaction to support dual-target detection alongside Cas12a.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.93</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_25</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
