      <data key="d8">ORTHOPOXVIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
      <data key="d10">Non-MPXV orthopoxvirus genomes in the database are used to assess potential cross-reactivity of primers and gRNAs with closely related viruses.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="IN-SILICO MPXV AND NON-MPXV REFERENCE DATABASE" target="HERPES SIMPLEX VIRUS TYPE 1">
      <data key="d7">IN-SILICO MPXV AND NON-MPXV REFERENCE DATABASE</data>
      <data key="d8">HERPES SIMPLEX VIRUS TYPE 1</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
      <data key="d10">HSV-1 genomes in the database serve as non-target controls to evaluate off-target binding of primers and gRNAs and thus contribute to the assay’s specificity profile. | HSV-2 genomes are included as additional non-target sequences to test whether the designed assay components cross-react with this human pathogen.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d_chunk_38</data>
      <data key="d14">6f94756d-fd42-4a77-b6b1-d9dc6901591d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="IN-SILICO MPXV AND NON-MPXV REFERENCE DATABASE" target="VARICELLA-ZOSTER VIRUS">
      <data key="d7">IN-SILICO MPXV AND NON-MPXV REFERENCE DATABASE</data>
      <data key="d8">VARICELLA-ZOSTER VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
