      <data key="d7">IMPEDANCE-BASED BIOSENSORS</data>
      <data key="d8">ELISA</data>
      <data key="d9">OUTPERFORMS</data>
      <data key="d10">Impedance-based biosensors are implied to have better sensitivity than conventional ELISA in the low viral concentration regime relevant to early infection in water and aerosols.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.6</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="IMPEDANCE-BASED BIOSENSORS" target="LATERAL-FLOW FORMATS">
      <data key="d7">IMPEDANCE-BASED BIOSENSORS</data>
      <data key="d8">LATERAL-FLOW FORMATS</data>
      <data key="d9">OUTPERFORMS</data>
      <data key="d10">Impedance-based biosensors are implied to outperform conventional lateral-flow formats when detecting low viral concentrations in water and aerosols, due to their lower effective limit of detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.6</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_39</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
