      <data key="d7">ELECTROCHEMICAL DEVICES</data>
      <data key="d8">H5N1 AVIAN INFLUENZA VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Electrochemical devices detect H5N1 avian influenza virus by measuring viral RNA or antigens directly from swabbed or environmental matrices in under one hour.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SPR APTASENSOR" target="HPAI AVIAN INFLUENZA VIRUSES">
      <data key="d7">SPR APTASENSOR</data>
      <data key="d8">H5N1 AVIAN INFLUENZA VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The SPR aptasensor is specifically designed to detect H5N1 avian influenza virus, resolving a broad range of viral loads within approximately 1.5 hours using aptamer-mediated surface plasmon resonance.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SPR APTASENSOR" target="H5N1">
      <data key="d7">SPR APTASENSOR</data>
      <data key="d8">H5N1</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The SPR aptasensor targets H5N1, referenced in shorthand, confirming its specificity for this avian influenza subtype across a broad viral-load range.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HANDHELD NANOPORE PLATFORMS" target="AVIAN INFLUENZA A H5N1 VIRUS">
      <data key="d7">HANDHELD NANOPORE PLATFORMS</data>
      <data key="d8">AVIAN INFLUENZA A VIRUSES</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Handheld nanopore platforms generate same-day genomic data that enable detection and pathotyping of avian influenza A viruses, supporting rapid molecular epidemiology in field and laboratory settings.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ON-FARM CONFIRMATION ASSAY RUNS" target="CAPACITIVE BIOSENSOR FOR RAPID DETECTION OF AVIAN (H5N1) INFLUENZA AND E. COLI IN AEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">ON-FARM CONFIRMATION ASSAY RUNS</data>
      <data key="d8">CAPACITIVE BIOSENSOR FOR RAPID DETECTION OF AVIAN (H5N1) INFLUENZA AND E. COLI IN AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">On-farm confirmation assay runs provide field data that help validate the performance of the capacitive biosensor platform under real-world conditions when anomalies are flagged by nontargeted screens.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.5</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_47</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CAPACITIVE BIOSENSOR INTEGRATED WITH A WET-CYCLONE BIOAEROSOL SAMPLER" target="AIRBORNE H5N1">
      <data key="d7">CAPACITIVE BIOSENSOR INTEGRATED WITH A WET-CYCLONE BIOAEROSOL SAMPLER</data>
      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE H5N1</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The integrated capacitive biosensor–wet cyclone platform is configured and demonstrated to detect airborne H5N1 influenza virus in aerosols in near real time.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.98</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_49</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CAPACITIVE BIOSENSOR INTEGRATED WITH A WET-CYCLONE BIOAEROSOL SAMPLER" target="WET-CYCLONE BIOAEROSOL SAMPLER">
      <data key="d7">CAPACITIVE BIOSENSOR INTEGRATED WITH A WET-CYCLONE BIOAEROSOL SAMPLER</data>
      <data key="d8">WET-CYCLONE BIOAEROSOL SAMPLER</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">The capacitive biosensor platform relies on the wet-cyclone bioaerosol sampler as an upstream sample collection and preparation step to convert airborne particles into a liquid sample suitable for impedance-based detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_49</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CAPACITIVE BIOSENSOR INTEGRATED WITH A WET-CYCLONE BIOAEROSOL SAMPLER" target="IMPEDANCE-BASED QUANTITATIVE SIGNAL">
      <data key="d7">CAPACITIVE BIOSENSOR INTEGRATED WITH A WET-CYCLONE BIOAEROSOL SAMPLER</data>
      <data key="d8">IMPEDANCE-BASED QUANTITATIVE SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">Upon binding of target analytes such as airborne H5N1, the capacitive biosensor produces an impedance-based quantitative signal that reports both presence and approximate concentration of the pathogen.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_49</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
