    <edge source="MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA" target="H5N1 AVIAN INFLUENZA A VIRUS">
      <data key="d7">MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA</data>
      <data key="d8">H5N1 AVIAN INFLUENZA A VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The microfluidic electrochemical chip is designed to detect H5N1 by targeting DNA sequences derived from its viral genome, enabling quantitative measurement of H5N1-associated nucleic acids.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA" target="LIMIT OF DETECTION 0.16 FM">
      <data key="d7">MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA</data>
      <data key="d8">LIMIT OF DETECTION 0.16 FM</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_LOD</data>
      <data key="d10">Under optimized conditions, the microfluidic electrochemical chip achieves a limit of detection of 0.16 fM for H5N1-target DNA, reflecting its high analytical sensitivity.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA" target="LINEAR RANGE 1 FM–1 NM">
      <data key="d7">MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA</data>
      <data key="d8">LINEAR RANGE 1 FM–1 NM</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
      <data key="d10">The microfluidic electrochemical chip exhibits a quantitative linear response for H5N1-target DNA over the concentration range 1 fM–1 nM under optimized assay conditions.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA" target="REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION">
      <data key="d7">MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA</data>
      <data key="d8">REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">For clinical or environmental deployment on H5N1, the chip requires a reverse transcription step to convert viral RNA into DNA prior to electrochemical detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA" target="NUCLEIC ACID EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d7">MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA</data>
      <data key="d8">NUCLEIC-ACID EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">The platform requires nucleic-acid extraction from clinical or environmental samples as part of a multistep workflow before H5N1-target DNA can be measured.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA" target="THERMAL DENATURATION">
      <data key="d7">MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA</data>
      <data key="d8">THERMAL DENATURATION</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">Thermal denaturation is needed to separate nucleic-acid strands, enabling efficient hybridization of H5N1-target sequences on the chip’s aptamer interface.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_52</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA" target="NUCLEIC-ACID HYBRIDIZATION AT APTAMER INTERFACE">
      <data key="d7">MICROFLUIDIC ELECTROCHEMICAL CHIP USING CATALYTIC REDOX-RECYCLING FOR INFLUENZA VIRUS DNA</data>
      <data key="d8">NUCLEIC-ACID HYBRIDIZATION AT APTAMER INTERFACE</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">A hybridization step at the aptamer-functionalized interface is required for the chip to specifically bind H5N1-target DNA, which in turn modulates the redox-recycling current for quantitative readout.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_52</data>
