    <edge source="LABEL-FREE SERS DETECTION OF PATHOGENIC ENVELOPED VIRUSES USING MACHINE LEARNING DATA ANALYTICS" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">LABEL-FREE SERS DETECTION OF PATHOGENIC ENVELOPED VIRUSES USING MACHINE LEARNING DATA ANALYTICS</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The label-free SERS platform, coupled with machine-learning-based spectral analysis, detects SARS-CoV-2 by identifying its characteristic Raman fingerprints in complex samples such as aerosols, dust, and animal-derived materials without requiring virus-specific antibodies or primers.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LABEL-FREE SERS DETECTION OF PATHOGENIC ENVELOPED VIRUSES USING MACHINE LEARNING DATA ANALYTICS" target="INFLUENZA A">
      <data key="d7">LABEL-FREE SERS DETECTION OF PATHOGENIC ENVELOPED VIRUSES USING MACHINE LEARNING DATA ANALYTICS</data>
      <data key="d8">INFLUENZA A</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The SERS–machine learning biosensor detects influenza A by discriminating its virus-specific spectral patterns from other viral and environmental signals in mixed dust and similar complex matrices.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LABEL-FREE SERS DETECTION OF PATHOGENIC ENVELOPED VIRUSES USING MACHINE LEARNING DATA ANALYTICS" target="ZIKA VIRUS">
      <data key="d7">LABEL-FREE SERS DETECTION OF PATHOGENIC ENVELOPED VIRUSES USING MACHINE LEARNING DATA ANALYTICS</data>
      <data key="d8">ZIKA VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The label-free SERS platform identifies Zika virus signatures within complex environmental dust samples by leveraging machine-learning classification of Raman spectra.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LABEL-FREE SERS DETECTION OF PATHOGENIC ENVELOPED VIRUSES USING MACHINE LEARNING DATA ANALYTICS" target="OVER 86% CLASSIFICATION ACCURACY">
      <data key="d7">LABEL-FREE SERS DETECTION OF PATHOGENIC ENVELOPED VIRUSES USING MACHINE LEARNING DATA ANALYTICS</data>
      <data key="d8">OVER 86% CLASSIFICATION ACCURACY</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The SERS–machine learning platform’s ability to distinguish multiple enveloped viruses in mixed dust matrices is validated by achieving over 86% classification accuracy when discriminating SARS-CoV-2, influenza A, and Zika virus signatures. | The broader performance of the label-free SERS detection approach as a surveillance tool in animal populations is supported by validation studies reporting classification accuracies often exceeding 90% without virus-specific antibodies or primers.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MACHINE LEARNING-DRIVEN SERS FINGERPRINTING OF DISINTEGRATED VIRAL COMPONENTS FOR RAPID DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 IN ENVIRONMENTAL DUST" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">MACHINE LEARNING-DRIVEN SERS FINGERPRINTING OF DISINTEGRATED VIRAL COMPONENTS FOR RAPID DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 IN ENVIRONMENTAL DUST</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">This specific SERS fingerprinting methodology is designed to rapidly detect and classify SARS-CoV-2 in environmental dust by analyzing Raman spectra of disintegrated viral components with multivariate machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.98</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MACHINE LEARNING-DRIVEN SERS FINGERPRINTING OF DISINTEGRATED VIRAL COMPONENTS FOR RAPID DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 IN ENVIRONMENTAL DUST" target="VIRION DISINTEGRATION">
      <data key="d7">MACHINE LEARNING-DRIVEN SERS FINGERPRINTING OF DISINTEGRATED VIRAL COMPONENTS FOR RAPID DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 IN ENVIRONMENTAL DUST</data>
      <data key="d8">VIRION DISINTEGRATION</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">The SERS fingerprinting platform requires virion disintegration as a preparatory step to release viral proteins, lipids, and nucleic acids, which enrich the Raman signal used for machine-learning-based detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MACHINE LEARNING-DRIVEN SERS FINGERPRINTING OF DISINTEGRATED VIRAL COMPONENTS FOR RAPID DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 IN ENVIRONMENTAL DUST" target="GENTLE LYSIS PROTOCOL">
      <data key="d7">MACHINE LEARNING-DRIVEN SERS FINGERPRINTING OF DISINTEGRATED VIRAL COMPONENTS FOR RAPID DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 IN ENVIRONMENTAL DUST</data>
      <data key="d8">GENTLE LYSIS PROTOCOL</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">The platform employs a gentle lysis protocol to achieve virion disintegration in aerosol or dust samples, ensuring sufficient release of viral components while preserving informative spectral features.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MACHINE LEARNING-DRIVEN SERS FINGERPRINTING OF DISINTEGRATED VIRAL COMPONENTS FOR RAPID DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 IN ENVIRONMENTAL DUST" target="CONCENTRATION INTO DENSELY PACKED HOTSPOTS ON A NANOSTRUCTURED SERS SUBSTRATE">
      <data key="d7">MACHINE LEARNING-DRIVEN SERS FINGERPRINTING OF DISINTEGRATED VIRAL COMPONENTS FOR RAPID DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2 IN ENVIRONMENTAL DUST</data>
      <data key="d8">CONCENTRATION INTO DENSELY PACKED HOTSPOTS ON A NANOSTRUCTURED SERS SUBSTRATE</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">The methodology includes concentrating released viral components into densely packed hotspots on a nanostructured SERS substrate, which is critical for achieving sufficient sensitivity to trace viral levels in environmental dust.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VIRION DISINTEGRATION" target="GENTLE LYSIS PROTOCOL">
      <data key="d7">VIRION DISINTEGRATION</data>
      <data key="d8">GENTLE LYSIS PROTOCOL</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">In this methodology, virion disintegration is operationally implemented via a gentle lysis protocol, which is the specific sample preparation procedure used to achieve controlled disruption of intact virions in aerosol or dust samples for SERS analysis.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_57</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SERS-BASED VIRAL DETECTION WORKFLOW IN CLEAN CELL SUPERNATANT" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">SERS-BASED VIRAL DETECTION WORKFLOW IN CLEAN CELL SUPERNATANT</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The SERS workflow in clean cell supernatant differentiates and identifies SARS-CoV-2 based on average SERS spectra and PCA-LDA analysis.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.96</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_58</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SERS-BASED VIRAL DETECTION WORKFLOW IN CLEAN CELL SUPERNATANT" target="INFLUENZA A">
