    <edge source="TIER 1 ON-FARM HPAI SURVEILLANCE" target="HIGHLY PATHOGENIC AVIAN INFLUENZA">
      <data key="d7">TIER 1 ON-FARM HPAI SURVEILLANCE</data>
      <data key="d8">HIGHLY PATHOGENIC AVIAN INFLUENZA</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Tier 1 surveillance is designed to detect early anomalies that may indicate highly pathogenic avian influenza in poultry houses by integrating behavioral and airborne biosensor signals, enabling minutes-to-hours response times.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_68</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TIER 1 ON-FARM HPAI SURVEILLANCE" target="TIER 2 RAPID MOLECULAR AND ELECTROCHEMICAL ASSAYS">
      <data key="d7">TIER 1 ON-FARM HPAI SURVEILLANCE</data>
      <data key="d8">TIER 2 RAPID MOLECULAR AND ELECTROCHEMICAL ASSAYS</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">Tier 1 anomaly alerts are followed by Tier 2 confirmatory assays, which validate whether Tier 1-detected anomalies correspond to true HPAI infection events.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_68</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TIER 2 RAPID MOLECULAR AND ELECTROCHEMICAL ASSAYS" target="HIGHLY PATHOGENIC AVIAN INFLUENZA">
      <data key="d7">TIER 2 RAPID MOLECULAR AND ELECTROCHEMICAL ASSAYS</data>
      <data key="d8">HIGHLY PATHOGENIC AVIAN INFLUENZA</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Tier 2 assays provide confirmatory detection of highly pathogenic avian influenza following Tier 1 anomalies, using rapid molecular and electrochemical biosensor methods to classify samples as positive or negative within 30–60 minutes.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.94</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_68</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TIER 2 RAPID MOLECULAR AND ELECTROCHEMICAL ASSAYS" target="CRISPR-CAS13A">
      <data key="d7">TIER 2 RAPID MOLECULAR AND ELECTROCHEMICAL ASSAYS</data>
      <data key="d8">CRISPR-CAS12A</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">Within Tier 2, one of the rapid molecular assay options uses the CRISPR-Cas12a effector enzyme to enable sequence-specific recognition and detection of HPAI nucleic acids.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_68</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TIER 2 RAPID MOLECULAR AND ELECTROCHEMICAL ASSAYS" target="RT-LAMP">
      <data key="d7">TIER 2 RAPID MOLECULAR AND ELECTROCHEMICAL ASSAYS</data>
      <data key="d8">RT-LAMP</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d10">Tier 2 employs RT-LAMP as a rapid isothermal amplification method to increase viral nucleic acid copies for sensitive detection of HPAI in suspected samples.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_68</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TIER 2 RAPID MOLECULAR AND ELECTROCHEMICAL ASSAYS" target="ELECTROCHEMICAL IMPEDANCE ASSAYS">
