      <data key="d8">INFLUENZA A VIRUS</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The magnetic quantum dot nanobead test-strip biosensor detects influenza A virus by magnetically enriching virus-bound nanobeads and using quantum dot fluorescence on the strip to provide an ultrasensitive readout.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.97</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b_chunk_111</data>
      <data key="d14">de3c3a3b-6855-4b40-bff9-eef9df2e0d4b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CRISPR/CAS12 SYSTEM" target="COLLATERAL CLEAVAGE ACTIVITY OF CAS12">
      <data key="d7">CRISPR/CAS12 SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d8">COLLATERAL CLEAVAGE ACTIVITY OF CAS12</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">CRISPR/Cas12 diagnostic platforms exploit Cas12’s collateral cleavage of single-stranded DNA as the core reporter signal, which is triggered after target recognition. | CRISPR/Cas13 diagnostic platforms use Cas13’s collateral cleavage of single-stranded RNA as the reporter signal, activated upon binding to the target RNA sequence.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.98</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
