      <data key="d8">CAS12</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">The CRISPR-Cas12b-assisted platform relies on a Cas12b nuclease, a member of the Cas12 family, as the effector enzyme for nucleic acid detection and methylation analysis.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CRISPR/CAS12A-BASED BIOSENSOR" target="CAS12">
      <data key="d7">CRISPR/CAS12A-BASED BIOSENSOR</data>
      <data key="d8">CAS12</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">The CRISPR/Cas12a-based biosensor uses Cas12a, a specific Cas12-family nuclease, as its effector enzyme to drive target recognition and collateral cleavage of a DNA reporter.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CRISPR/CAS12A-BASED BIOSENSOR" target="DNA REPORTER FOR CRISPR/CAS12A">
      <data key="d7">CRISPR/CAS12A-BASED BIOSENSOR</data>
      <data key="d8">DNA REPORTER FOR CRISPR/CAS12A</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">The Cas12a-based biosensor generates its detection signal by Cas12a-mediated cleavage of a specially designed DNA reporter, converting collateral activity into a measurable output such as fluorescence.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.92</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CRISPR/DCAS9 COLORIMETRIC ASSAY" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">CRISPR/DCAS9 COLORIMETRIC ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The CRISPR/dCas9 colorimetric assay is explicitly described as detecting SARS-CoV-2 by using dCas9-mediated target recognition to trigger a colorimetric signal.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CRISPR/DCAS9 COLORIMETRIC ASSAY" target="DRUG-RESISTANT PH1N1">
      <data key="d7">CRISPR/DCAS9 COLORIMETRIC ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">DRUG-RESISTANT PH1N1</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The CRISPR/dCas9 colorimetric assay is reported to detect drug-resistant pH1N1 influenza virus, indicating its applicability to multiple airborne viral targets.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CRISPR/DCAS9 COLORIMETRIC ASSAY" target="COLORIMETRIC READOUT">
      <data key="d7">CRISPR/DCAS9 COLORIMETRIC ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">COLORIMETRIC READOUT</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">Upon successful target binding, the CRISPR/dCas9 assay produces a colorimetric readout, providing a visible signal that indicates presence of SARS-CoV-2 or drug-resistant pH1N1.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="STRINGENT CLEAVAGE-SITE PROXIMITY REQUIREMENT" target="CRISPR/CAS12 SYSTEM">
      <data key="d7">STRINGENT CLEAVAGE-SITE PROXIMITY REQUIREMENT</data>
      <data key="d8">CRISPR/CAS12 SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The text notes that CRISPR/Cas diagnostic applications, including Cas12-based systems, face challenges due to the stringent requirement that the preferred cleavage site be in close proximity to the target sequence, highlighting a limitation in assay design. | The same stringent requirement for cleavage-site proximity is mentioned as a general challenge for CRISPR/Cas diagnostic systems, including Cas13-based platforms, constraining target and reporter design.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION (LAMP)" target="E. COLI">
      <data key="d7">LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL DNA AMPLIFICATION (LAMP)</data>
      <data key="d8">E. COLI</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">Prior work integrated thermal lysis with LAMP to detect E. coli in a one-step assay on a paper substrate, demonstrating direct bacterial detection via isothermal amplification.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL AMPLIFICATION (LAMP)" target="M. SMEGMATIS">
      <data key="d7">LOOP-MEDIATED ISOTHERMAL DNA AMPLIFICATION (LAMP)</data>
      <data key="d8">M. SMEGMATIS</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The same integrated thermal lysis–LAMP approach was applied to M. smegmatis, supporting the generalizability of high-temperature, one-step nucleic-acid detection for different bacterial species.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LIGATION CHAIN REACTION" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">LIGATION CHAIN REACTION</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The Pyrococcus furiosus Argonaute assay employs ligation chain reaction on oligonucleotides corresponding to SARS-CoV-2 sequences prior to Argonaute-directed reporter probe cleavage.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="LIGATION CHAIN REACTION" target="HPV">
      <data key="d7">LIGATION CHAIN REACTION</data>
      <data key="d8">HPV</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The same Argonaute-coupled ligation chain reaction is applied to HPV target sequences, enabling their amplification and subsequent detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_8</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE (CPKP)">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE (CPKP)</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method is reported to successfully detect carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae (CPKP), establishing it as a primary target pathogen for this platform.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING BACTERIA">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING BACTERIA</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method detects carbapenemase-producing bacteria spiked into human samples such as urine and blood, demonstrating applicability beyond a single Klebsiella strain.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method is described as operating without nucleic acid amplification, indicating that this amplification step is not used in its detection workflow.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.6</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="NUCLEIC ACID EXTRACTION">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">NUCLEIC ACID EXTRACTION</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method detects carbapenemase-producing bacteria without nucleic acid extraction, indicating that this conventional sample preparation step is not required by the platform.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="BACTERIA SWABBED FROM SURFACES">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">BACTERIA SWABBED FROM SURFACES</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">For surface-based detection, the ANCA method operates on bacteria collected via swabbing from surfaces such as pig skin, desks, gloves, scissors, knobs, and tweezers, making this swabbing step a prerequisite sample preparation step.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="THREE-DIMENSIONAL (3D) NANOPILLAR ARRAY STRUCTURE">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">THREE-DIMENSIONAL (3D) NANOPILLAR ARRAY STRUCTURE</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method is demonstrated in conjunction with a three-dimensional (3D) nanopillar array structure to directly identify bacteria swabbed from various surfaces, serving as a specific implementation and performance demonstration of the platform.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.65</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="TARGET DNA">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">TARGET DNA</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method detects the presence of target DNA by initiating a positive feedback cleavage cycle only when target DNA is present, leading to exponential amplification and signal generation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="KPC">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">KPC</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method was experimentally evaluated using KPC as the target DNA sequence, demonstrating that the amplification scheme can detect this specific analyte. | The ANCA method is applied in a KPC-targeted assay run, detecting KPC carbapenemase gene DNA and generating time-dependent fluorescence curves across KPC concentrations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="FLUORESCENT SIGNAL">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">FLUORESCENCE SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">During the ANCA reaction, cleavage of reporter substrates generates an output DNA material that produces a fluorescence signal, which serves as the measurable readout of successful amplification.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="IMP">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">IMP</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method is adapted with an IMP-specific circuit in an assay run to detect IMP carbapenemase gene DNA, enabling quantification over a 1 fM to 1 nM range.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="VIM">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">VIM</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">VIM-specific circuits within the ANCA method are used in an assay run to detect VIM carbapenemase gene DNA, with performance characterized by linear response and a sub-femtomolar LOD.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="NDM">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">NDM</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">NDM-specific circuits in the ANCA method are used in an assay run to detect NDM carbapenemase gene DNA, allowing sensitivity evaluation and LOD calculation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="OXA-48">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">OXA-48</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">OXA-48-specific circuits in the ANCA method are used in an assay run to detect OXA-48 carbapenemase gene DNA, contributing to the panel of targets assessed.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="TIME-DEPENDENT FLUORESCENCE INTENSITIES">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">TIME-DEPENDENT FLUORESCENCE INTENSITIES</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method produces time-dependent fluorescence intensities as its reporter signal, with a defined threshold intensity of 10,000 used to determine threshold times and construct calibration curves.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="ASSAY SENSITIVITY EVALUATION">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">ASSAY SENSITIVITY EVALUATION</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method is validated by sensitivity evaluation, including determination of linearity (R² = 0.99), dynamic range, and limits of detection for KPC, IMP, VIM, NDM, and OXA-48 assay runs.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="PREVIOUS AGO-BASED METHODS WITHOUT PRE-AMPLIFICATION">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">PREVIOUS AGO-BASED METHODS WITHOUT PRE-AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d9">OUTPERFORMS</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method demonstrates superior sensitivity compared to previous Ago protein-based nucleic-acid detection methods that do not use pre-amplification.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_16</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="CPKP">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">CPKP</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method directly detects carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae in buffer, urine, and blood without conventional pre-processing, enabling rapid diagnosis of antibiotic-resistant infections.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="K. PNEU (IMP)">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">K. PNEU (IMP)</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method enables direct identification of IMP-type carbapenemase-producing K. pneumoniae, demonstrating its capability to resolve specific carbapenemase resistance genotypes.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="K. PNEU (WT)">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">K. PNEU (WT)</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method, via carbapenemase-specific circuits, discriminates between wild-type K. pneumoniae and carbapenemase-producing K. pneumoniae, indicating specificity for resistance determinants.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="PRE-CONCENTRATION">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">PRE-CONCENTRATION</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method does not require a pre-concentration step, simplifying the workflow compared with conventional molecular assays that often concentrate bacteria or nucleic acids before detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="LYSIS">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">LYSIS</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA method eliminates the need for a separate lysis step; bacterial lysis occurs implicitly during the high-temperature reaction rather than as a distinct sample preparation process.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="RNA PURIFICATION">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">DNA PURIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA workflow does not require DNA purification, reducing complexity and time-to-result compared with standard nucleic-acid testing protocols that include cleanup steps.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="BUFFER MATRIX">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">BUFFER MATRIX</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
      <data key="d10">In buffer, the ANCA method, using carbapenemase-specific circuits, discriminates between wild-type K. pneumoniae and CPKP based on T0 – T values as a function of bacterial concentration.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="URINE MATRIX (99%)">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">URINE MATRIX (99%)</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
      <data key="d10">In 99% urine, the ANCA method directly detects CPKP without pre-concentration, lysis, or DNA purification, demonstrating robust performance in a clinically relevant matrix.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA METHOD" target="BLOOD MATRIX (99%)">
      <data key="d7">ANCA METHOD</data>
      <data key="d8">BLOOD MATRIX (99%)</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
      <data key="d10">In 99% blood, the ANCA method directly detects CPKP without separate sample preparation steps, indicating compatibility with complex blood matrices for rapid diagnosis.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_20</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA ASSAY" target="CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE (CPKP)">
      <data key="d7">ANCA ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">CARBAPENEMASE-PRODUCING KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE (CPKP)</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">In clinical use, the ANCA assay detects carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella pneumoniae (CPKP) in rectal swab specimens from infected patients.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA ASSAY" target="RECTAL SWAB SPECIMENS">
      <data key="d7">ANCA ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">RECTAL SWAB SPECIMENS</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA assay uses rectal swab specimens as the clinical sample type for diagnosing CPKP-infected patients, so collection of rectal swabs is a required pre-analytical step.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA ASSAY" target="CLINICAL SENSITIVITY AND SPECIFICITY OF 100% AND 100%">
      <data key="d7">ANCA ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">CLINICAL SENSITIVITY AND SPECIFICITY OF 100% AND 100%</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_SPECIFICITY</data>
      <data key="d10">When applied to diagnose CPKP-infected patients using rectal swab specimens, the ANCA assay exhibits a performance profile of 100% clinical sensitivity and 100% clinical specificity.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA ASSAY" target="DIAGNOSE CPKP-INFECTED PATIENTS USING RECTAL SWAB SPECIMENS">
      <data key="d7">ANCA ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">DIAGNOSE CPKP-INFECTED PATIENTS USING RECTAL SWAB SPECIMENS</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA assay’s diagnostic performance is established through its application to rectal swab specimens from CPKP-infected patients, constituting a clinical validation study.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ANCA ASSAY" target="POINT-OF-CARE BACTERIAL TESTING">
      <data key="d7">ANCA ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">POINT-OF-CARE BACTERIAL TESTING</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The ANCA assay is proposed and partially validated for point-of-care bacterial testing, highlighting its suitability for early-stage infection diagnosis and improved clinical decision-making.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.6</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TARGET DNA" target="FLUORESCENT SIGNAL">
      <data key="d7">TARGET DNA</data>
      <data key="d8">FLUORESCENCE SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">The presence of target DNA indirectly leads to an increase in fluorescence signal by triggering and sustaining the ANCA positive feedback loop, which generates fluorescent reporter output.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_12</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="KPC" target="FLUORESCENT SIGNAL">
      <data key="d7">KPC</data>
      <data key="d8">FLUORESCENCE SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">When KPC DNA is present as the target in the ANCA assay, strong fluorescence signals are observed, indicating that KPC-driven amplification yields a robust reporter output.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_12</data>
