      <data key="d7">CRISPR-BASED DIAGNOSTICS (GENERAL)</data>
      <data key="d8">CRISPR-CAS12B</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">General CRISPR-based diagnostic platforms can incorporate Cas12b, as exemplified by the HOLMESv2 platform, for nucleic acid detection and epigenetic analysis.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_50</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PFAGO-BASED DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">PFAGO-BASED DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">DETECTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The PfAgo-based biosensor platform developed by Wang et al. is designed to detect SARS-CoV-2 nucleic acids for diagnostic purposes.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.98</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_56</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ARGONAUTE INTEGRATED SINGLE-TUBE PCR SYSTEM" target="PCR">
      <data key="d7">ARGONAUTE INTEGRATED SINGLE-TUBE PCR SYSTEM</data>
      <data key="d8">PCR</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_AMPLIFICATION</data>
      <data key="d10">The Argonaute integrated single-tube PCR system incorporates PCR as its core amplification method to achieve supersensitive detection of rare mutations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.96</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b_chunk_56</data>
      <data key="d14">8cd80207-0825-48ce-af82-eed721eee13b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CAS13A-BASED NUCLEIC ACID DETECTION PLATFORM" target="CAS13A">
      <data key="d7">CAS13A-BASED NUCLEIC ACID DETECTION PLATFORM</data>
      <data key="d8">CAS13A</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">The Cas13a-based nucleic acid detection platform employs Cas13a as its core CRISPR effector enzyme, leveraging Cas13a’s collateral ssRNA trans-cleavage activity to generate a detectable signal upon recognition of a specific nucleic acid target.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_40</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SHERLOCKV2" target="CAS13">
      <data key="d7">SHERLOCKV2</data>
      <data key="d8">CAS13</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">SHERLOCKv2 utilizes orthogonal Cas13 enzymes to enable multiplexed detection of multiple RNA targets in a single assay.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SHERLOCKV2" target="CAS12">
      <data key="d7">SHERLOCKV2</data>
      <data key="d8">CAS12</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">SHERLOCKv2 incorporates Cas12 enzymes alongside Cas13, allowing detection of DNA targets and expanding multiplexing capabilities.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SHERLOCKV2" target="CSM6">
      <data key="d7">SHERLOCKV2</data>
      <data key="d8">CSM6</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">SHERLOCKv2 combines Cas13 with the type III effector nuclease Csm6, where Cas13 activation leads to secondary activation of Csm6 to amplify reporter cleavage and increase sensitivity.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SHERLOCKV2" target="LATERAL FLOW READOUT">
      <data key="d7">SHERLOCKV2</data>
      <data key="d8">LATERAL FLOW READOUT</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">SHERLOCKv2 produces a lateral flow readout, translating CRISPR-mediated reporter cleavage into a visible band pattern on a strip for point-of-care interpretation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HUDSON" target="SHERLOCK">
      <data key="d7">HUDSON</data>
      <data key="d8">SHERLOCK</data>
      <data key="d9">REQUIRES_PREP</data>
      <data key="d10">When used for instrument-free diagnostics directly from patient samples, SHERLOCK is paired with the HUDSON protocol as a sample preparation step to inactivate nucleases and release nucleic acids.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HOLMES" target="CAS12A">
      <data key="d7">HOLMES</data>
      <data key="d8">CAS12A</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">HOLMES is a CRISPR-Cas12-based system that specifically leverages Cas12a’s DNA-targeting and collateral ssDNA cleavage activities for nucleic acid detection. | The HOLMES platform employs Cas12a as its core nuclease to recognize target DNA and trigger collateral cleavage of a reporter.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HOLMES" target="QUENCHED SSDNA REPORTER">
      <data key="d7">HOLMES</data>
      <data key="d8">QUENCHED SSDNA REPORTER</data>
      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">HOLMES couples Cas12a collateral cleavage to a quenched ssDNA reporter, producing a fluorescence signal upon target DNA recognition.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HOLMES" target="ATTOMOLAR DETECTION OF TARGET DNA">
      <data key="d7">HOLMES</data>
      <data key="d8">ATTOMOLAR DETECTION OF TARGET DNA</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_LOD</data>
      <data key="d10">HOLMES achieves attomolar-level detection of target DNA, reflecting its very low limit of detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PORTABLE CRISPR-CAS12 BIOSENSING PLATFORMS" target="CAS12A">
      <data key="d7">PORTABLE CRISPR-CAS12 BIOSENSING PLATFORMS</data>
      <data key="d8">CAS12A</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">Portable CRISPR-Cas12 biosensing platforms commonly employ Cas12 effectors such as Cas12a, exploiting their cis and trans ssDNA cleavage activities for field-deployable nucleic acid detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.86</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_41</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PORTABLE CRISPR-CAS12 BIOSENSING PLATFORMS" target="HOLMES">
      <data key="d7">PORTABLE CRISPR-CAS12 BIOSENSING PLATFORMS</data>
      <data key="d8">HOLMES</data>
      <data key="d9">OUTPERFORMS</data>
      <data key="d10">HOLMES is highlighted as a representative example within the broader class of portable Cas12-based platforms, offering a one-hour, low-cost, multipurpose and highly efficient detection system that exemplifies or surpasses typical field-ready Cas12 platforms in speed and efficiency.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
