      <data key="d9">PRODUCES_SIGNAL</data>
      <data key="d10">The DETECTR lateral flow assay produces a visible signal on a lateral flow strip to indicate the presence of SARS-CoV-2 nucleic acid.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DETECTR LATERAL FLOW ASSAY" target="CRISPR–CAS12-BASED DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">DETECTR LATERAL FLOW ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">CRISPR–CAS12-BASED DETECTION OF SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">OUTPERFORMS</data>
      <data key="d10">Within the Broughton et al. work, the DETECTR lateral flow assay is presented as a practical, rapid, point-of-care implementation of CRISPR–Cas12-based detection of SARS-CoV-2, offering improved usability and turnaround time compared with more general laboratory-based Cas12 detection formats.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.6</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_114</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="ONE-POT CRISPR-CAS12A-BASED ASSAY" target="CAS12A">
      <data key="d7">ONE-POT CRISPR-CAS12A-BASED ASSAY</data>
      <data key="d8">CAS12A</data>
      <data key="d9">USES_VARIANT</data>
      <data key="d10">The all-in-one dual CRISPR-Cas12a assay relies on Cas12a as the effector enzyme, leveraging its DNA-targeting and collateral cleavage activities for ultrasensitive detection.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f_chunk_42</data>
      <data key="d14">4b595dc6-a258-44ed-89fc-c349fc64a77f</data>
    </edge>
